127// Return reverse of "key".
128// Used to test non-lexicographic comparators.
129std::string Reverse(const Slice& key) {
130 auto rev = key.ToString();
131 std::reverse(rev.begin(), rev.end());
132 return rev;
133}
134
135class ReverseKeyComparator : public Comparator {
136 public:
137 const char* Name() const override {
138 return "rocksdb.ReverseBytewiseComparator";
139 }
140
141 int Compare(const Slice& a, const Slice& b) const override {
142 return BytewiseComparator()->Compare(Reverse(a), Reverse(b));
143 }
144
145 void FindShortestSeparator(std::string* start,
146 const Slice& limit) const override {
147 std::string s = Reverse(*start);
148 std::string l = Reverse(limit);
149 BytewiseComparator()->FindShortestSeparator(&s, l);
150 *start = Reverse(s);
151 }
152
153 void FindShortSuccessor(std::string* key) const override {
154 std::string s = Reverse(*key);
155 BytewiseComparator()->FindShortSuccessor(&s);
156 *key = Reverse(s);
157 }
158};
159
160ReverseKeyComparator reverse_key_comparator;
161
162void Increment(const Comparator* cmp, std::string* key) {
163 if (cmp == BytewiseComparator()) {
164 key->push_back('\0');
165 } else {
166 assert(cmp == &reverse_key_comparator);
167 std::string rev = Reverse(*key);
168 rev.push_back('\0');
169 *key = Reverse(rev);
170 }
171}

174 TablePropertiesCollectorFactory::Context::kUnknownColumnFamily;

178// Helper class for tests to unify the interface between
179// BlockBuilder/TableBuilder and Block/Table.
180class Constructor {
181 public:
182 explicit Constructor(const Comparator* cmp)
183 : data_(stl_wrappers::LessOfComparator(cmp)) {}
184 virtual ~Constructor() = default;
185
186 void Add(const std::string& key, const Slice& value) {
187 data_[key] = value.ToString();
188 }
189
190 // Finish constructing the data structure with all the keys that have
191 // been added so far. Returns the keys in sorted order in "*keys"
192 // and stores the key/value pairs in "*kvmap"
193 void Finish(const Options& options, const ImmutableOptions& ioptions,
194 const MutableCFOptions& moptions,
195 const BlockBasedTableOptions& table_options,
196 const InternalKeyComparator& internal_comparator,
197 std::vector<std::string>* keys, stl_wrappers::KVMap* kvmap) {
198 last_internal_comparator_ = &internal_comparator;
199 *kvmap = data_;
200 keys->clear();
201 for (const auto& kv : data_) {
202 keys->push_back(kv.first);
203 }
204 data_.clear();
205 Status s = FinishImpl(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
206 internal_comparator, *kvmap);
207 ASSERT_TRUE(s.ok()) << s.ToString();
208 }
209
210 // Construct the data structure from the data in "data"
211 virtual Status FinishImpl(const Options& options,
212 const ImmutableOptions& ioptions,
213 const MutableCFOptions& moptions,
214 const BlockBasedTableOptions& table_options,
215 const InternalKeyComparator& internal_comparator,
216 const stl_wrappers::KVMap& data) = 0;
217
218 virtual InternalIterator* NewIterator(
219 const SliceTransform* prefix_extractor = nullptr) const = 0;
220
221 virtual const stl_wrappers::KVMap& data() { return data_; }
222
223 virtual bool IsArenaMode() const { return false; }
224
225 virtual DB* db() const { return nullptr; } // Overridden in DBConstructor
226
227 virtual bool AnywayDeleteIterator() const { return false; }
228
229 protected:
230 const InternalKeyComparator* last_internal_comparator_;
231
232 private:
233 stl_wrappers::KVMap data_;
234};
235
236// A helper class that converts internal format keys into user keys
237class KeyConvertingIterator : public InternalIterator {
238 public:
239 explicit KeyConvertingIterator(InternalIterator* iter,
240 bool arena_mode = false)
241 : iter_(iter), arena_mode_(arena_mode) {}
242 ~KeyConvertingIterator() override {
243 if (arena_mode_) {
244 iter_->~InternalIterator();
245 } else {
246 delete iter_;
247 }
248 }
249 bool Valid() const override { return iter_->Valid() && status_.ok(); }
250 void Seek(const Slice& target) override {
251 ParsedInternalKey ikey(target, kMaxSequenceNumber, kTypeValue);
252 std::string encoded;
253 AppendInternalKey(&encoded, ikey);
254 iter_->Seek(encoded);
255 }
256 void SeekForPrev(const Slice& target) override {
257 ParsedInternalKey ikey(target, kMaxSequenceNumber, kTypeValue);
258 std::string encoded;
259 AppendInternalKey(&encoded, ikey);
260 iter_->SeekForPrev(encoded);
261 }
262 void SeekToFirst() override { iter_->SeekToFirst(); }
263 void SeekToLast() override { iter_->SeekToLast(); }
264 void Next() override { iter_->Next(); }
265 void Prev() override { iter_->Prev(); }
266 IterBoundCheck UpperBoundCheckResult() override {
267 return iter_->UpperBoundCheckResult();
268 }
269
270 Slice key() const override {
271 assert(Valid());
272 ParsedInternalKey parsed_key;
273 Status pik_status =
274 ParseInternalKey(iter_->key(), &parsed_key, true /* log_err_key */);
275 if (!pik_status.ok()) {
276 status_ = pik_status;
277 return Slice(status_.getState());
278 }
279 return parsed_key.user_key;
280 }
281
282 Slice value() const override { return iter_->value(); }
283 Status status() const override {
284 return status_.ok() ? iter_->status() : status_;
285 }
286
287 private:
288 mutable Status status_;
289 InternalIterator* iter_;
290 bool arena_mode_;
291
292 // No copying allowed
293 KeyConvertingIterator(const KeyConvertingIterator&) = delete;
294 void operator=(const KeyConvertingIterator&) = delete;
295};
296
297// `BlockConstructor` APIs always accept/return user keys.
298class BlockConstructor : public Constructor {
299 public:
300 explicit BlockConstructor(const Comparator* cmp)
301 : Constructor(cmp), comparator_(cmp), block_(nullptr) {}
302 ~BlockConstructor() override { delete block_; }
303 Status FinishImpl(const Options& /*options*/,
304 const ImmutableOptions& /*ioptions*/,
305 const MutableCFOptions& /*moptions*/,
306 const BlockBasedTableOptions& table_options,
307 const InternalKeyComparator& /*internal_comparator*/,
308 const stl_wrappers::KVMap& kv_map) override {
309 delete block_;
310 block_ = nullptr;
311 BlockBuilder builder(table_options.block_restart_interval);
312
313 for (const auto& kv : kv_map) {
314 // `DataBlockIter` assumes it reads only internal keys. `BlockConstructor`
315 // clients provide user keys, so we need to convert to internal key format
316 // before writing the data block.
317 ParsedInternalKey ikey(kv.first, kMaxSequenceNumber, kTypeValue);
318 std::string encoded;
319 AppendInternalKey(&encoded, ikey);
320 builder.Add(encoded, kv.second);
321 }
322 // Open the block
323 data_ = builder.Finish().ToString();
324 BlockContents contents;
325 contents.data = data_;
326 block_ = new Block(std::move(contents));
327 return Status::OK();
328 }
329 InternalIterator* NewIterator(
330 const SliceTransform* /*prefix_extractor*/) const override {
331 // `DataBlockIter` returns the internal keys it reads.
332 // `KeyConvertingIterator` converts them to user keys before they are
333 // exposed to the `BlockConstructor` clients.
334 return new KeyConvertingIterator(
335 block_->NewDataIterator(comparator_, kDisableGlobalSequenceNumber));
336 }
337
338 private:
339 const Comparator* comparator_;
340 std::string data_;
341 Block* block_;
342
343 BlockConstructor() = delete;
344};
345
346class TableConstructor : public Constructor {
347 public:
348 explicit TableConstructor(const Comparator* cmp,
349 bool convert_to_internal_key = false,
350 int level = -1, SequenceNumber largest_seqno = 0)
351 : Constructor(cmp),
352 largest_seqno_(largest_seqno),
353 convert_to_internal_key_(convert_to_internal_key),
354 level_(level) {
355 env_ = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::Env::Default();
356 }
357 ~TableConstructor() override { Reset(); }
358
359 Status FinishImpl(const Options& options, const ImmutableOptions& ioptions,
360 const MutableCFOptions& moptions,
361 const BlockBasedTableOptions& /*table_options*/,
362 const InternalKeyComparator& internal_comparator,
363 const stl_wrappers::KVMap& kv_map) override {
364 Reset();
365 soptions.use_mmap_reads = ioptions.allow_mmap_reads;
366 std::unique_ptr<FSWritableFile> sink(new test::StringSink());
367 file_writer_.reset(new WritableFileWriter(
368 std::move(sink), "" /* don't care */, FileOptions()));
369 std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder> builder;
370 InternalTblPropCollFactories internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories;
371
372 if (largest_seqno_ != 0) {
373 // Pretend that it's an external file written by SstFileWriter.
374 internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories.emplace_back(
375 new SstFileWriterPropertiesCollectorFactory(2 /* version */,
376 0 /* global_seqno*/));
377 }
378
379 std::string column_family_name;
380 const ReadOptions read_options;
381 const WriteOptions write_options;
382 builder.reset(moptions.table_factory->NewTableBuilder(
383 TableBuilderOptions(
384 ioptions, moptions, read_options, write_options,
385 internal_comparator, &internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories,
386 options.compression, options.compression_opts, kUnknownColumnFamily,
387 column_family_name, level_, kUnknownNewestKeyTime),
388 file_writer_.get()));
389
390 for (const auto& kv : kv_map) {
391 if (convert_to_internal_key_) {
392 ParsedInternalKey ikey(kv.first, kMaxSequenceNumber, kTypeValue);
393 std::string encoded;
394 AppendInternalKey(&encoded, ikey);
395 builder->Add(encoded, kv.second);
396 } else {
397 builder->Add(kv.first, kv.second);
398 }
399 EXPECT_OK(builder->status());
400 }
401 Status s = builder->Finish();
402 EXPECT_OK(file_writer_->Flush(IOOptions()));
403 EXPECT_TRUE(s.ok()) << s.ToString();
404
405 EXPECT_EQ(TEST_GetSink()->contents().size(), builder->FileSize());
406
407 // Open the table
408 file_num_ = cur_file_num_++;
409
410 return Reopen(ioptions, moptions);
411 }
412
413 InternalIterator* NewIterator(
414 const SliceTransform* prefix_extractor) const override {
415 InternalIterator* iter = table_reader_->NewIterator(
416 read_options_, prefix_extractor, /*arena=*/nullptr,
417 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized);
418 if (convert_to_internal_key_) {
419 return new KeyConvertingIterator(iter);
420 } else {
421 return iter;
422 }
423 }
424
425 uint64_t ApproximateOffsetOf(const Slice& key) const {
426 const ReadOptions read_options;
427 if (convert_to_internal_key_) {
428 InternalKey ikey(key, kMaxSequenceNumber, kTypeValue);
429 const Slice skey = ikey.Encode();
430 return table_reader_->ApproximateOffsetOf(
431 read_options, skey, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized);
432 }
433 return table_reader_->ApproximateOffsetOf(
434 read_options, key, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized);
435 }
436
437 virtual Status Reopen(const ImmutableOptions& ioptions,
438 const MutableCFOptions& moptions) {
439 std::unique_ptr<FSRandomAccessFile> source(new test::StringSource(
440 TEST_GetSink()->contents(), file_num_, ioptions.allow_mmap_reads));
441
442 file_reader_.reset(new RandomAccessFileReader(std::move(source), "test"));
443 return moptions.table_factory->NewTableReader(
444 TableReaderOptions(ioptions, moptions.prefix_extractor, soptions,
445 *last_internal_comparator_,
446 0 /* block_protection_bytes_per_key */,
447 /*skip_filters*/ false,
448 /*immortal*/ false, false, level_,
449 &block_cache_tracer_, moptions.write_buffer_size, "",
450 file_num_, kNullUniqueId64x2, largest_seqno_),
451 std::move(file_reader_), TEST_GetSink()->contents().size(),
452 &table_reader_);
453 }
454
455 virtual TableReader* GetTableReader() { return table_reader_.get(); }
456
457 bool AnywayDeleteIterator() const override {
458 return convert_to_internal_key_;
459 }
460
461 void ResetTableReader() { table_reader_.reset(); }
462
463 bool ConvertToInternalKey() { return convert_to_internal_key_; }
464
465 test::StringSink* TEST_GetSink() {
466 return static_cast<test::StringSink*>(file_writer_->writable_file());
467 }
468
469 BlockCacheTracer block_cache_tracer_;
470 Env* env_;
471
472 private:
473 void Reset() {
474 file_num_ = 0;
475 table_reader_.reset();
476 file_writer_.reset();
477 file_reader_.reset();
478 }
479
480 const ReadOptions read_options_;
481 uint64_t file_num_;
482 std::unique_ptr<WritableFileWriter> file_writer_;
483 std::unique_ptr<RandomAccessFileReader> file_reader_;
484 std::unique_ptr<TableReader> table_reader_;
485 SequenceNumber largest_seqno_;
486 bool convert_to_internal_key_;
487 int level_;
488
489 TableConstructor() = delete;
490
491 static uint64_t cur_file_num_;
492 EnvOptions soptions;
493};
494uint64_t TableConstructor::cur_file_num_ = 1;

496class MemTableConstructor : public Constructor {
497 public:
498 explicit MemTableConstructor(const Comparator* cmp, WriteBufferManager* wb)
499 : Constructor(cmp),
500 internal_comparator_(cmp),
501 write_buffer_manager_(wb),
502 table_factory_(new SkipListFactory) {
503 options_.memtable_factory = table_factory_;
504 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options_);
505 memtable_ =
506 new MemTable(internal_comparator_, ioptions, MutableCFOptions(options_),
507 wb, kMaxSequenceNumber, 0 /* column_family_id */);
508 memtable_->Ref();
509 }
510 ~MemTableConstructor() override { delete memtable_->Unref(); }
511 Status FinishImpl(const Options&, const ImmutableOptions& ioptions,
512 const MutableCFOptions& /*moptions*/,
513 const BlockBasedTableOptions& /*table_options*/,
514 const InternalKeyComparator& /*internal_comparator*/,
515 const stl_wrappers::KVMap& kv_map) override {
516 delete memtable_->Unref();
517 ImmutableOptions mem_ioptions(ioptions);
518 memtable_ = new MemTable(internal_comparator_, mem_ioptions,
519 MutableCFOptions(options_), write_buffer_manager_,
520 kMaxSequenceNumber, 0 /* column_family_id */);
521 memtable_->Ref();
522 int seq = 1;
523 for (const auto& kv : kv_map) {
524 Status s = memtable_->Add(seq, kTypeValue, kv.first, kv.second,
525 nullptr /* kv_prot_info */);
526 if (!s.ok()) {
527 return s;
528 }
529 seq++;
530 }
531 return Status::OK();
532 }
533 InternalIterator* NewIterator(
534 const SliceTransform* /*prefix_extractor*/) const override {
535 return new KeyConvertingIterator(
536 memtable_->NewIterator(ReadOptions(), /*seqno_to_time_mapping=*/nullptr,
537 &arena_, /*prefix_extractor=*/nullptr,
538 /*for_flush=*/false),
539 true);
540 }
541
542 bool AnywayDeleteIterator() const override { return true; }
543
544 bool IsArenaMode() const override { return true; }
545
546 private:
547 mutable Arena arena_;
548 InternalKeyComparator internal_comparator_;
549 Options options_;
550 WriteBufferManager* write_buffer_manager_;
551 MemTable* memtable_;
552 std::shared_ptr<SkipListFactory> table_factory_;
553};

555class InternalIteratorFromIterator : public InternalIterator {
556 public:
557 explicit InternalIteratorFromIterator(Iterator* it) : it_(it) {}
558 bool Valid() const override { return it_->Valid(); }
559 void Seek(const Slice& target) override { it_->Seek(target); }
560 void SeekForPrev(const Slice& target) override { it_->SeekForPrev(target); }
561 void SeekToFirst() override { it_->SeekToFirst(); }
562 void SeekToLast() override { it_->SeekToLast(); }
563 void Next() override { it_->Next(); }
564 void Prev() override { it_->Prev(); }
565 Slice key() const override { return it_->key(); }
566 Slice value() const override { return it_->value(); }
567 Status status() const override { return it_->status(); }
568
569 private:
570 std::unique_ptr<Iterator> it_;
571};

573class DBConstructor : public Constructor {
574 public:
575 explicit DBConstructor(const Comparator* cmp)
576 : Constructor(cmp), comparator_(cmp) {
577 db_ = nullptr;
578 NewDB();
579 }
580 ~DBConstructor() override { delete db_; }
581 Status FinishImpl(const Options& /*options*/,
582 const ImmutableOptions& /*ioptions*/,
583 const MutableCFOptions& /*moptions*/,
584 const BlockBasedTableOptions& /*table_options*/,
585 const InternalKeyComparator& /*internal_comparator*/,
586 const stl_wrappers::KVMap& kv_map) override {
587 delete db_;
588 db_ = nullptr;
589 NewDB();
590 for (const auto& kv : kv_map) {
591 WriteBatch batch;
592 EXPECT_OK(batch.Put(kv.first, kv.second));
593 EXPECT_TRUE(db_->Write(WriteOptions(), &batch).ok());
594 }
595 return Status::OK();
596 }
597
598 InternalIterator* NewIterator(
599 const SliceTransform* /*prefix_extractor*/) const override {
600 return new InternalIteratorFromIterator(db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions()));
601 }
602
603 DB* db() const override { return db_; }
604
605 private:
606 void NewDB() {
607 std::string name = test::PerThreadDBPath("table_testdb");
608
609 Options options;
610 options.comparator = comparator_;
611 Status status = DestroyDB(name, options);
612 ASSERT_TRUE(status.ok()) << status.ToString();
613
614 options.create_if_missing = true;
615 options.error_if_exists = true;
616 options.write_buffer_size = 10000; // Something small to force merging
617 status = DB::Open(options, name, &db_);
618 ASSERT_TRUE(status.ok()) << status.ToString();
619 }
620
621 const Comparator* comparator_;
622 DB* db_;
623};
624
625enum TestType {
626 BLOCK_BASED_TABLE_TEST,
627 PLAIN_TABLE_SEMI_FIXED_PREFIX,
628 PLAIN_TABLE_FULL_STR_PREFIX,
629 PLAIN_TABLE_TOTAL_ORDER,
630 BLOCK_TEST,
631 MEMTABLE_TEST,
632 DB_TEST
633};
634
635struct TestArgs {
636 TestType type;
637 bool reverse_compare;
638 int restart_interval;
639 CompressionType compression;
640 uint32_t compression_parallel_threads;
641 uint32_t format_version;
642 bool use_mmap;
643};
644
645std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const TestArgs& args) {
646 os << "type: " << args.type << " reverse_compare: " << args.reverse_compare
647 << " restart_interval: " << args.restart_interval
648 << " compression: " << args.compression
649 << " compression_parallel_threads: " << args.compression_parallel_threads
650 << " format_version: " << args.format_version
651 << " use_mmap: " << args.use_mmap;
652
653 return os;
654}
655
656static std::vector<TestArgs> GenerateArgList() {
657 std::vector<TestArgs> test_args;
658 std::vector<TestType> test_types = {BLOCK_BASED_TABLE_TEST,
659 PLAIN_TABLE_SEMI_FIXED_PREFIX,
660 PLAIN_TABLE_FULL_STR_PREFIX,
661 PLAIN_TABLE_TOTAL_ORDER,
662 BLOCK_TEST,
663 MEMTABLE_TEST,
664 DB_TEST};
665 std::vector<bool> reverse_compare_types = {false, true};
666 std::vector<int> restart_intervals = {16, 1, 1024};
667 std::vector<uint32_t> compression_parallel_threads = {1, 4};
668
669 // Only add compression if it is supported
670 std::vector<std::pair<CompressionType, bool>> compression_types;
671 compression_types.emplace_back(kNoCompression, false);
672 if (Snappy_Supported()) {
673 compression_types.emplace_back(kSnappyCompression, false);
674 }
675 if (Zlib_Supported()) {
676 compression_types.emplace_back(kZlibCompression, false);
677 compression_types.emplace_back(kZlibCompression, true);
678 }
679 if (BZip2_Supported()) {
680 compression_types.emplace_back(kBZip2Compression, false);
681 compression_types.emplace_back(kBZip2Compression, true);
682 }
683 if (LZ4_Supported()) {
684 compression_types.emplace_back(kLZ4Compression, false);
685 compression_types.emplace_back(kLZ4Compression, true);
686 compression_types.emplace_back(kLZ4HCCompression, false);
687 compression_types.emplace_back(kLZ4HCCompression, true);
688 }
689 if (XPRESS_Supported()) {
690 compression_types.emplace_back(kXpressCompression, false);
691 compression_types.emplace_back(kXpressCompression, true);
692 }
693 if (ZSTD_Supported()) {
694 compression_types.emplace_back(kZSTD, false);
695 compression_types.emplace_back(kZSTD, true);
696 }
697
698 for (auto test_type : test_types) {
699 for (auto reverse_compare : reverse_compare_types) {
700 if (test_type == PLAIN_TABLE_SEMI_FIXED_PREFIX ||
701 test_type == PLAIN_TABLE_FULL_STR_PREFIX ||
702 test_type == PLAIN_TABLE_TOTAL_ORDER) {
703 // Plain table doesn't use restart index or compression.
704 TestArgs one_arg;
705 one_arg.type = test_type;
706 one_arg.reverse_compare = reverse_compare;
707 one_arg.restart_interval = restart_intervals[0];
708 one_arg.compression = compression_types[0].first;
709 one_arg.compression_parallel_threads = 1;
710 one_arg.format_version = 0;
711 one_arg.use_mmap = true;
712 test_args.push_back(one_arg);
713 one_arg.use_mmap = false;
714 test_args.push_back(one_arg);
715 continue;
716 }
717
718 for (auto restart_interval : restart_intervals) {
719 for (auto compression_type : compression_types) {
720 for (auto num_threads : compression_parallel_threads) {
721 TestArgs one_arg;
722 one_arg.type = test_type;
723 one_arg.reverse_compare = reverse_compare;
724 one_arg.restart_interval = restart_interval;
725 one_arg.compression = compression_type.first;
726 one_arg.compression_parallel_threads = num_threads;
727 one_arg.format_version = compression_type.second ? 2 : 1;
728 one_arg.use_mmap = false;
729 test_args.push_back(one_arg);
730 }
731 }
732 }
733 }
734 }
735 return test_args;
736}
737
738// In order to make all tests run for plain table format, including
739// those operating on empty keys, create a new prefix transformer which
740// return fixed prefix if the slice is not shorter than the prefix length,
741// and the full slice if it is shorter.
742class FixedOrLessPrefixTransform : public SliceTransform {
743 private:
744 const size_t prefix_len_;
745
746 public:
747 explicit FixedOrLessPrefixTransform(size_t prefix_len)
748 : prefix_len_(prefix_len) {}
749
750 const char* Name() const override { return "rocksdb.FixedPrefix"; }
751
752 Slice Transform(const Slice& src) const override {
753 assert(InDomain(src));
754 if (src.size() < prefix_len_) {
755 return src;
756 }
757 return Slice(src.data(), prefix_len_);
758 }
759
760 bool InDomain(const Slice& /*src*/) const override { return true; }
761
762 bool InRange(const Slice& dst) const override {
763 return (dst.size() <= prefix_len_);
764 }
765 bool FullLengthEnabled(size_t* /*len*/) const override { return false; }
766};
767
768class HarnessTest : public testing::Test {
769 public:
770 explicit HarnessTest(const TestArgs& args)
771 : args_(args),
772 ioptions_(options_),
773 moptions_(options_),
774 write_buffer_(options_.db_write_buffer_size),
775 support_prev_(true),
776 only_support_prefix_seek_(false) {
777 options_.compression = args_.compression;
778 options_.compression_opts.parallel_threads =
779 args_.compression_parallel_threads;
780 // Use shorter block size for tests to exercise block boundary
781 // conditions more.
782 if (args_.reverse_compare) {
783 options_.comparator = &reverse_key_comparator;
784 }
785
786 internal_comparator_.reset(
787 new test::PlainInternalKeyComparator(options_.comparator));
788
789 options_.allow_mmap_reads = args_.use_mmap;
790 switch (args_.type) {
791 case BLOCK_BASED_TABLE_TEST:
792 table_options_.flush_block_policy_factory.reset(
793 new FlushBlockBySizePolicyFactory());
794 table_options_.block_size = 256;
795 table_options_.block_restart_interval = args_.restart_interval;
796 table_options_.index_block_restart_interval = args_.restart_interval;
797 table_options_.format_version = args_.format_version;
798 options_.table_factory.reset(
799 new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options_));
800 constructor_.reset(new TableConstructor(
801 options_.comparator, true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */));
802 internal_comparator_.reset(
803 new InternalKeyComparator(options_.comparator));
804 break;
805
806 case PLAIN_TABLE_SEMI_FIXED_PREFIX:
807 support_prev_ = false;
808 only_support_prefix_seek_ = true;
809 options_.prefix_extractor.reset(new FixedOrLessPrefixTransform(2));
810 options_.table_factory.reset(NewPlainTableFactory());
811 constructor_.reset(new TableConstructor(
812 options_.comparator, true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */));
813 internal_comparator_.reset(
814 new InternalKeyComparator(options_.comparator));
815 break;
816 case PLAIN_TABLE_FULL_STR_PREFIX:
817 support_prev_ = false;
818 only_support_prefix_seek_ = true;
819 options_.prefix_extractor.reset(NewNoopTransform());
820 options_.table_factory.reset(NewPlainTableFactory());
821 constructor_.reset(new TableConstructor(
822 options_.comparator, true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */));
823 internal_comparator_.reset(
824 new InternalKeyComparator(options_.comparator));
825 break;
826 case PLAIN_TABLE_TOTAL_ORDER:
827 support_prev_ = false;
828 only_support_prefix_seek_ = false;
829 options_.prefix_extractor = nullptr;
830
831 {
832 PlainTableOptions plain_table_options;
833 plain_table_options.user_key_len = kPlainTableVariableLength;
834 plain_table_options.bloom_bits_per_key = 0;
835 plain_table_options.hash_table_ratio = 0;
836
837 options_.table_factory.reset(
838 NewPlainTableFactory(plain_table_options));
839 }
840 constructor_.reset(new TableConstructor(
841 options_.comparator, true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */));
842 internal_comparator_.reset(
843 new InternalKeyComparator(options_.comparator));
844 break;
845 case BLOCK_TEST:
846 table_options_.block_size = 256;
847 options_.table_factory.reset(
848 new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options_));
849 constructor_.reset(new BlockConstructor(options_.comparator));
850 break;
851 case MEMTABLE_TEST:
852 table_options_.block_size = 256;
853 options_.table_factory.reset(
854 new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options_));
855 constructor_.reset(
856 new MemTableConstructor(options_.comparator, &write_buffer_));
857 break;
858 case DB_TEST:
859 table_options_.block_size = 256;
860 options_.table_factory.reset(
861 new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options_));
862 constructor_.reset(new DBConstructor(options_.comparator));
863 break;
864 }
865 ioptions_ = ImmutableOptions(options_);
866 moptions_ = MutableCFOptions(options_);
867 }
868
869 void Add(const std::string& key, const std::string& value) {
870 constructor_->Add(key, value);
871 }
872
873 void Test(Random* rnd) {
874 std::vector<std::string> keys;
875 stl_wrappers::KVMap data;
876 constructor_->Finish(options_, ioptions_, moptions_, table_options_,
877 *internal_comparator_, &keys, &data);
878
879 TestForwardScan(keys, data);
880 if (support_prev_) {
881 TestBackwardScan(keys, data);
882 }
883 TestRandomAccess(rnd, keys, data);
884 }
885
886 void TestForwardScan(const std::vector<std::string>& /*keys*/,
887 const stl_wrappers::KVMap& data) {
888 InternalIterator* iter = constructor_->NewIterator();
889 ASSERT_TRUE(!iter->Valid());
890 iter->SeekToFirst();
891 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
892 for (stl_wrappers::KVMap::const_iterator model_iter = data.begin();
893 model_iter != data.end(); ++model_iter) {
894 ASSERT_EQ(ToString(data, model_iter), ToString(iter));
895 iter->Next();
896 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
897 }
898 ASSERT_TRUE(!iter->Valid());
899 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
900 if (constructor_->IsArenaMode() && !constructor_->AnywayDeleteIterator()) {
901 iter->~InternalIterator();
902 } else {
903 delete iter;
904 }
905 }
906
907 void TestBackwardScan(const std::vector<std::string>& /*keys*/,
908 const stl_wrappers::KVMap& data) {
909 InternalIterator* iter = constructor_->NewIterator();
910 ASSERT_TRUE(!iter->Valid());
911 iter->SeekToLast();
912 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
913 for (stl_wrappers::KVMap::const_reverse_iterator model_iter = data.rbegin();
914 model_iter != data.rend(); ++model_iter) {
915 ASSERT_EQ(ToString(data, model_iter), ToString(iter));
916 iter->Prev();
917 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
918 }
919 ASSERT_TRUE(!iter->Valid());
920 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
921 if (constructor_->IsArenaMode() && !constructor_->AnywayDeleteIterator()) {
922 iter->~InternalIterator();
923 } else {
924 delete iter;
925 }
926 }
927
928 void TestRandomAccess(Random* rnd, const std::vector<std::string>& keys,
929 const stl_wrappers::KVMap& data) {
930 static const bool kVerbose = false;
931 InternalIterator* iter = constructor_->NewIterator();
932 ASSERT_TRUE(!iter->Valid());
933 stl_wrappers::KVMap::const_iterator model_iter = data.begin();
934 if (kVerbose) {
935 fprintf(stderr, "---\n");
936 }
937 for (int i = 0; i < 200; i++) {
938 const int toss = rnd->Uniform(support_prev_ ? 5 : 3);
939 switch (toss) {
940 case 0: {
941 if (iter->Valid()) {
942 if (kVerbose) {
943 fprintf(stderr, "Next\n");
944 }
945 iter->Next();
946 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
947 ++model_iter;
948 ASSERT_EQ(ToString(data, model_iter), ToString(iter));
949 }
950 break;
951 }
952
953 case 1: {
954 if (kVerbose) {
955 fprintf(stderr, "SeekToFirst\n");
956 }
957 iter->SeekToFirst();
958 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
959 model_iter = data.begin();
960 ASSERT_EQ(ToString(data, model_iter), ToString(iter));
961 break;
962 }
963
964 case 2: {
965 std::string key = PickRandomKey(rnd, keys);
966 model_iter = data.lower_bound(key);
967 if (kVerbose) {
968 fprintf(stderr, "Seek '%s'\n", EscapeString(key).c_str());
969 }
970 iter->Seek(Slice(key));
971 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
972 ASSERT_EQ(ToString(data, model_iter), ToString(iter));
973 break;
974 }
975
976 case 3: {
977 if (iter->Valid()) {
978 if (kVerbose) {
979 fprintf(stderr, "Prev\n");
980 }
981 iter->Prev();
982 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
983 if (model_iter == data.begin()) {
984 model_iter = data.end(); // Wrap around to invalid value
985 } else {
986 --model_iter;
987 }
988 ASSERT_EQ(ToString(data, model_iter), ToString(iter));
989 }
990 break;
991 }
992
993 case 4: {
994 if (kVerbose) {
995 fprintf(stderr, "SeekToLast\n");
996 }
997 iter->SeekToLast();
998 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
999 if (keys.empty()) {
1000 model_iter = data.end();
1001 } else {
1002 std::string last = data.rbegin()->first;
1003 model_iter = data.lower_bound(last);
1004 }
1005 ASSERT_EQ(ToString(data, model_iter), ToString(iter));
1006 break;
1007 }
1008 }
1009 }
1010 if (constructor_->IsArenaMode() && !constructor_->AnywayDeleteIterator()) {
1011 iter->~InternalIterator();
1012 } else {
1013 delete iter;
1014 }
1015 }
1016
1017 std::string ToString(const stl_wrappers::KVMap& data,
1018 const stl_wrappers::KVMap::const_iterator& it) {
1019 if (it == data.end()) {
1020 return "END";
1021 } else {
1022 return "'" + it->first + "->" + it->second + "'";
1023 }
1024 }
1025
1026 std::string ToString(const stl_wrappers::KVMap& data,
1027 const stl_wrappers::KVMap::const_reverse_iterator& it) {
1028 if (it == data.rend()) {
1029 return "END";
1030 } else {
1031 return "'" + it->first + "->" + it->second + "'";
1032 }
1033 }
1034
1035 std::string ToString(const InternalIterator* it) {
1036 if (!it->Valid()) {
1037 return "END";
1038 } else {
1039 return "'" + it->key().ToString() + "->" + it->value().ToString() + "'";
1040 }
1041 }
1042
1043 std::string PickRandomKey(Random* rnd, const std::vector<std::string>& keys) {
1044 if (keys.empty()) {
1045 return "foo";
1046 } else {
1047 const int index = rnd->Uniform(static_cast<int>(keys.size()));
1048 std::string result = keys[index];
1049 switch (rnd->Uniform(support_prev_ ? 3 : 1)) {
1050 case 0:
1051 // Return an existing key
1052 break;
1053 case 1: {
1054 // Attempt to return something smaller than an existing key
1055 if (result.size() > 0 && result[result.size() - 1] > '\0' &&
1056 (!only_support_prefix_seek_ ||
1057 options_.prefix_extractor->Transform(result).size() <
1058 result.size())) {
1059 result[result.size() - 1]--;
1060 }
1061 break;
1062 }
1063 case 2: {
1064 // Return something larger than an existing key
1065 Increment(options_.comparator, &result);
1066 break;
1067 }
1068 }
1069 return result;
1070 }
1071 }
1072
1073 // Returns nullptr if not running against a DB
1074 DB* db() const { return constructor_->db(); }
1075
1076 private:
1077 TestArgs args_;
1078 Options options_;
1079 ImmutableOptions ioptions_;
1080 MutableCFOptions moptions_;
1081 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options_;
1082 std::unique_ptr<Constructor> constructor_;
1083 WriteBufferManager write_buffer_;
1084 bool support_prev_;
1085 bool only_support_prefix_seek_;
1086 std::shared_ptr<InternalKeyComparator> internal_comparator_;
1087};

1106
1107static bool Between(uint64_t val, uint64_t low, uint64_t high) {
1108 bool result = (val >= low) && (val <= high);
1109 if (!result) {
1110 fprintf(stderr, "Value %llu is not in range [%llu, %llu]\n",
1111 (unsigned long long)(val), (unsigned long long)(low),
1112 (unsigned long long)(high));
1113 }
1114 return result;
1115}

1150 EXPECT_OK(env_->CreateDir(test_path_));

1163 ASSERT_OK(c->block_cache_tracer_.StartTrace(
1164 trace_opt, std::move(block_cache_trace_writer)));

1168 std::string encoded_key = internal_key.Encode().ToString();
1169 c->Add(encoded_key, kDummyValue);

1171 {

1177
1178 void VerifyBlockAccessTrace(
1179 TableConstructor* c,
1180 const std::vector<BlockCacheTraceRecord>& expected_records) {
1181 c->block_cache_tracer_.EndTrace();
1182
1183 {
1184 std::unique_ptr<TraceReader> trace_reader;
1185 Status s = NewFileTraceReader(env_, EnvOptions(), trace_file_path_,
1186 &trace_reader);
1187 EXPECT_OK(s);
1188 BlockCacheTraceReader reader(std::move(trace_reader));
1189 BlockCacheTraceHeader header;
1190 EXPECT_OK(reader.ReadHeader(&header));
1191 uint32_t index = 0;
1192 while (s.ok()) {
1193 SCOPED_TRACE("expected_records[" + std::to_string(index) + "]");
1194 BlockCacheTraceRecord access;
1195 s = reader.ReadAccess(&access);
1196 if (!s.ok()) {
1197 break;
1198 }
1199 ASSERT_LT(index, expected_records.size());
1200 EXPECT_NE("", access.block_key);
1201 EXPECT_EQ(access.block_type, expected_records[index].block_type);
1202 EXPECT_GT(access.block_size, 0);
1203 EXPECT_EQ(access.caller, expected_records[index].caller);
1204 EXPECT_EQ(access.no_insert, expected_records[index].no_insert);
1205 EXPECT_EQ(access.is_cache_hit, expected_records[index].is_cache_hit);
1206 EXPECT_EQ(access.get_id, expected_records[index].get_id);
1207 // The well-populated cases
1208 if (access.caller == TableReaderCaller::kUserGet ||
1209 (access.caller == TableReaderCaller::kUserMultiGet &&
1210 access.block_type == TraceType::kBlockTraceDataBlock)) {
1211 EXPECT_EQ(access.referenced_key,
1212 expected_records[index].referenced_key);
1213 EXPECT_EQ(access.get_from_user_specified_snapshot,
1214 expected_records[index].get_from_user_specified_snapshot);
1215 if (access.block_type == TraceType::kBlockTraceDataBlock) {
1216 EXPECT_GT(access.referenced_data_size, 0);
1217 EXPECT_GT(access.num_keys_in_block, 0);
1218 if (access.caller == TableReaderCaller::kUserMultiGet) {
1219 // Test num_keys_in_block estimate, assuming default restart
1220 // interval of 16 and just one interval.
1221 // Rounding depends on get_id.
1222 if (access.get_id & 1) {
1223 EXPECT_EQ(access.num_keys_in_block, 9);
1224 } else {
1225 EXPECT_EQ(access.num_keys_in_block, 8);
1226 }
1227 }
1228 EXPECT_EQ(access.referenced_key_exist_in_block,
1229 expected_records[index].referenced_key_exist_in_block);
1230 }
1231 } else {
1232 EXPECT_EQ(access.referenced_key, "");
1233 EXPECT_FALSE(access.get_from_user_specified_snapshot);
1234 EXPECT_EQ(access.referenced_data_size, 0);
1235 EXPECT_EQ(access.num_keys_in_block, 0);
1236 EXPECT_FALSE(access.referenced_key_exist_in_block);
1237 }
1238 index++;
1239 }
1240 EXPECT_EQ(index, expected_records.size());
1241 }
1242 EXPECT_OK(env_->DeleteFile(trace_file_path_));
1243 EXPECT_OK(env_->DeleteDir(test_path_));
1244 }
1245
1246 protected:
1247 uint64_t IndexUncompressedHelper(bool indexCompress);
1248 const std::string auto_add_key1 = "aak01";
1249 const std::string auto_add_key2 = "aak02";
1250
1251 private:
1252 uint32_t format_;
1253 Env* env_;
1254 std::string trace_file_path_;
1255 std::string test_path_;
1256};

1261// The helper class to test the file checksum
1262class FileChecksumTestHelper {
1263 public:
1264 FileChecksumTestHelper(bool convert_to_internal_key = false)
1265 : convert_to_internal_key_(convert_to_internal_key) {}
1266 ~FileChecksumTestHelper() = default;
1267
1268 void CreateWritableFile() {
1269 sink_ = new test::StringSink();
1270 std::unique_ptr<FSWritableFile> holder(sink_);
1271 file_writer_.reset(new WritableFileWriter(
1272 std::move(holder), "" /* don't care */, FileOptions()));
1273 }
1274
1275 void SetFileChecksumGenerator(FileChecksumGenerator* checksum_generator) {
1276 if (file_writer_ != nullptr) {
1277 file_writer_->TEST_SetFileChecksumGenerator(checksum_generator);
1278 } else {
1279 delete checksum_generator;
1280 }
1281 }
1282
1283 WritableFileWriter* GetFileWriter() { return file_writer_.get(); }
1284
1285 Status ResetTableBuilder(std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder>&& builder) {
1286 assert(builder != nullptr);
1287 table_builder_ = std::move(builder);
1288 return Status::OK();
1289 }
1290
1291 void AddKVtoKVMap(int num_entries) {
1292 Random rnd(test::RandomSeed());
1293 for (int i = 0; i < num_entries; i++) {
1294 std::string v = rnd.RandomString(100);
1295 kv_map_[test::RandomKey(&rnd, 20)] = v;
1296 }
1297 }
1298
1299 Status WriteKVAndFlushTable() {
1300 for (const auto& kv : kv_map_) {
1301 if (convert_to_internal_key_) {
1302 ParsedInternalKey ikey(kv.first, kMaxSequenceNumber, kTypeValue);
1303 std::string encoded;
1304 AppendInternalKey(&encoded, ikey);
1305 table_builder_->Add(encoded, kv.second);
1306 } else {
1307 table_builder_->Add(kv.first, kv.second);
1308 }
1309 EXPECT_TRUE(table_builder_->status().ok());
1310 }
1311 Status s = table_builder_->Finish();
1312 EXPECT_OK(file_writer_->Flush(IOOptions()));
1313 EXPECT_OK(s);
1314
1315 EXPECT_EQ(sink_->contents().size(), table_builder_->FileSize());
1316 return s;
1317 }
1318
1319 std::string GetFileChecksum() {
1320 EXPECT_OK(file_writer_->Close(IOOptions()));
1321 return table_builder_->GetFileChecksum();
1322 }
1323
1324 const char* GetFileChecksumFuncName() {
1325 return table_builder_->GetFileChecksumFuncName();
1326 }
1327
1328 Status CalculateFileChecksum(FileChecksumGenerator* file_checksum_generator,
1329 std::string* checksum) {
1330 assert(file_checksum_generator != nullptr);
1331 cur_file_num_ = checksum_file_num_++;
1332 test::StringSink* ss_rw =
1333 static_cast<test::StringSink*>(file_writer_->writable_file());
1334 std::unique_ptr<FSRandomAccessFile> source(
1335 new test::StringSource(ss_rw->contents()));
1336 file_reader_.reset(new RandomAccessFileReader(std::move(source), "test"));
1337
1338 std::unique_ptr<char[]> scratch(new char[2048]);
1339 Slice result;
1340 uint64_t offset = 0;
1341 Status s;
1342 s = file_reader_->Read(IOOptions(), offset, 2048, &result, scratch.get(),
1343 nullptr);
1344 if (!s.ok()) {
1345 return s;
1346 }
1347 while (result.size() != 0) {
1348 file_checksum_generator->Update(scratch.get(), result.size());
1349 offset += static_cast<uint64_t>(result.size());
1350 s = file_reader_->Read(IOOptions(), offset, 2048, &result, scratch.get(),
1351 nullptr);
1352 if (!s.ok()) {
1353 return s;
1354 }
1355 }
1356 EXPECT_EQ(offset, static_cast<uint64_t>(table_builder_->FileSize()));
1357 file_checksum_generator->Finalize();
1358 *checksum = file_checksum_generator->GetChecksum();
1359 return Status::OK();
1360 }
1361
1362 private:
1363 bool convert_to_internal_key_;
1364 uint64_t cur_file_num_;
1365 std::unique_ptr<WritableFileWriter> file_writer_;
1366 std::unique_ptr<RandomAccessFileReader> file_reader_;
1367 std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder> table_builder_;
1368 stl_wrappers::KVMap kv_map_;
1369 test::StringSink* sink_ = nullptr;
1370
1371 static uint64_t checksum_file_num_;
1372};

1379// This test serves as the living tutorial for the prefix scan of user collected
1380// properties.
1381TEST_F(TablePropertyTest, PrefixScanTest) {
1382 UserCollectedProperties props{
1383 {"num.111.1", "1"}, {"num.111.2", "2"}, {"num.111.3", "3"},
1384 {"num.333.1", "1"}, {"num.333.2", "2"}, {"num.333.3", "3"},
1385 {"num.555.1", "1"}, {"num.555.2", "2"}, {"num.555.3", "3"},
1386 };
1387
1388 // prefixes that exist
1389 for (const std::string prefix : {"num.111", "num.333", "num.555"}) {
1390 int num = 0;
1391 for (auto pos = props.lower_bound(prefix);
1392 pos != props.end() &&
1393 pos->first.compare(0, prefix.size(), prefix) == 0;
1394 ++pos) {
1395 ++num;
1396 auto key = prefix + "." + std::to_string(num);
1397 ASSERT_EQ(key, pos->first);
1398 ASSERT_EQ(std::to_string(num), pos->second);
1399 }
1400 ASSERT_EQ(3, num);
1401 }
1402
1403 // prefixes that don't exist
1404 for (const std::string prefix :
1405 {"num.000", "num.222", "num.444", "num.666"}) {
1406 auto pos = props.lower_bound(prefix);
1407 ASSERT_TRUE(pos == props.end() ||
1408 pos->first.compare(0, prefix.size(), prefix) != 0);
1409 }
1410}
1411
1412namespace {
1413struct TestIds {
1414 UniqueId64x3 internal_id;
1415 UniqueId64x3 external_id;
1416};
1417
1418inline bool operator==(const TestIds& lhs, const TestIds& rhs) {
1419 return lhs.internal_id == rhs.internal_id &&
1420 lhs.external_id == rhs.external_id;
1421}
1422
1423std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const TestIds& ids) {
1424 return os << std::hex << "{{{ 0x" << ids.internal_id[0] << "U, 0x"
1425 << ids.internal_id[1] << "U, 0x" << ids.internal_id[2]
1426 << "U }}, {{ 0x" << ids.external_id[0] << "U, 0x"
1427 << ids.external_id[1] << "U, 0x" << ids.external_id[2] << "U }}}";
1428}
1429
1430TestIds GetUniqueId(TableProperties* tp, std::unordered_set<uint64_t>* seen,
1431 const std::string& db_id, const std::string& db_session_id,
1432 uint64_t file_number) {
1433 // First test session id logic
1434 if (db_session_id.size() == 20) {
1435 uint64_t upper;
1436 uint64_t lower;
1437 EXPECT_OK(DecodeSessionId(db_session_id, &upper, &lower));
1438 EXPECT_EQ(EncodeSessionId(upper, lower), db_session_id);
1439 }
1440
1441 // Get external using public API
1442 tp->db_id = db_id;
1443 tp->db_session_id = db_session_id;
1444 tp->orig_file_number = file_number;
1445 TestIds t;
1446 {
1447 std::string euid;
1448 EXPECT_OK(GetExtendedUniqueIdFromTableProperties(*tp, &euid));
1449 EXPECT_EQ(euid.size(), 24U);
1450 t.external_id[0] = DecodeFixed64(euid.data());
1451 t.external_id[1] = DecodeFixed64(&euid[8]);
1452 t.external_id[2] = DecodeFixed64(&euid[16]);
1453
1454 std::string uid;
1455 EXPECT_OK(GetUniqueIdFromTableProperties(*tp, &uid));
1456 EXPECT_EQ(uid.size(), 16U);
1457 EXPECT_EQ(uid, euid.substr(0, 16));
1458 EXPECT_EQ(t.external_id[0], DecodeFixed64(uid.data()));
1459 EXPECT_EQ(t.external_id[1], DecodeFixed64(&uid[8]));
1460 }
1461 // All these should be effectively random
1462 EXPECT_TRUE(seen->insert(t.external_id[0]).second);
1463 EXPECT_TRUE(seen->insert(t.external_id[1]).second);
1464 EXPECT_TRUE(seen->insert(t.external_id[2]).second);
1465
1466 // Get internal with internal API
1467 EXPECT_OK(GetSstInternalUniqueId(db_id, db_session_id, file_number,
1468 &t.internal_id));
1469 EXPECT_NE(t.internal_id, kNullUniqueId64x3);
1470
1471 // Verify relationship
1472 UniqueId64x3 tmp = t.internal_id;
1473 InternalUniqueIdToExternal(&tmp);
1474 EXPECT_EQ(tmp, t.external_id);
1475 ExternalUniqueIdToInternal(&tmp);
1476 EXPECT_EQ(tmp, t.internal_id);
1477
1478 // And 128-bit internal version
1479 UniqueId64x2 tmp2{};
1480 EXPECT_OK(GetSstInternalUniqueId(db_id, db_session_id, file_number, &tmp2));
1481 EXPECT_NE(tmp2, kNullUniqueId64x2);
1482
1483 EXPECT_EQ(tmp2[0], t.internal_id[0]);
1484 EXPECT_EQ(tmp2[1], t.internal_id[1]);
1485 InternalUniqueIdToExternal(&tmp2);
1486 EXPECT_EQ(tmp2[0], t.external_id[0]);
1487 EXPECT_EQ(tmp2[1], t.external_id[1]);
1488 ExternalUniqueIdToInternal(&tmp2);
1489 EXPECT_EQ(tmp2[0], t.internal_id[0]);
1490 EXPECT_EQ(tmp2[1], t.internal_id[1]);
1491
1492 return t;
1493}
1494} // namespace
1495
1496TEST_F(TablePropertyTest, UniqueIdsSchemaAndQuality) {
1497 // To ensure the computation only depends on the expected entries, we set
1498 // the rest randomly
1499 TableProperties tp;
1500 TEST_SetRandomTableProperties(&tp);
1501
1502 // DB id is normally RFC-4122
1503 const std::string db_id1 = "7265b6eb-4e42-4aec-86a4-0dc5e73a228d";
1504 // Allow other forms of DB id
1505 const std::string db_id2 = "1728000184588763620";
1506 const std::string db_id3 = "x";
1507
1508 // DB session id is normally 20 chars in base-36, but 13 to 24 chars
1509 // is ok, roughly 64 to 128 bits.
1510 const std::string ses_id1 = "ABCDEFGHIJ0123456789";
1511 // Same trailing 13 digits
1512 const std::string ses_id2 = "HIJ0123456789";
1513 const std::string ses_id3 = "0123ABCDEFGHIJ0123456789";
1514 // Different trailing 12 digits
1515 const std::string ses_id4 = "ABCDEFGH888888888888";
1516 // And change length
1517 const std::string ses_id5 = "ABCDEFGHIJ012";
1518 const std::string ses_id6 = "ABCDEFGHIJ0123456789ABCD";
1519
1520 using T = TestIds;
1521 std::unordered_set<uint64_t> seen;
1522 // Establish a stable schema for the unique IDs. These values must not
1523 // change for existing table files.
1524 // (Note: parens needed for macro parsing, extra braces needed for some
1525 // compilers.)
1526 EXPECT_EQ(
1527 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id1, ses_id1, 1),
1528 T({{{0x61d7dcf415d9cf19U, 0x160d77aae90757fdU, 0x907f41dfd90724ffU}},
1529 {{0xf0bd230365df7464U, 0xca089303f3648eb4U, 0x4b44f7e7324b2817U}}}));
1530 // Only change internal_id[1] with file number
1531 EXPECT_EQ(
1532 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id1, ses_id1, 2),
1533 T({{{0x61d7dcf415d9cf19U, 0x160d77aae90757feU, 0x907f41dfd90724ffU}},
1534 {{0xf13fdf7adcfebb6dU, 0x97cd2226cc033ea2U, 0x198c438182091f0eU}}}));
1535 EXPECT_EQ(
1536 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id1, ses_id1, 123456789),
1537 T({{{0x61d7dcf415d9cf19U, 0x160d77aaee5c9ae9U, 0x907f41dfd90724ffU}},
1538 {{0x81fbcebe1ac6c4f0U, 0x6b14a64cfdc0f1c4U, 0x7d8fb6eaf18edbb3U}}}));
1539 // Change internal_id[1] and internal_id[2] with db_id
1540 EXPECT_EQ(
1541 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id2, ses_id1, 1),
1542 T({{{0x61d7dcf415d9cf19U, 0xf89c471f572f0d25U, 0x1f0f2a5eb0e6257eU}},
1543 {{0x7f1d01d453616991U, 0x32ddf2afec804ab2U, 0xd10a1ee2f0c7d9c1U}}}));
1544 EXPECT_EQ(
1545 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id3, ses_id1, 1),
1546 T({{{0x61d7dcf415d9cf19U, 0xfed297a8154a57d0U, 0x8b931b9cdebd9e8U}},
1547 {{0x62b2f43183f6894bU, 0x897ff2b460eefad1U, 0xf4ec189fb2d15e04U}}}));
1548 // Keeping same last 13 digits of ses_id keeps same internal_id[0]
1549 EXPECT_EQ(
1550 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id1, ses_id2, 1),
1551 T({{{0x61d7dcf415d9cf19U, 0x5f6cc4fa2d528c8U, 0x7b70845d5bfb5446U}},
1552 {{0x96d1c83ffcc94266U, 0x82663eac0ec6e14aU, 0x94a88b49678b77f6U}}}));
1553 EXPECT_EQ(
1554 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id1, ses_id3, 1),
1555 T({{{0x61d7dcf415d9cf19U, 0xfc7232879db37ea2U, 0xc0378d74ea4c89cdU}},
1556 {{0xdf2ef57e98776905U, 0xda5b31c987da833bU, 0x79c1b4bd0a9e760dU}}}));
1557 // Changing last 12 digits of ses_id only changes internal_id[0]
1558 // (vs. db_id1, ses_id1, 1)
1559 EXPECT_EQ(
1560 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id1, ses_id4, 1),
1561 T({{{0x4f07cc0d003a83a8U, 0x160d77aae90757fdU, 0x907f41dfd90724ffU}},
1562 {{0xbcf85336a9f71f04U, 0x4f2949e2f3adb60dU, 0x9ca0def976abfa10U}}}));
1563 // ses_id can change everything.
1564 EXPECT_EQ(
1565 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id1, ses_id5, 1),
1566 T({{{0x94b8768e43f87ce6U, 0xc2559653ac4e7c93U, 0xde6dff6bbb1223U}},
1567 {{0x5a9537af681817fbU, 0x1afcd1fecaead5eaU, 0x767077ad9ebe0008U}}}));
1568 EXPECT_EQ(
1569 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id1, ses_id6, 1),
1570 T({{{0x43cfb0ffa3b710edU, 0x263c580426406a1bU, 0xfacc91379a80d29dU}},
1571 {{0xfa90547d84cb1cdbU, 0x2afe99c641992d4aU, 0x205b7f7b60e51cc2U}}}));
1572
1573 // Now verify more thoroughly that any small change in inputs completely
1574 // changes external unique id.
1575 // (Relying on 'seen' checks etc. in GetUniqueId)
1576 std::string db_id = "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000";
1577 std::string ses_id = "000000000000000000000000";
1578 uint64_t file_num = 1;
1579 // change db_id
1580 for (size_t i = 0; i < db_id.size(); ++i) {
1581 if (db_id[i] == '-') {
1582 continue;
1583 }
1584 for (char alt : std::string("123456789abcdef")) {
1585 db_id[i] = alt;
1586 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id, ses_id, file_num);
1587 }
1588 db_id[i] = '0';
1589 }
1590 // change ses_id
1591 for (size_t i = 0; i < ses_id.size(); ++i) {
1592 for (char alt : std::string("123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ")) {
1593 ses_id[i] = alt;
1594 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id, ses_id, file_num);
1595 }
1596 ses_id[i] = '0';
1597 }
1598 // change file_num
1599 for (int i = 1; i < 64; ++i) {
1600 GetUniqueId(&tp, &seen, db_id, ses_id, file_num << i);
1601 }
1602
1603 // Verify that "all zeros" in first 128 bits is equivalent for internal and
1604 // external IDs. This way, as long as we avoid "all zeros" in internal IDs,
1605 // we avoid it in external IDs.
1606 {
1607 UniqueId64x3 id1{{0, 0, Random::GetTLSInstance()->Next64()}};
1608 UniqueId64x3 id2 = id1;
1609 InternalUniqueIdToExternal(&id1);
1610 EXPECT_EQ(id1, id2);
1611 ExternalUniqueIdToInternal(&id2);
1612 EXPECT_EQ(id1, id2);
1613 }
1614}

1627TEST_F(TablePropertyTest, UniqueIdHumanStrings) {
1628 TableProperties tp;
1629 SetGoodTableProperties(&tp);
1630
1631 std::string tmp;
1632 EXPECT_OK(GetExtendedUniqueIdFromTableProperties(tp, &tmp));
1633 EXPECT_EQ(tmp,
1634 (std::string{{'\x64', '\x74', '\xdf', '\x65', '\x03', '\x23',
1635 '\xbd', '\xf0', '\xb4', '\x8e', '\x64', '\xf3',
1636 '\x03', '\x93', '\x08', '\xca', '\x17', '\x28',
1637 '\x4b', '\x32', '\xe7', '\xf7', '\x44', '\x4b'}}));
1638 EXPECT_EQ(UniqueIdToHumanString(tmp),
1639 "6474DF650323BDF0-B48E64F3039308CA-17284B32E7F7444B");
1640
1641 EXPECT_OK(GetUniqueIdFromTableProperties(tp, &tmp));
1642 EXPECT_EQ(UniqueIdToHumanString(tmp), "6474DF650323BDF0-B48E64F3039308CA");
1643
1644 // including zero padding
1645 tmp = std::string(24U, '\0');
1646 tmp[15] = '\x12';
1647 tmp[23] = '\xAB';
1648 EXPECT_EQ(UniqueIdToHumanString(tmp),
1649 "0000000000000000-0000000000000012-00000000000000AB");
1650
1651 // And shortened
1652 tmp = std::string(20U, '\0');
1653 tmp[5] = '\x12';
1654 tmp[10] = '\xAB';
1655 tmp[17] = '\xEF';
1656 EXPECT_EQ(UniqueIdToHumanString(tmp),
1657 "0000000000120000-0000AB0000000000-00EF0000");
1658
1659 tmp.resize(16);
1660 EXPECT_EQ(UniqueIdToHumanString(tmp), "0000000000120000-0000AB0000000000");
1661
1662 tmp.resize(11);
1663 EXPECT_EQ(UniqueIdToHumanString(tmp), "0000000000120000-0000AB");
1664
1665 tmp.resize(6);
1666 EXPECT_EQ(UniqueIdToHumanString(tmp), "000000000012");
1667
1668 // Also internal IDs to human string
1669 UniqueId64x3 euid = {12345, 678, 9};
1670 EXPECT_EQ(InternalUniqueIdToHumanString(&euid), "{12345,678,9}");
1671
1672 UniqueId64x2 uid = {1234, 567890};
1673 EXPECT_EQ(InternalUniqueIdToHumanString(&uid), "{1234,567890}");
1674}

1702// This test include all the basic checks except those for index size and block
1703// size, which will be conducted in separated unit tests.
1704TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, BasicBlockBasedTableProperties) {
1705 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
1706
1707 c.Add("a1", "val1");
1708 c.Add("b2", "val2");
1709 c.Add("c3", "val3");
1710 c.Add("d4", "val4");
1711 c.Add("e5", "val5");
1712 c.Add("f6", "val6");
1713 c.Add("g7", "val7");
1714 c.Add("h8", "val8");
1715 c.Add("j9", "val9");
1716 uint64_t diff_internal_user_bytes = 9 * 8; // 8 is seq size, 9 k-v totally
1717
1718 std::vector<std::string> keys;
1719 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
1720 Options options;
1721 options.compression = kNoCompression;
1722 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
1723 options.statistics->set_stats_level(StatsLevel::kAll);
1724 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
1725 table_options.block_restart_interval = 1;
1726 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
1727
1728 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
1729 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
1730 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
1731 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
1732 ASSERT_EQ(
1733 options.statistics->getTickerCount(NUMBER_BLOCK_COMPRESSION_REJECTED), 0);
1734
1735 auto& props = *c.GetTableReader()->GetTableProperties();
1736 ASSERT_EQ(kvmap.size(), props.num_entries);
1737
1738 auto raw_key_size = kvmap.size() * 2ul;
1739 auto raw_value_size = kvmap.size() * 4ul;
1740
1741 ASSERT_EQ(raw_key_size + diff_internal_user_bytes, props.raw_key_size);
1742 ASSERT_EQ(raw_value_size, props.raw_value_size);
1743 ASSERT_EQ(1ul, props.num_data_blocks);
1744 ASSERT_EQ("", props.filter_policy_name); // no filter policy is used
1745
1746 // Verify data size.
1747 BlockBuilder block_builder(1);
1748 for (const auto& item : kvmap) {
1749 block_builder.Add(item.first, item.second);
1750 }
1751 Slice content = block_builder.Finish();
1752 ASSERT_EQ(content.size() + BlockBasedTable::kBlockTrailerSize +
1753 diff_internal_user_bytes,
1754 props.data_size);
1755 c.ResetTableReader();
1756}

1759uint64_t BlockBasedTableTest::IndexUncompressedHelper(bool compressed) {
1760 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
1761 constexpr size_t kNumKeys = 10000;
1762
1763 for (size_t k = 0; k < kNumKeys; ++k) {

1768 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
1769 Options options;
1770 options.compression = kSnappyCompression;

1772 options.statistics->set_stats_level(StatsLevel::kAll);
1773 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
1774 table_options.block_restart_interval = 1;
1775 table_options.enable_index_compression = compressed;
1776 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));

1778 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
1779 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
1780 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
1781 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
1782 c.ResetTableReader();
1783 return options.statistics->getTickerCount(NUMBER_BLOCK_COMPRESSED);
1784}

1793TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, BlockBasedTableProperties2) {
1794 TableConstructor c(&reverse_key_comparator);
1795 std::vector<std::string> keys;
1796 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
1797
1798 {
1799 Options options;
1800 options.compression = CompressionType::kNoCompression;
1801 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
1802 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
1803
1804 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
1805 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
1806 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
1807 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
1808

1810
1811 // Default comparator
1812 ASSERT_EQ("leveldb.BytewiseComparator", props.comparator_name);
1813 // No merge operator
1814 ASSERT_EQ("nullptr", props.merge_operator_name);
1815 // No prefix extractor
1816 ASSERT_EQ("nullptr", props.prefix_extractor_name);
1817 // No property collectors
1818 ASSERT_EQ("[]", props.property_collectors_names);
1819 // No filter policy is used
1820 ASSERT_EQ("", props.filter_policy_name);
1821 // Compression type == that set:
1822 ASSERT_EQ("NoCompression", props.compression_name);
1823 c.ResetTableReader();
1824 }
1825
1826 {
1827 Options options;
1828 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
1829 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
1830 options.comparator = &reverse_key_comparator;
1831 options.merge_operator = MergeOperators::CreateUInt64AddOperator();
1832 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewNoopTransform());
1833 options.table_properties_collector_factories.emplace_back(
1834 new DummyPropertiesCollectorFactory1());
1835 options.table_properties_collector_factories.emplace_back(
1836 new DummyPropertiesCollectorFactory2());
1837
1838 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
1839 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
1840 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
1841 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
1842
1843 auto& props = *c.GetTableReader()->GetTableProperties();
1844
1845 ASSERT_EQ("rocksdb.ReverseBytewiseComparator", props.comparator_name);
1846 ASSERT_EQ("UInt64AddOperator", props.merge_operator_name);
1847 ASSERT_EQ("rocksdb.Noop", props.prefix_extractor_name);
1848 ASSERT_EQ(
1849 "[DummyPropertiesCollectorFactory1,DummyPropertiesCollectorFactory2]",
1850 props.property_collectors_names);
1851 ASSERT_EQ("", props.filter_policy_name); // no filter policy is used
1852 c.ResetTableReader();
1853 }

1856TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, RangeDelBlock) {
1857 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator());
1858 std::vector<std::string> keys = {"1pika", "2chu"};
1859 std::vector<std::string> vals = {"p", "c"};
1860
1861 std::vector<RangeTombstone> expected_tombstones = {
1862 {"1pika", "2chu", 0},
1863 {"2chu", "c", 1},
1864 {"2chu", "c", 0},
1865 {"c", "p", 0},
1866 };
1867
1868 for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
1869 RangeTombstone t(keys[i], vals[i], i);
1870 std::pair<InternalKey, Slice> p = t.Serialize();
1871 c.Add(p.first.Encode().ToString(), p.second);
1872 }
1873
1874 std::vector<std::string> sorted_keys;
1875 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
1876 Options options;
1877 options.compression = kNoCompression;
1878 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
1879 table_options.block_restart_interval = 1;
1880 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
1881
1882 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
1883 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
1884 std::unique_ptr<InternalKeyComparator> internal_cmp(
1885 new InternalKeyComparator(options.comparator));
1886 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options, *internal_cmp,
1887 &sorted_keys, &kvmap);
1888
1889 for (int j = 0; j < 2; ++j) {
1890 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter(
1891 c.GetTableReader()->NewRangeTombstoneIterator(ReadOptions()));
1892 if (j > 0) {
1893 // For second iteration, delete the table reader object and verify the
1894 // iterator can still access its metablock's range tombstones.
1895 c.ResetTableReader();
1896 }
1897 ASSERT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
1898 iter->SeekToFirst();
1899 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
1900 for (size_t i = 0; i < expected_tombstones.size(); i++) {
1901 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
1902 ParsedInternalKey parsed_key;
1903 ASSERT_OK(
1904 ParseInternalKey(iter->key(), &parsed_key, true /* log_err_key */));
1905 RangeTombstone t(parsed_key, iter->value());
1906 const auto& expected_t = expected_tombstones[i];
1907 ASSERT_EQ(t.start_key_, expected_t.start_key_);
1908 ASSERT_EQ(t.end_key_, expected_t.end_key_);
1909 ASSERT_EQ(t.seq_, expected_t.seq_);
1910 iter->Next();
1911 }
1912 ASSERT_TRUE(!iter->Valid());
1913 }
1914}

1934
1935//
1936// BlockBasedTableTest::PrefetchTest
1937//
1938void AssertKeysInCache(BlockBasedTable* table_reader,
1939 const std::vector<std::string>& keys_in_cache,
1940 const std::vector<std::string>& keys_not_in_cache,
1941 bool convert = false) {
1942 if (convert) {
1943 for (const auto& key : keys_in_cache) {
1944 InternalKey ikey(key, kMaxSequenceNumber, kTypeValue);
1945 ASSERT_TRUE(table_reader->TEST_KeyInCache(ReadOptions(), ikey.Encode()));
1946 }
1947 for (const auto& key : keys_not_in_cache) {
1948 InternalKey ikey(key, kMaxSequenceNumber, kTypeValue);
1949 ASSERT_TRUE(!table_reader->TEST_KeyInCache(ReadOptions(), ikey.Encode()));
1950 }
1951 } else {
1952 for (const auto& key : keys_in_cache) {
1953 ASSERT_TRUE(table_reader->TEST_KeyInCache(ReadOptions(), key));
1954 }
1955 for (const auto& key : keys_not_in_cache) {
1956 ASSERT_TRUE(!table_reader->TEST_KeyInCache(ReadOptions(), key));
1957 }
1958 }
1959}
1960
1961void PrefetchRange(TableConstructor* c, Options* opt,
1962 BlockBasedTableOptions* table_options, const char* key_begin,
1963 const char* key_end,
1964 const std::vector<std::string>& keys_in_cache,
1965 const std::vector<std::string>& keys_not_in_cache,
1966 const Status expected_status = Status::OK()) {
1967 // reset the cache and reopen the table
1968 table_options->block_cache = NewLRUCache(16 * 1024 * 1024, 4);
1969 opt->table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(*table_options));
1970 const ImmutableOptions ioptions2(*opt);
1971 const MutableCFOptions moptions(*opt);
1972 ASSERT_OK(c->Reopen(ioptions2, moptions));
1973
1974 // prefetch
1975 auto* table_reader = dynamic_cast<BlockBasedTable*>(c->GetTableReader());
1976 Status s;
1977 std::unique_ptr<Slice> begin, end;
1978 std::unique_ptr<InternalKey> i_begin, i_end;
1979 if (key_begin != nullptr) {
1980 if (c->ConvertToInternalKey()) {
1981 i_begin.reset(new InternalKey(key_begin, kMaxSequenceNumber, kTypeValue));
1982 begin.reset(new Slice(i_begin->Encode()));
1983 } else {
1984 begin.reset(new Slice(key_begin));
1985 }
1986 }
1987 if (key_end != nullptr) {
1988 if (c->ConvertToInternalKey()) {
1989 i_end.reset(new InternalKey(key_end, kMaxSequenceNumber, kTypeValue));
1990 end.reset(new Slice(i_end->Encode()));
1991 } else {
1992 end.reset(new Slice(key_end));
1993 }
1994 }
1995 const ReadOptions read_options;
1996 s = table_reader->Prefetch(read_options, begin.get(), end.get());
1997
1998 ASSERT_TRUE(s.code() == expected_status.code());
1999
2000 // assert our expectation in cache warmup
2001 AssertKeysInCache(table_reader, keys_in_cache, keys_not_in_cache,
2002 c->ConvertToInternalKey());
2003 c->ResetTableReader();
2004}
2005
2006TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, PrefetchTest) {
2007 // The purpose of this test is to test the prefetching operation built into
2008 // BlockBasedTable.
2009 Options opt;
2010 std::unique_ptr<InternalKeyComparator> ikc;
2011 ikc.reset(new test::PlainInternalKeyComparator(opt.comparator));
2012 opt.compression = kNoCompression;
2013 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
2014 table_options.block_size = 1024;
2015 // big enough so we don't ever lose cached values.
2016 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(16 * 1024 * 1024, 4);
2017 opt.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2018
2019 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
2020 c.Add("k01", "hello");
2021 c.Add("k02", "hello2");
2022 c.Add("k03", std::string(10000, 'x'));
2023 c.Add("k04", std::string(200000, 'x'));
2024 c.Add("k05", std::string(300000, 'x'));
2025 c.Add("k06", "hello3");
2026 c.Add("k07", std::string(100000, 'x'));
2027 std::vector<std::string> keys;
2028 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
2029 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(opt);
2030 const MutableCFOptions moptions(opt);
2031 c.Finish(opt, ioptions, moptions, table_options, *ikc, &keys, &kvmap);
2032 c.ResetTableReader();
2033
2034 // We get the following data spread :
2035 //
2036 // Data block Index
2037 // ========================
2038 // [ k01 k02 k03 ] k03
2039 // [ k04 ] k04
2040 // [ k05 ] k05
2041 // [ k06 k07 ] k07
2042
2043 // Simple
2044 PrefetchRange(&c, &opt, &table_options,
2045 /*key_range=*/"k01", "k05",
2046 /*keys_in_cache=*/{"k01", "k02", "k03", "k04", "k05"},
2047 /*keys_not_in_cache=*/{"k06", "k07"});
2048 PrefetchRange(&c, &opt, &table_options, "k01", "k01", {"k01", "k02", "k03"},
2049 {"k04", "k05", "k06", "k07"});
2050 // odd
2051 PrefetchRange(&c, &opt, &table_options, "a", "z",
2052 {"k01", "k02", "k03", "k04", "k05", "k06", "k07"}, {});
2053 PrefetchRange(&c, &opt, &table_options, "k00", "k00", {"k01", "k02", "k03"},
2054 {"k04", "k05", "k06", "k07"});
2055 // Edge cases
2056 PrefetchRange(&c, &opt, &table_options, "k00", "k06",
2057 {"k01", "k02", "k03", "k04", "k05", "k06", "k07"}, {});
2058 PrefetchRange(&c, &opt, &table_options, "k00", "zzz",
2059 {"k01", "k02", "k03", "k04", "k05", "k06", "k07"}, {});
2060 // null keys
2061 PrefetchRange(&c, &opt, &table_options, nullptr, nullptr,
2062 {"k01", "k02", "k03", "k04", "k05", "k06", "k07"}, {});
2063 PrefetchRange(&c, &opt, &table_options, "k04", nullptr,
2064 {"k04", "k05", "k06", "k07"}, {"k01", "k02", "k03"});
2065 PrefetchRange(&c, &opt, &table_options, nullptr, "k05",
2066 {"k01", "k02", "k03", "k04", "k05"}, {"k06", "k07"});
2067 // invalid
2068 PrefetchRange(&c, &opt, &table_options, "k06", "k00", {}, {},
2069 Status::InvalidArgument(Slice("k06 "), Slice("k07")));
2070 c.ResetTableReader();
2071}

2073TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, TotalOrderSeekOnHashIndex) {
2074 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
2075 for (int i = 0; i <= 4; ++i) {
2076 Options options;
2077 // Make each key/value an individual block
2078 table_options.block_size = 64;
2079 switch (i) {
2080 case 0:
2081 // Binary search index
2082 table_options.index_type = BlockBasedTableOptions::kBinarySearch;
2083 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2084 break;
2085 case 1:
2086 // Hash search index
2087 table_options.index_type = BlockBasedTableOptions::kHashSearch;
2088 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2089 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewFixedPrefixTransform(4));
2090 break;
2091 case 2:
2092 // Hash search index with filter policy
2093 table_options.index_type = BlockBasedTableOptions::kHashSearch;
2094 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(10));
2095 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2096 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewFixedPrefixTransform(4));
2097 break;
2098 case 3:
2099 // Two-level index
2100 table_options.index_type = BlockBasedTableOptions::kTwoLevelIndexSearch;
2101 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2102 break;
2103 case 4:
2104 // Binary search with first key
2105 table_options.index_type =
2106 BlockBasedTableOptions::kBinarySearchWithFirstKey;
2107 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2108 break;
2109 }
2110
2111 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(),
2112 true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
2113 c.Add("aaaa1", std::string('a', 56));
2114 c.Add("bbaa1", std::string('a', 56));
2115 c.Add("cccc1", std::string('a', 56));
2116 c.Add("bbbb1", std::string('a', 56));
2117 c.Add("baaa1", std::string('a', 56));
2118 c.Add("abbb1", std::string('a', 56));
2119 c.Add("cccc2", std::string('a', 56));
2120 std::vector<std::string> keys;
2121 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
2122 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
2123 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
2124 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
2125 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
2126 auto props = c.GetTableReader()->GetTableProperties();
2127 ASSERT_EQ(7u, props->num_data_blocks);
2128 auto* reader = c.GetTableReader();
2129 ReadOptions ro;
2130 ro.total_order_seek = true;
2131 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter(reader->NewIterator(
2132 ro, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), /*arena=*/nullptr,
2133 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized));
2134
2135 iter->Seek(InternalKey("b", 0, kTypeValue).Encode());
2136 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
2137 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2138 ASSERT_EQ("baaa1", ExtractUserKey(iter->key()).ToString());
2139 iter->Next();
2140 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
2141 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2142 ASSERT_EQ("bbaa1", ExtractUserKey(iter->key()).ToString());
2143
2144 iter->Seek(InternalKey("bb", 0, kTypeValue).Encode());
2145 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
2146 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2147 ASSERT_EQ("bbaa1", ExtractUserKey(iter->key()).ToString());
2148 iter->Next();
2149 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
2150 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2151 ASSERT_EQ("bbbb1", ExtractUserKey(iter->key()).ToString());
2152
2153 iter->Seek(InternalKey("bbb", 0, kTypeValue).Encode());
2154 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
2155 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2156 ASSERT_EQ("bbbb1", ExtractUserKey(iter->key()).ToString());
2157 iter->Next();
2158 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
2159 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2160 ASSERT_EQ("cccc1", ExtractUserKey(iter->key()).ToString());
2161 }
2162}

2164TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, NoopTransformSeek) {
2165 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
2166 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(10));
2167
2168 Options options;
2169 options.comparator = BytewiseComparator();
2170 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2171 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewNoopTransform());
2172
2173 TableConstructor c(options.comparator);
2174 // To tickle the PrefixMayMatch bug it is important that the
2175 // user-key is a single byte so that the index key exactly matches
2176 // the user-key.
2177 InternalKey key("a", 1, kTypeValue);
2178 c.Add(key.Encode().ToString(), "b");
2179 std::vector<std::string> keys;
2180 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
2181 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
2182 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
2183 const InternalKeyComparator internal_comparator(options.comparator);
2184 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options, internal_comparator,
2185 &keys, &kvmap);
2186
2187 auto* reader = c.GetTableReader();
2188 for (int i = 0; i < 2; ++i) {
2189 ReadOptions ro;
2190 ro.total_order_seek = (i == 0);
2191 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter(reader->NewIterator(
2192 ro, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), /*arena=*/nullptr,
2193 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized));
2194
2195 iter->Seek(key.Encode());
2196 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
2197 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2198 ASSERT_EQ("a", ExtractUserKey(iter->key()).ToString());
2199 }
2200}

2246TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, BadChecksumType) {
2247 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
2248
2249 Options options;
2250 options.comparator = BytewiseComparator();
2251 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2252
2253 TableConstructor c(options.comparator);
2254 InternalKey key("abc", 1, kTypeValue);
2255 c.Add(key.Encode().ToString(), "test");
2256 std::vector<std::string> keys;
2257 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
2258 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
2259 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
2260 const InternalKeyComparator internal_comparator(options.comparator);
2261 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options, internal_comparator,
2262 &keys, &kvmap);
2263
2264 // Corrupt checksum type (123 is invalid)
2265 auto& sink = *c.TEST_GetSink();
2266 size_t len = sink.contents_.size();
2267 ASSERT_EQ(sink.contents_[len - Footer::kNewVersionsEncodedLength],
2268 table_options.checksum);
2269 sink.contents_[len - Footer::kNewVersionsEncodedLength] = char{123};
2270
2271 // (Re-)Open table file with bad checksum type
2272 const ImmutableOptions new_ioptions(options);
2273 const MutableCFOptions new_moptions(options);
2274 Status s = c.Reopen(new_ioptions, new_moptions);
2275 ASSERT_NOK(s);
2276 // "test" is file name
2277 ASSERT_EQ(s.ToString(),
2278 "Corruption: Corrupt or unsupported checksum type: 123 in test");
2279}

2281class BuiltinChecksumTest : public testing::Test,
2282 public testing::WithParamInterface<ChecksumType> {};

2284INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(SupportedChecksums, BuiltinChecksumTest,
2285 testing::ValuesIn(GetSupportedChecksums()));

2287namespace {
2288std::string ChecksumAsString(const std::string& data,
2289 ChecksumType checksum_type) {
2290 uint32_t v = ComputeBuiltinChecksum(checksum_type, data.data(), data.size());
2291
2292 // Verify consistency with other function
2293 if (data.size() >= 1) {
2294 EXPECT_EQ(v, ComputeBuiltinChecksumWithLastByte(
2295 checksum_type, data.data(), data.size() - 1, data.back()));
2296 }
2297 // Little endian as in file
2298 std::array<char, 4> raw_bytes;
2299 EncodeFixed32(raw_bytes.data(), v);
2300 return Slice(raw_bytes.data(), raw_bytes.size()).ToString(/*hex*/ true);
2301}
2302
2303std::string ChecksumAsString(std::string* data, char new_last_byte,
2304 ChecksumType checksum_type) {
2305 data->back() = new_last_byte;
2306 return ChecksumAsString(*data, checksum_type);
2307}
2308} // namespace
2309
2310// Make sure that checksum values don't change in later versions, even if
2311// consistent within current version.
2312TEST_P(BuiltinChecksumTest, ChecksumSchemas) {
2313 // Trailing 'x' chars will be replaced by compression type. Specifically,
2314 // the first byte of a block trailer is compression type, which is part of
2315 // the checksum input. This test does not deal with storing or parsing
2316 // checksums from the trailer (next 4 bytes of trailer).
2317 std::string b0 = "x";
2318 std::string b1 = "This is a short block!x";
2319 std::string b2;
2320 for (int i = 0; i < 100; ++i) {
2321 b2.append("This is a long block!");
2322 }
2323 b2.append("x");
2324
2325 std::string empty;
2326
2327 char ct1 = kNoCompression;
2328 char ct2 = kSnappyCompression;
2329 char ct3 = kZSTD;
2330
2331 ChecksumType t = GetParam();
2332 switch (t) {
2333 case kNoChecksum:
2334 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(empty, t), "00000000");
2335 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct1, t), "00000000");
2336 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct2, t), "00000000");
2337 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct3, t), "00000000");
2338 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct1, t), "00000000");
2339 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct2, t), "00000000");
2340 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct3, t), "00000000");
2341 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct1, t), "00000000");
2342 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct2, t), "00000000");
2343 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct3, t), "00000000");
2344 break;
2345 case kCRC32c:
2346 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(empty, t), "D8EA82A2");
2347 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct1, t), "D28F2549");
2348 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct2, t), "052B2843");
2349 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct3, t), "46F8F711");
2350 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct1, t), "583F0355");
2351 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct2, t), "2F9B0A57");
2352 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct3, t), "ECE7DA1D");
2353 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct1, t), "943EF0AB");
2354 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct2, t), "43A2EDB1");
2355 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct3, t), "00E53D63");
2356 break;
2357 case kxxHash:
2358 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(empty, t), "055DCC02");
2359 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct1, t), "3EB065CF");
2360 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct2, t), "31F79238");
2361 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct3, t), "320D2E00");
2362 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct1, t), "4A2E5FB0");
2363 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct2, t), "0BD9F652");
2364 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct3, t), "B4107E50");
2365 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct1, t), "20F4D4BA");
2366 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct2, t), "8F1A1F99");
2367 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct3, t), "A191A338");
2368 break;
2369 case kxxHash64:
2370 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(empty, t), "99E9D851");
2371 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct1, t), "682705DB");
2372 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct2, t), "30E7211B");
2373 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct3, t), "B7BB58E8");
2374 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct1, t), "B74655EF");
2375 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct2, t), "B6C8BBBE");
2376 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct3, t), "AED9E3B4");
2377 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct1, t), "0D4999FE");
2378 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct2, t), "F5932423");
2379 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct3, t), "6B31BAB1");
2380 break;
2381 case kXXH3:
2382 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(empty, t), "00000000");
2383 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct1, t), "C294D338");
2384 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct2, t), "1B174353");
2385 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b0, ct3, t), "2D0E20C8");
2386 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct1, t), "B37FB5E6");
2387 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct2, t), "6AFC258D");
2388 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b1, ct3, t), "5CE54616");
2389 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct1, t), "FA2D482E");
2390 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct2, t), "23AED845");
2391 EXPECT_EQ(ChecksumAsString(&b2, ct3, t), "15B7BBDE");
2392 break;
2393 default:
2394 // Force this test to be updated on new ChecksumTypes
2395 assert(false);
2396 break;
2397 }
2398}
