2400TEST_P(BuiltinChecksumTest, ChecksumZeroInputs) {
2401 // Verify that no reasonably sized "all zeros" inputs produce "all zeros"
2402 // output. Otherwise, "wiped" data could appear to be well-formed.
2403 // Assuming essentially random assignment of output values, the likelihood
2404 // of encountering checksum == 0 for an input not specifically crafted is
2405 // 1 in 4 billion.
2406 if (GetParam() == kNoChecksum) {
2407 return;
2408 }
2409 // "Thorough" case is too slow for continouous testing
2410 bool thorough = getenv("ROCKSDB_THOROUGH_CHECKSUM_TEST") != nullptr;
2411 // Verified through 10M
2412 size_t kMaxZerosLen = thorough ? 10000000 : 20000;
2413 std::string zeros(kMaxZerosLen, '\0');
2414
2415 for (size_t len = 0; len < kMaxZerosLen; ++len) {
2416 if (thorough && (len & 0xffffU) == 0) {
2417 fprintf(stderr, "t=%u len=%u\n", (unsigned)GetParam(), (unsigned)len);
2418 }
2419 uint32_t v = ComputeBuiltinChecksum(GetParam(), zeros.data(), len);
2420 if (v == 0U) {
2421 // One exception case:
2422 if (GetParam() == kXXH3 && len == 0) {
2423 // This is not a big deal because assuming the block length is known
2424 // from the block handle, which comes from a checksum-verified block,
2425 // there is nothing to corrupt in a zero-length block. And when there
2426 // is a block trailer with compression byte (as in block-based table),
2427 // zero length checksummed data never arises.
2428 continue;
2429 }
2430 // Only compute this on failure
2431 SCOPED_TRACE("len=" + std::to_string(len));
2432 ASSERT_NE(v, 0U);
2433 }
2434 }
2435}
2436
2437void AddInternalKey(TableConstructor* c, const std::string& prefix,
2438 std::string value = "v", int /*suffix_len*/ = 800) {
2439 static Random rnd(1023);
2440 InternalKey k(prefix + rnd.RandomString(800), 0, kTypeValue);
2441 c->Add(k.Encode().ToString(), value);
2442}
2443
2444void TableTest::IndexTest(BlockBasedTableOptions table_options) {
2445 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator());
2446
2447 // keys with prefix length 3, make sure the key/value is big enough to fill
2448 // one block
2449 AddInternalKey(&c, "0015");
2450 AddInternalKey(&c, "0035");
2451
2452 AddInternalKey(&c, "0054");
2453 AddInternalKey(&c, "0055");
2454
2455 AddInternalKey(&c, "0056");
2456 AddInternalKey(&c, "0057");
2457
2458 AddInternalKey(&c, "0058");
2459 AddInternalKey(&c, "0075");
2460
2461 AddInternalKey(&c, "0076");
2462 AddInternalKey(&c, "0095");
2463
2464 std::vector<std::string> keys;
2465 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
2466 Options options;
2467 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewFixedPrefixTransform(3));
2468 table_options.block_size = 1700;
2469 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(1024, 4);
2470 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2471
2472 std::unique_ptr<InternalKeyComparator> comparator(
2473 new InternalKeyComparator(BytewiseComparator()));
2474 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
2475 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
2476 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options, *comparator, &keys,
2477 &kvmap);
2478 auto reader = c.GetTableReader();
2479
2480 auto props = reader->GetTableProperties();
2481 ASSERT_EQ(5u, props->num_data_blocks);
2482
2483 // TODO(Zhongyi): update test to use MutableCFOptions
2484 ReadOptions read_options;
2485 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> index_iter(reader->NewIterator(
2486 read_options, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), /*arena=*/nullptr,
2487 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized));
2488
2489 // -- Find keys do not exist, but have common prefix.
2490 std::vector<std::string> prefixes = {"001", "003", "005", "007", "009"};
2491 std::vector<std::string> lower_bound = {
2492 keys[0], keys[1], keys[2], keys[7], keys[9],
2493 };
2494
2495 // find the lower bound of the prefix
2496 for (size_t i = 0; i < prefixes.size(); ++i) {
2497 index_iter->Seek(InternalKey(prefixes[i], 0, kTypeValue).Encode());
2498 ASSERT_OK(index_iter->status());
2499 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter->Valid());
2500
2501 // seek the first element in the block
2502 ASSERT_EQ(lower_bound[i], index_iter->key().ToString());
2503 ASSERT_EQ("v", index_iter->value().ToString());
2504 }
2505
2506 // find the upper bound of prefixes
2507 std::vector<std::string> upper_bound = {
2508 keys[1],
2509 keys[2],
2510 keys[7],
2511 keys[9],
2512 };
2513
2514 // find existing keys
2515 for (const auto& item : kvmap) {
2516 auto ukey = ExtractUserKey(item.first).ToString();
2517 index_iter->Seek(ukey);
2518
2519 // ASSERT_OK(regular_iter->status());
2520 ASSERT_OK(index_iter->status());
2521
2522 // ASSERT_TRUE(regular_iter->Valid());
2523 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter->Valid());
2524
2525 ASSERT_EQ(item.first, index_iter->key().ToString());
2526 ASSERT_EQ(item.second, index_iter->value().ToString());
2527 }
2528
2529 for (size_t i = 0; i < prefixes.size(); ++i) {
2530 // the key is greater than any existing keys.
2531 auto key = prefixes[i] + "9";
2532 index_iter->Seek(InternalKey(key, 0, kTypeValue).Encode());
2533
2534 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter->status().ok() || index_iter->status().IsNotFound());
2535 ASSERT_TRUE(!index_iter->status().IsNotFound() || !index_iter->Valid());
2536 if (i == prefixes.size() - 1) {
2537 // last key
2538 ASSERT_TRUE(!index_iter->Valid());
2539 } else {
2540 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter->Valid());
2541 // seek the first element in the block
2542 ASSERT_EQ(upper_bound[i], index_iter->key().ToString());
2543 ASSERT_EQ("v", index_iter->value().ToString());
2544 }
2545 }
2546
2547 // find keys with prefix that don't match any of the existing prefixes.
2548 std::vector<std::string> non_exist_prefixes = {"002", "004", "006", "008"};
2549 for (const auto& prefix : non_exist_prefixes) {
2550 index_iter->Seek(InternalKey(prefix, 0, kTypeValue).Encode());
2551 // regular_iter->Seek(prefix);
2552
2553 ASSERT_OK(index_iter->status());
2554 // Seek to non-existing prefixes should yield either invalid, or a
2555 // key with prefix greater than the target.
2556 if (index_iter->Valid()) {
2557 Slice ukey = ExtractUserKey(index_iter->key());
2558 Slice ukey_prefix = options.prefix_extractor->Transform(ukey);
2559 ASSERT_TRUE(BytewiseComparator()->Compare(prefix, ukey_prefix) < 0);
2560 }
2561 }
2562 for (const auto& prefix : non_exist_prefixes) {
2563 index_iter->SeekForPrev(InternalKey(prefix, 0, kTypeValue).Encode());
2564 // regular_iter->Seek(prefix);
2565
2566 ASSERT_OK(index_iter->status());
2567 // Seek to non-existing prefixes should yield either invalid, or a
2568 // key with prefix greater than the target.
2569 if (index_iter->Valid()) {
2570 Slice ukey = ExtractUserKey(index_iter->key());
2571 Slice ukey_prefix = options.prefix_extractor->Transform(ukey);
2572 ASSERT_TRUE(BytewiseComparator()->Compare(prefix, ukey_prefix) > 0);
2573 }
2574 }
2575
2576 {
2577 // Test reseek case. It should impact partitioned index more.
2578 ReadOptions ro;
2579 ro.total_order_seek = true;
2580 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> index_iter2(reader->NewIterator(
2581 ro, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), /*arena=*/nullptr,
2582 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized));
2583
2584 // Things to cover in partitioned index:
2585 // 1. Both of Seek() and SeekToLast() has optimization to prevent
2586 // rereek leaf index block if it remains to the same one, and
2587 // they reuse the same variable.
2588 // 2. When Next() or Prev() is called, the block moves, so the
2589 // optimization should kick in only with the current one.
2590 index_iter2->Seek(InternalKey("0055", 0, kTypeValue).Encode());
2591 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2592 ASSERT_EQ("0055", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2593
2594 index_iter2->SeekToLast();
2595 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2596 ASSERT_EQ("0095", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2597
2598 index_iter2->Seek(InternalKey("0055", 0, kTypeValue).Encode());
2599 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2600 ASSERT_EQ("0055", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2601
2602 index_iter2->SeekToLast();
2603 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2604 ASSERT_EQ("0095", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2605 index_iter2->Prev();
2606 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2607 index_iter2->Prev();
2608 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2609 ASSERT_EQ("0075", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2610
2611 index_iter2->Seek(InternalKey("0095", 0, kTypeValue).Encode());
2612 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2613 ASSERT_EQ("0095", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2614 index_iter2->Prev();
2615 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2616 index_iter2->Prev();
2617 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2618 ASSERT_EQ("0075", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2619
2620 index_iter2->SeekToLast();
2621 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2622 ASSERT_EQ("0095", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2623
2624 index_iter2->Seek(InternalKey("0095", 0, kTypeValue).Encode());
2625 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2626 ASSERT_EQ("0095", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2627
2628 index_iter2->Prev();
2629 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2630 index_iter2->Prev();
2631 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2632 ASSERT_EQ("0075", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2633
2634 index_iter2->Seek(InternalKey("0075", 0, kTypeValue).Encode());
2635 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2636 ASSERT_EQ("0075", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2637
2638 index_iter2->Next();
2639 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2640 index_iter2->Next();
2641 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2642 ASSERT_EQ("0095", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2643
2644 index_iter2->SeekToLast();
2645 ASSERT_TRUE(index_iter2->Valid());
2646 ASSERT_EQ("0095", index_iter2->key().ToString().substr(0, 4));
2647 }
2648
2649 c.ResetTableReader();
2650}

2676TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, IndexSeekOptimizationIncomplete) {

2703 };
2704

2707 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->status().IsIncomplete());
2708
2709 // This used to crash at some point.
2710 iter->Seek(ikey("pika"));
2711 ASSERT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
2712 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->status().IsIncomplete());
2713}

2720
2721class CustomFlushBlockPolicy : public FlushBlockPolicyFactory,
2722 public FlushBlockPolicy {
2723 public:
2724 explicit CustomFlushBlockPolicy(std::vector<int> keys_per_block)
2725 : keys_per_block_(keys_per_block) {}
2726
2727 const char* Name() const override { return "CustomFlushBlockPolicy"; }
2728
2729 FlushBlockPolicy* NewFlushBlockPolicy(const BlockBasedTableOptions&,
2730 const BlockBuilder&) const override {
2731 return new CustomFlushBlockPolicy(keys_per_block_);
2732 }
2733
2734 bool Update(const Slice&, const Slice&) override {
2735 if (keys_in_current_block_ >= keys_per_block_.at(current_block_idx_)) {
2736 ++current_block_idx_;
2737 keys_in_current_block_ = 1;
2738 return true;
2739 }
2740
2741 ++keys_in_current_block_;
2742 return false;
2743 }
2744
2745 std::vector<int> keys_per_block_;
2746
2747 int current_block_idx_ = 0;
2748 int keys_in_current_block_ = 0;
2749};
2750
2751TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, BinaryIndexWithFirstKey2) {
2752 for (int use_first_key = 0; use_first_key < 2; ++use_first_key) {
2753 SCOPED_TRACE("use_first_key = " + std::to_string(use_first_key));
2754 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
2755 table_options.index_type =
2756 use_first_key ? BlockBasedTableOptions::kBinarySearchWithFirstKey
2757 : BlockBasedTableOptions::kBinarySearch;
2758 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(10000); // fits all blocks
2759 table_options.index_shortening =
2760 BlockBasedTableOptions::IndexShorteningMode::kNoShortening;
2761 table_options.flush_block_policy_factory =
2762 std::make_shared<CustomFlushBlockPolicy>(std::vector<int>{2, 1, 3, 2});
2763 Options options;
2764 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2765 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
2766 Statistics* stats = options.statistics.get();
2767 std::unique_ptr<InternalKeyComparator> comparator(
2768 new InternalKeyComparator(BytewiseComparator()));
2769 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
2770 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
2771
2772 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator());
2773
2774 // Block 0.
2775 AddInternalKey(&c, "aaaa", "v0");
2776 AddInternalKey(&c, "aaac", "v1");
2777
2778 // Block 1.
2779 AddInternalKey(&c, "aaca", "v2");
2780
2781 // Block 2.
2782 AddInternalKey(&c, "caaa", "v3");
2783 AddInternalKey(&c, "caac", "v4");
2784 AddInternalKey(&c, "caae", "v5");
2785
2786 // Block 3.
2787 AddInternalKey(&c, "ccaa", "v6");
2788 AddInternalKey(&c, "ccac", "v7");
2789
2790 // Write the file.
2791 std::vector<std::string> keys;
2792 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
2793 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options, *comparator, &keys,
2794 &kvmap);
2795 ASSERT_EQ(8, keys.size());
2796
2797 auto reader = c.GetTableReader();
2798 auto props = reader->GetTableProperties();
2799 ASSERT_EQ(4u, props->num_data_blocks);
2800 ReadOptions read_options;
2801 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter(reader->NewIterator(
2802 read_options, /*prefix_extractor=*/nullptr, /*arena=*/nullptr,
2803 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized,
2804 /*compaction_readahead_size=*/0, /*allow_unprepared_value=*/true));
2805
2806 // Shouldn't have read data blocks before iterator is seeked.
2807 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2808 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2809
2810 auto ikey = [](Slice user_key) {
2811 return InternalKey(user_key, 0, kTypeValue).Encode().ToString();
2812 };
2813
2814 // Seek to a key between blocks. If index contains first key, we shouldn't
2815 // read any data blocks until value is requested.
2816 iter->Seek(ikey("aaba"));
2817 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2818 EXPECT_EQ(keys[2], iter->key().ToString());
2819 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 0 : 1,
2820 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2821 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->PrepareValue());
2822 EXPECT_EQ("v2", iter->value().ToString());
2823 EXPECT_EQ(1, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2824 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2825
2826 // Seek to the middle of a block. The block should be read right away.
2827 iter->Seek(ikey("caab"));
2828 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2829 EXPECT_EQ(keys[4], iter->key().ToString());
2830 EXPECT_EQ(2, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2831 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2832 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->PrepareValue());
2833 EXPECT_EQ("v4", iter->value().ToString());
2834 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2835
2836 // Seek to just before the same block and don't access value.
2837 // The iterator should keep pinning the block contents.
2838 iter->Seek(ikey("baaa"));
2839 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2840 EXPECT_EQ(keys[3], iter->key().ToString());
2841 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2842
2843 // Seek to the same block again to check that the block is still pinned.
2844 iter->Seek(ikey("caae"));
2845 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2846 EXPECT_EQ(keys[5], iter->key().ToString());
2847 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2848 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->PrepareValue());
2849 EXPECT_EQ("v5", iter->value().ToString());
2850 EXPECT_EQ(2, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2851 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2852
2853 // Step forward and fall through to the next block. Don't access value.
2854 iter->Next();
2855 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2856 EXPECT_EQ(keys[6], iter->key().ToString());
2857 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 2 : 3,
2858 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2859 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2860
2861 // Step forward again. Block should be read.
2862 iter->Next();
2863 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2864 EXPECT_EQ(keys[7], iter->key().ToString());
2865 EXPECT_EQ(3, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2866 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->PrepareValue());
2867 EXPECT_EQ("v7", iter->value().ToString());
2868 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2869
2870 // Step forward and reach the end.
2871 iter->Next();
2872 EXPECT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
2873 EXPECT_EQ(3, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2874 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2875
2876 // Seek to a single-key block and step forward without accessing value.
2877 iter->Seek(ikey("aaca"));
2878 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2879 EXPECT_EQ(keys[2], iter->key().ToString());
2880 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 0 : 1,
2881 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2882
2883 iter->Next();
2884 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2885 EXPECT_EQ(keys[3], iter->key().ToString());
2886 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 1 : 2,
2887 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2888 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->PrepareValue());
2889 EXPECT_EQ("v3", iter->value().ToString());
2890 EXPECT_EQ(2, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2891 EXPECT_EQ(3, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2892
2893 // Seek between blocks and step back without accessing value.
2894 iter->Seek(ikey("aaca"));
2895 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2896 EXPECT_EQ(keys[2], iter->key().ToString());
2897 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 2 : 3,
2898 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2899 EXPECT_EQ(3, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2900
2901 iter->Prev();
2902 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2903 EXPECT_EQ(keys[1], iter->key().ToString());
2904 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 2 : 3,
2905 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2906 // All blocks are in cache now, there'll be no more misses ever.
2907 EXPECT_EQ(4, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2908 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->PrepareValue());
2909 EXPECT_EQ("v1", iter->value().ToString());
2910
2911 // Next into the next block again.
2912 iter->Next();
2913 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2914 EXPECT_EQ(keys[2], iter->key().ToString());
2915 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 2 : 4,
2916 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2917
2918 // Seek to first and step back without accessing value.
2919 iter->SeekToFirst();
2920 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2921 EXPECT_EQ(keys[0], iter->key().ToString());
2922 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 2 : 5,
2923 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2924
2925 iter->Prev();
2926 EXPECT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
2927 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 2 : 5,
2928 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2929
2930 // Do some SeekForPrev() and SeekToLast() just to cover all methods.
2931 iter->SeekForPrev(ikey("caad"));
2932 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2933 EXPECT_EQ(keys[4], iter->key().ToString());
2934 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 3 : 6,
2935 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2936 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->PrepareValue());
2937 EXPECT_EQ("v4", iter->value().ToString());
2938 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 3 : 6,
2939 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2940
2941 iter->SeekToLast();
2942 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2943 EXPECT_EQ(keys[7], iter->key().ToString());
2944 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 4 : 7,
2945 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2946 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->PrepareValue());
2947 EXPECT_EQ("v7", iter->value().ToString());
2948 EXPECT_EQ(use_first_key ? 4 : 7,
2949 stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
2950
2951 EXPECT_EQ(4, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2952
2953 c.ResetTableReader();
2954 }
2955}

2957TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, BinaryIndexWithFirstKeyGlobalSeqno) {
2958 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
2959 table_options.index_type = BlockBasedTableOptions::kBinarySearchWithFirstKey;
2960 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(10000);
2961 Options options;
2962 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
2963 Statistics* stats = options.statistics.get();
2964 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
2965 std::unique_ptr<InternalKeyComparator> comparator(
2966 new InternalKeyComparator(BytewiseComparator()));
2967 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
2968 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
2969
2970 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), /* convert_to_internal_key */ false,
2971 /* level */ -1, /* largest_seqno */ 42);
2972
2973 c.Add(InternalKey("b", 0, kTypeValue).Encode().ToString(), "x");
2974 c.Add(InternalKey("c", 0, kTypeValue).Encode().ToString(), "y");
2975
2976 std::vector<std::string> keys;
2977 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
2978 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options, *comparator, &keys,
2979 &kvmap);
2980 ASSERT_EQ(2, keys.size());
2981
2982 auto reader = c.GetTableReader();
2983 auto props = reader->GetTableProperties();
2984 ASSERT_EQ(1u, props->num_data_blocks);
2985 ReadOptions read_options;
2986 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter(reader->NewIterator(
2987 read_options, /*prefix_extractor=*/nullptr, /*arena=*/nullptr,
2988 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized,
2989 /*compaction_readahead_size=*/0, /*allow_unprepared_value=*/true));
2990
2991 iter->Seek(InternalKey("a", 0, kTypeValue).Encode().ToString());
2992 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
2993 EXPECT_EQ(InternalKey("b", 42, kTypeValue).Encode().ToString(),
2994 iter->key().ToString());
2995 EXPECT_NE(keys[0], iter->key().ToString());
2996 // Key should have been served from index, without reading data blocks.
2997 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
2998
2999 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->PrepareValue());
3000 EXPECT_EQ("x", iter->value().ToString());
3001 EXPECT_EQ(1, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS));
3002 EXPECT_EQ(0, stats->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT));
3003 EXPECT_EQ(InternalKey("b", 42, kTypeValue).Encode().ToString(),
3004 iter->key().ToString());
3005
3006 c.ResetTableReader();
3007}
3008
3009// It's very hard to figure out the index block size of a block accurately.
3010// To make sure we get the index size, we just make sure as key number
3011// grows, the filter block size also grows.
3012TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, IndexSizeStat) {
3013 uint64_t last_index_size = 0;
3014
3015 // we need to use random keys since the pure human readable texts
3016 // may be well compressed, resulting insignifcant change of index
3017 // block size.
3018 Random rnd(test::RandomSeed());
3019 std::vector<std::string> keys;
3020
3021 for (int i = 0; i < 100; ++i) {
3022 keys.push_back(rnd.RandomString(10000));
3023 }
3024
3025 // Each time we load one more key to the table. the table index block
3026 // size is expected to be larger than last time's.
3027 for (size_t i = 1; i < keys.size(); ++i) {
3028 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(),
3029 true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
3030 for (size_t j = 0; j < i; ++j) {
3031 c.Add(keys[j], "val");
3032 }
3033
3034 std::vector<std::string> ks;
3035 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
3036 Options options;
3037 options.compression = kNoCompression;
3038 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
3039 table_options.block_restart_interval = 1;
3040 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
3041
3042 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
3043 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
3044 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
3045 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &ks, &kvmap);
3046 auto index_size = c.GetTableReader()->GetTableProperties()->index_size;
3047 ASSERT_GT(index_size, last_index_size);
3048 last_index_size = index_size;
3049 c.ResetTableReader();
3050 }
3051}

3053TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, NumBlockStat) {
3054 Random rnd(test::RandomSeed());
3055 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
3056 Options options;
3057 options.compression = kNoCompression;
3058 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
3059 table_options.block_restart_interval = 1;
3060 table_options.block_size = 1000;
3061 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
3062

3064 // the key/val are slightly smaller than block size, so that each block
3065 // holds roughly one key/value pair.
3066 c.Add(rnd.RandomString(900), "val");
3067 }
3068
3069 std::vector<std::string> ks;
3070 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;

3075 ASSERT_EQ(kvmap.size(),
3076 c.GetTableReader()->GetTableProperties()->num_data_blocks);
3077 c.ResetTableReader();
3078}

3080TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, TracingGetTest) {
3081 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator());
3082 Options options;
3083 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
3084 options.create_if_missing = true;
3085 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(1024 * 1024, 0);
3086 table_options.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = true;
3087 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(10));
3088 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
3089 SetupTracingTest(&c);
3090 std::vector<std::string> keys;
3091 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
3092 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
3093 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
3094 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
3095 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
3096 InternalKey internal_key(auto_add_key1, 0, kTypeValue);
3097 std::string encoded_key = internal_key.Encode().ToString();
3098 for (uint32_t i = 1; i <= 2; i++) {
3099 PinnableSlice value;
3100 GetContext get_context(
3101 options.comparator, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, GetContext::kNotFound,
3102 auto_add_key1, &value, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr,
3103 nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, /*tracing_get_id=*/i);
3104 get_perf_context()->Reset();
3105 ASSERT_OK(c.GetTableReader()->Get(ReadOptions(), encoded_key, &get_context,
3106 moptions.prefix_extractor.get()));
3107 ASSERT_EQ(get_context.State(), GetContext::kFound);
3108 ASSERT_EQ(value.ToString(), kDummyValue);
3109 }
3110
3111 // Verify traces.
3112 std::vector<BlockCacheTraceRecord> expected_records;
3113 // The first two records should be prefetching index and filter blocks.
3114 BlockCacheTraceRecord record;
3115 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceIndexBlock;
3116 record.caller = TableReaderCaller::kPrefetch;
3117 record.is_cache_hit = false;
3118 record.no_insert = false;
3119 expected_records.push_back(record);
3120 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceFilterBlock;
3121 expected_records.push_back(record);
3122 // Then we should have three records for one index, one filter, and one data
3123 // block access.
3124 record.get_id = 1;
3125 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceFilterBlock;
3126 record.caller = TableReaderCaller::kUserGet;
3127 record.get_from_user_specified_snapshot = false;
3128 record.referenced_key = encoded_key;
3129 record.referenced_key_exist_in_block = true;
3130 record.is_cache_hit = true;
3131 expected_records.push_back(record);
3132 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceIndexBlock;
3133 expected_records.push_back(record);
3134 record.is_cache_hit = false;
3135 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceDataBlock;
3136 expected_records.push_back(record);
3137 // The second get should all observe cache hits.
3138 record.is_cache_hit = true;
3139 record.get_id = 2;
3140 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceFilterBlock;
3141 record.caller = TableReaderCaller::kUserGet;
3142 record.get_from_user_specified_snapshot = false;
3143 record.referenced_key = encoded_key;
3144 expected_records.push_back(record);
3145 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceIndexBlock;
3146 expected_records.push_back(record);
3147 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceDataBlock;
3148 expected_records.push_back(record);
3149 VerifyBlockAccessTrace(&c, expected_records);
3150 c.ResetTableReader();
3151}
3152
3153void GenerateKVMap(TableConstructor* c) {
3154 int num_block = 100;
3155 Random rnd(101);
3156 uint32_t key = 0;
3157 for (int block = 0; block < num_block; block++) {
3158 for (int i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
3159 char k[9] = {0};
3160 // Internal key is constructed directly from this key,
3161 // and internal key size is required to be >= 8 bytes,
3162 // so use %08u as the format string.
3163 snprintf(k, sizeof(k), "%08u", key);
3164 std::string v = rnd.RandomString(256);
3165 InternalKey ikey(std::string(k), 0, kTypeValue);
3166 c->Add(ikey.Encode().ToString(), rnd.RandomString(256));
3167 key++;
3168 }
3169 }
3170}
3171
3172void WarmUpCache(TableConstructor* c, const MutableCFOptions& moptions,
3173 const std::vector<std::string>& warm_keys) {
3174 ReadOptions ro;
3175 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter(c->GetTableReader()->NewIterator(
3176 ro, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), nullptr, false,
3177 TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized));
3178 size_t i = 0;
3179 while (i < warm_keys.size()) {
3180 InternalKey ikey(warm_keys[i], 0, kTypeValue);
3181 iter->Seek(ikey.Encode().ToString());
3182 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3183 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
3184 i++;
3185 }
3186}

3188TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, BlockCacheLookupSeqScans) {
3189 Options options;
3190 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
3191 options.create_if_missing = true;
3192 options.compression = kNoCompression;
3193 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
3194 table_options.index_type =
3195 BlockBasedTableOptions::IndexType::kTwoLevelIndexSearch;
3196 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(1024 * 1024, 0);
3197 table_options.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = true;
3198 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(10, true));
3199 table_options.block_align = true;
3200 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
3201 ASSERT_OK(options.table_factory->ValidateOptions(
3202 DBOptions(options), ColumnFamilyOptions(options)));
3203
3204 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator());
3205 GenerateKVMap(&c);
3206
3207 std::vector<std::string> keys;
3208 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
3209 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
3210 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
3211 const InternalKeyComparator internal_comparator(options.comparator);
3212
3213 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options, internal_comparator,
3214 &keys, &kvmap);
3215
3216 BlockBasedTable* bbt = static_cast<BlockBasedTable*>(c.GetTableReader());
3217 BlockHandle block_handle;
3218
3219 ReadOptions read_options;
3220 read_options.auto_readahead_size = true;
3221 Slice ub = Slice("00000805");
3222 Slice* ub_ptr = &ub;
3223 read_options.iterate_upper_bound = ub_ptr;
3224 read_options.readahead_size = 16384;
3225
3226 // Test various functionalities -
3227 // 5 blocks prefetched - Current + 4 additional (readahead_size).
3228 {
3229 // Check the behavior when it's -
3230 // Miss(200), Hit(210), Hit(225), Hit(240), Hit(255).
3231 // It should only prefetch current block (200).
3232 {
3233 std::vector<std::string> warm_keys{"00000210", "00000225", "00000240",
3234 "00000255"};
3235 WarmUpCache(&c, moptions, warm_keys);
3236
3237 ASSERT_OK(options.statistics->Reset());
3238
3239 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter(c.GetTableReader()->NewIterator(
3240 read_options, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), /*arena=*/nullptr,
3241 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized));
3242
3243 // Seek key -
3244 InternalKey ikey("00000200", 0, kTypeValue);
3245 auto kv_iter = kvmap.find(ikey.Encode().ToString());
3246
3247 iter->Seek(kv_iter->first);
3248 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3249 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
3250 ASSERT_EQ(iter->key(), kv_iter->first);
3251 ASSERT_EQ(iter->value().ToString(), kv_iter->second);
3252
3253 FilePrefetchBuffer* prefetch_buffer =
3254 (static_cast<BlockBasedTableIterator*>(iter.get()))
3255 ->prefetch_buffer();
3256 std::vector<std::tuple<uint64_t, size_t, bool>> buffer_info(1);
3257 prefetch_buffer->TEST_GetBufferOffsetandSize(buffer_info);
3258
3259 bbt->TEST_GetDataBlockHandle(read_options, kv_iter->first, block_handle);
3260 // It won't prefetch the data of cache hit.
3261 // One block data.
3262 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[0]), 4096);
3263 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<0>(buffer_info[0]), block_handle.offset());
3264
3265 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getAndResetTickerCount(READAHEAD_TRIMMED),
3266 1);
3267 }
3268
3269 {
3270 // Check the behavior when it's -
3271 // First Prefetch - Miss(315), Miss(330), Miss(345), Hit(360), Hit(375),
3272 // Second Prefetch - Miss(390), Miss(405) ...
3273 // First prefetch should only prefetch from 315 to 345.
3274 std::vector<std::string> warm_keys{"00000360", "00000375"};
3275 WarmUpCache(&c, moptions, warm_keys);
3276
3277 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter(c.GetTableReader()->NewIterator(
3278 read_options, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), nullptr, false,
3279 TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized));
3280
3281 // Seek key -
3282 InternalKey ikey("00000315", 0, kTypeValue);
3283 auto kv_iter = kvmap.find(ikey.Encode().ToString());
3284
3285 iter->Seek(kv_iter->first);
3286 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3287 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
3288 ASSERT_EQ(iter->key(), kv_iter->first);
3289 ASSERT_EQ(iter->value().ToString(), kv_iter->second);
3290
3291 FilePrefetchBuffer* prefetch_buffer =
3292 (static_cast<BlockBasedTableIterator*>(iter.get()))
3293 ->prefetch_buffer();
3294 std::vector<std::tuple<uint64_t, size_t, bool>> buffer_info(1);
3295 prefetch_buffer->TEST_GetBufferOffsetandSize(buffer_info);
3296 bbt->TEST_GetDataBlockHandle(read_options, kv_iter->first, block_handle);
3297
3298 // It won't prefetch the data of cache hit.
3299 // 3 blocks data.
3300 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[0]), 12288);
3301 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<0>(buffer_info[0]), block_handle.offset());
3302
3303 for (; kv_iter != kvmap.end() && iter->Valid(); kv_iter++) {
3304 ASSERT_EQ(iter->key(), kv_iter->first);
3305 ASSERT_EQ(iter->value().ToString(), kv_iter->second);
3306 iter->Next();
3307 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3308
3309 if (iter->user_key().ToString() == "00000400") {
3310 break;
3311 }
3312 }
3313
3314 // Second Prefetch.
3315 prefetch_buffer->TEST_GetBufferOffsetandSize(buffer_info);
3316 bbt->TEST_GetDataBlockHandle(read_options, kv_iter->first, block_handle);
3317 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[0]), 20480);
3318 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<0>(buffer_info[0]), block_handle.offset());
3319
3320 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getAndResetTickerCount(READAHEAD_TRIMMED),
3321 1);
3322 }
3323 }
3324 c.ResetTableReader();
3325}

3376 // 2nd Prefetch - Hit(240), Hit(255)

3381 "00000255"};

3406 prefetch_buffer->TEST_GetBufferOffsetandSize(buffer_info);

3408 bbt->TEST_GetDataBlockHandle(read_options, kv_iter->first, block_handle);
3409 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<0>(buffer_info[0]), block_handle.offset());

3411 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[1]), 0);

3413 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getAndResetTickerCount(READAHEAD_TRIMMED),
3414 2);
3415 }
3416 {
3417 // Check the behavior when it's -
3418 // First Prefetch - Miss(315), Miss(330), Hit(345),
3419 // Second Prefetch - Miss(360), Miss(375), ...
3420 // First prefetch should only prefetch from 315 to 330.
3421 // Second prefetch should start from 360.
3422 std::vector<std::string> warm_keys{"00000345"};
3423 WarmUpCache(&c, moptions, warm_keys);
3424

3426 read_options, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), nullptr, false,
3427 TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized));

3451 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[0]), 8192);

3458 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[1]), 8192);

3462 }
3463 }
3464
3465 {
3466 // Check the behavior when it's -
3467 // First Prefetch - Miss(495), Miss(510), Hit(525), prefetch len- 8192
3468 // Second Prefetch async - Miss(540), Miss(555), - 8192
3469 // Third Prefetch Async - Hit(570), Miss(585), - 4096
3470 // 4th Prefetch Async - Hit(600), Miss(615), - 4096
3471 // 5th Prefetch Async - Miss(630), Miss(645) - 8192
3472 std::vector<std::string> warm_keys{"00000525", "00000570", "00000600"};
3473 WarmUpCache(&c, moptions, warm_keys);
3474
3475 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter(c.GetTableReader()->NewIterator(
3476 read_options, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), /*arena=*/nullptr,
3477 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized));
3478

3480 InternalKey ikey("00000495", 0, kTypeValue);
3481 auto kv_iter = kvmap.find(ikey.Encode().ToString());
3482

3484 iter->Seek(kv_iter->first);
3485 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->status().IsTryAgain());
3486 iter->Seek(kv_iter->first);
3487 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3488 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
3489 ASSERT_EQ(iter->key(), kv_iter->first);
3490 ASSERT_EQ(iter->value().ToString(), kv_iter->second);

3493 (static_cast<BlockBasedTableIterator*>(iter.get()))
3494 ->prefetch_buffer();
3495
3496 {
3497 std::vector<std::tuple<uint64_t, size_t, bool>> buffer_info(2);
3498 prefetch_buffer->TEST_GetBufferOffsetandSize(buffer_info);
3499
3500 // 1st Buffer Verification.
3501 bbt->TEST_GetDataBlockHandle(read_options, kv_iter->first,
3502 block_handle);
3503 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<0>(buffer_info[0]), block_handle.offset());
3504 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[0]), 8192);
3505
3506 // 2nd Buffer Verification.
3507 InternalKey ikey_tmp("00000540", 0, kTypeValue);
3508 bbt->TEST_GetDataBlockHandle(read_options, ikey_tmp.Encode().ToString(),
3509 block_handle);
3510 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<0>(buffer_info[1]), block_handle.offset());
3511 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[1]), 8192);
3512
3513 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getAndResetTickerCount(READAHEAD_TRIMMED),
3514 1);
3515 }
3516
3517 // Third prefetch ReadAsync (buffers will swap).
3518 for (; kv_iter != kvmap.end() && iter->Valid(); kv_iter++) {
3519 ASSERT_EQ(iter->key(), kv_iter->first);
3520 ASSERT_EQ(iter->value().ToString(), kv_iter->second);
3521
3522 if (iter->user_key() == "00000540") {
3523 break;
3524 }
3525
3526 iter->Next();
3527 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3528 }
3529
3530 {
3531 std::vector<std::tuple<uint64_t, size_t, bool>> buffer_info(2);
3532 prefetch_buffer->TEST_GetBufferOffsetandSize(buffer_info);
3533
3534 // 1st Buffer Verification.
3535 bbt->TEST_GetDataBlockHandle(read_options, kv_iter->first,
3536 block_handle);
3537 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<0>(buffer_info[0]), block_handle.offset());
3538 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[0]), 8192);
3539
3540 // 2nd Buffer Verification.
3541 InternalKey ikey_tmp("00000585", 0, kTypeValue);
3542 bbt->TEST_GetDataBlockHandle(read_options, ikey_tmp.Encode().ToString(),
3543 block_handle);
3544 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<0>(buffer_info[1]), block_handle.offset());
3545 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[1]), 4096);
3546
3547 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getAndResetTickerCount(READAHEAD_TRIMMED),
3548 1);
3549 }
3550
3551 // 4th Prefetch ReadAsync (buffers will swap).
3552 for (; kv_iter != kvmap.end() && iter->Valid(); kv_iter++) {
3553 ASSERT_EQ(iter->key(), kv_iter->first);
3554 ASSERT_EQ(iter->value().ToString(), kv_iter->second);
3555
3556 if (iter->user_key() == "00000585") {
3557 break;
3558 }
3559
3560 iter->Next();
3561 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3562 }
3563
3564 {
3565 std::vector<std::tuple<uint64_t, size_t, bool>> buffer_info(2);
3566 prefetch_buffer->TEST_GetBufferOffsetandSize(buffer_info);
3567
3568 // 1st Buffer Verification.
3569 bbt->TEST_GetDataBlockHandle(read_options, kv_iter->first,
3570 block_handle);
3571 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<0>(buffer_info[0]), block_handle.offset());
3572 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[0]), 4096);
3573
3574 // 2nd Buffer Verification.
3575 InternalKey ikey_tmp("00000615", 0, kTypeValue);
3576 bbt->TEST_GetDataBlockHandle(read_options, ikey_tmp.Encode().ToString(),
3577 block_handle);
3578 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<0>(buffer_info[1]), block_handle.offset());
3579 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[1]), 4096);
3580
3581 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getAndResetTickerCount(READAHEAD_TRIMMED),
3582 1);
3583 }
3584
3585 // 5th Prefetch ReadAsync.
3586 for (; kv_iter != kvmap.end() && iter->Valid(); kv_iter++) {
3587 ASSERT_EQ(iter->key(), kv_iter->first);
3588 ASSERT_EQ(iter->value().ToString(), kv_iter->second);
3589
3590 if (iter->user_key() == "00000615") {
3591 break;
3592 }
3593
3594 iter->Next();
3595 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3596 }
3597
3598 {
3599 std::vector<std::tuple<uint64_t, size_t, bool>> buffer_info(2);
3600 prefetch_buffer->TEST_GetBufferOffsetandSize(buffer_info);
3601
3602 // 1st Buffer Verification.
3603 bbt->TEST_GetDataBlockHandle(read_options, kv_iter->first,
3604 block_handle);
3605 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<0>(buffer_info[0]), block_handle.offset());
3606 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[0]), 4096);
3607
3608 // 2nd Buffer Verification.
3609 InternalKey ikey_tmp("00000630", 0, kTypeValue);
3610 bbt->TEST_GetDataBlockHandle(read_options, ikey_tmp.Encode().ToString(),
3611 block_handle);
3612 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<0>(buffer_info[1]), block_handle.offset());
3613 ASSERT_EQ(std::get<1>(buffer_info[1]), 8192);
3614
3615 ASSERT_EQ(options.statistics->getAndResetTickerCount(READAHEAD_TRIMMED),
3616 0);
3617 }
3618 }
3619 }
3620 c.ResetTableReader();
3621}
3622
3623struct HitMissCountingCache : public CacheWrapper {
3624 using CacheWrapper::CacheWrapper;
3625 const char* Name() const override { return "HitMissCountingCache"; }
3626
3627 uint64_t hit_count_ = 0;
3628 uint64_t miss_count_ = 0;
3629
3630 void Reset() {
3631 hit_count_ = 0;
3632 miss_count_ = 0;
3633 }
3634
3635 Handle* Lookup(const Slice& key, const CacheItemHelper* helper,
3636 CreateContext* create_context,
3637 Priority priority = Priority::LOW,
3638 Statistics* stats = nullptr) override {
3639 // ASSUMES no blocking async lookups
3640 Handle* h = target_->Lookup(key, helper, create_context, priority, stats);
3641 if (h) {
3642 hit_count_++;
3643 } else {
3644 miss_count_++;
3645 }
3646 return h;
3647 }
3648
3649 void StartAsyncLookup(AsyncLookupHandle& async_handle) override {
3650 target_->StartAsyncLookup(async_handle);
3651 // If not pending, caller might not call WaitAll, so have to account here.
3652 if (!async_handle.IsPending()) {
3653 if (async_handle.Result()) {
3654 hit_count_++;
3655 } else {
3656 miss_count_++;
3657 }
3658 }
3659 }
3660
3661 void WaitAll(AsyncLookupHandle* async_handles, size_t count) override {
3662 // If !pending, then we already accounted for it in StartAsyncLookup.
3663 // Assume the pending status does not change asynchronously (since
3664 // StartAsyncLookup) and remember which still need accounting.
3665 std::vector<AsyncLookupHandle*> needs_accounting;
3666 for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i) {
3667 if (async_handles[i].IsPending()) {
3668 needs_accounting.push_back(async_handles + i);
3669 }
3670 }
3671 target_->WaitAll(async_handles, count);
3672 for (auto ah : needs_accounting) {
3673 if (ah->Result()) {
3674 hit_count_++;
3675 } else {
3676 miss_count_++;
3677 }
3678 }
3679 }
3680
3681 void VerifyExpectedHitMissCounts(
3682 const std::vector<BlockCacheTraceRecord>& expected_records) {
3683 uint64_t expected_hits = 0;
3684 uint64_t expected_misses = 0;
3685 for (const auto& r : expected_records) {
3686 if (r.is_cache_hit) {
3687 expected_hits++;
3688 } else {
3689 expected_misses++;
3690 }
3691 }
3692 EXPECT_EQ(expected_hits, hit_count_);
3693 EXPECT_EQ(expected_misses, miss_count_);
3694 Reset();
3695 }
3696};
3697
3698TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, TracingMultiGetTest) {
3699 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator());
3700 Options options;
3701 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
3702 options.create_if_missing = true;
3703 auto cache =
3704 std::make_shared<HitMissCountingCache>(NewLRUCache(1024 * 1024, 0));
3705 table_options.block_cache = cache;
3706 table_options.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = true;
3707 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(10));
3708 // Put auto_add_key1 and auto_add_key2 in the same data block
3709 table_options.block_size = kDummyValue.size() * 2 + 100;
3710 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
3711 SetupTracingTest(&c);
3712 std::vector<std::string> keys;
3713 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
3714 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
3715 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
3716 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
3717 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
3718
3719 std::vector<BlockCacheTraceRecord> expected_records;
3720
3721 for (bool first_pass : {true, false}) {
3722 uint64_t get_id_offset = first_pass ? 2 : 5;
3723 ReadOptions ro;
3724 std::array<Slice, 2> ukeys{{auto_add_key1, auto_add_key2}};
3725 std::array<PinnableSlice, 2> values;
3726 std::vector<GetContext> get_contexts;
3727 get_contexts.emplace_back(
3728 options.comparator, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, GetContext::kNotFound,
3729 ukeys[0], values.data(), nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr,
3730 nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, get_id_offset);
3731 get_contexts.emplace_back(
3732 options.comparator, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, GetContext::kNotFound,
3733 ukeys[1], &values[1], nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, nullptr,
3734 nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, get_id_offset + 1);
3735 std::array<std::string, 2> encoded_keys;
3736 encoded_keys[0] = InternalKey(ukeys[0], 0, kTypeValue).Encode().ToString();
3737 encoded_keys[1] = InternalKey(ukeys[1], 0, kTypeValue).Encode().ToString();
3738 std::array<Status, 2> statuses;
3739 autovector<KeyContext, MultiGetContext::MAX_BATCH_SIZE> key_context;
3740 key_context.emplace_back(/*ColumnFamilyHandle omitted*/ nullptr, ukeys[0],
3741 values.data(),
3742 /*PinnableWideColumns omitted*/ nullptr,
3743 /*timestamp omitted*/ nullptr, statuses.data());
3744 key_context[0].ukey_without_ts = ukeys[0];
3745 key_context[0].ikey = encoded_keys[0];
3746 key_context[0].get_context = get_contexts.data();
3747 key_context.emplace_back(/*ColumnFamilyHandle omitted*/ nullptr, ukeys[1],
3748 &values[1],
3749 /*PinnableWideColumns omitted*/ nullptr,
3750 /*timestamp omitted*/ nullptr, &statuses[1]);
3751 key_context[1].ukey_without_ts = ukeys[1];
3752 key_context[1].ikey = encoded_keys[1];
3753 key_context[1].get_context = &get_contexts[1];
3754 autovector<KeyContext*, MultiGetContext::MAX_BATCH_SIZE> sorted_keys;
3755 sorted_keys.push_back(&key_context[0]);
3756 sorted_keys.push_back(&key_context[1]);
3757 MultiGetContext m_context(
3758 &sorted_keys, 0, sorted_keys.size(), /*SequenceNumber*/ 42, ro,
3759 options.env->GetFileSystem().get(), options.statistics.get());
3760 MultiGetRange range = m_context.GetMultiGetRange();
3761
3762 get_perf_context()->Reset();
3763 c.GetTableReader()->MultiGet(ro, &range, /*prefix_extractor*/ nullptr);
3764
3765 // Verify read op result
3766 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= 1; i++) {
3767 ASSERT_OK(statuses[i]);
3768 ASSERT_EQ(get_contexts[i].State(), GetContext::kFound);
3769 ASSERT_EQ(values[i].ToString(), kDummyValue);
3770 }
3771
3772 // Verify traces.
3773 BlockCacheTraceRecord record;
3774 if (first_pass) {
3775 // The first two records should be prefetching index and filter blocks.
3776 record.get_id = 0;
3777 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceIndexBlock;
3778 record.caller = TableReaderCaller::kPrefetch;
3779 record.is_cache_hit = false;
3780 record.no_insert = false;
3781 expected_records.push_back(record);
3782 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceFilterBlock;
3783 expected_records.push_back(record);
3784 }
3785 // Then we should have three records for one index, one filter, and one
3786 // data block access. (The two keys share a data block.)
3787 record.get_id = get_id_offset;
3788 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceFilterBlock;
3789 record.caller = TableReaderCaller::kUserMultiGet;
3790 record.get_from_user_specified_snapshot = false;
3791 record.referenced_key = encoded_keys[0];
3792 record.referenced_key_exist_in_block = true;
3793 record.is_cache_hit = true;
3794 expected_records.push_back(record);
3795 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceIndexBlock;
3796 expected_records.push_back(record);
3797 record.is_cache_hit = !first_pass;
3798 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceDataBlock;
3799 expected_records.push_back(record);
3800 }
3801 VerifyBlockAccessTrace(&c, expected_records);
3802 cache->VerifyExpectedHitMissCounts(expected_records);
3803 c.ResetTableReader();
3804}

3850TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, TracingIterator) {
3851 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator());
3852 Options options;
3853 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
3854 options.create_if_missing = true;
3855 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(1024 * 1024, 0);
3856 table_options.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = true;
3857 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(10, true));
3858 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
3859 SetupTracingTest(&c);
3860 std::vector<std::string> keys;
3861 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
3862 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
3863 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
3864 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
3865 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
3866
3867 for (uint32_t i = 1; i <= 2; i++) {
3868 ReadOptions read_options;
3869 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter(c.GetTableReader()->NewIterator(
3870 read_options, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), /*arena=*/nullptr,
3871 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUserIterator));
3872 iter->SeekToFirst();
3873 while (iter->Valid()) {
3874 iter->key();
3875 iter->value();
3876 iter->Next();
3877 }
3878 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
3879 iter.reset();
3880 }
3881
3882 // Verify traces.
3883 std::vector<BlockCacheTraceRecord> expected_records;
3884 // The first two records should be prefetching index and filter blocks.
3885 BlockCacheTraceRecord record;
3886 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceIndexBlock;
3887 record.caller = TableReaderCaller::kPrefetch;
3888 record.is_cache_hit = false;
3889 record.no_insert = false;
3890 expected_records.push_back(record);
3891 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceFilterBlock;
3892 expected_records.push_back(record);
3893 // Then we should have three records for index and two data block access.
3894 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceIndexBlock;
3895 record.caller = TableReaderCaller::kUserIterator;
3896 record.is_cache_hit = true;
3897 expected_records.push_back(record);
3898 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceDataBlock;
3899 record.is_cache_hit = false;
3900 expected_records.push_back(record);
3901 expected_records.push_back(record);
3902 // When we iterate this file for the second time, we should observe all
3903 // cache hits.
3904 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceIndexBlock;
3905 record.is_cache_hit = true;
3906 expected_records.push_back(record);
3907 record.block_type = TraceType::kBlockTraceDataBlock;
3908 expected_records.push_back(record);
3909 expected_records.push_back(record);
3910 VerifyBlockAccessTrace(&c, expected_records);
3911 c.ResetTableReader();
3912}

3914// A simple tool that takes the snapshot of block cache statistics.
3915class BlockCachePropertiesSnapshot {
3916 public:
3917 explicit BlockCachePropertiesSnapshot(Statistics* statistics) {
3918 block_cache_miss = statistics->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_MISS);
3919 block_cache_hit = statistics->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_HIT);
3920 index_block_cache_miss = statistics->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_MISS);
3921 index_block_cache_hit = statistics->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_INDEX_HIT);
3922 data_block_cache_miss = statistics->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_MISS);
3923 data_block_cache_hit = statistics->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_DATA_HIT);
3924 filter_block_cache_miss =
3925 statistics->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_MISS);
3926 filter_block_cache_hit = statistics->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_FILTER_HIT);
3927 block_cache_bytes_read = statistics->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_BYTES_READ);
3928 block_cache_bytes_write =
3929 statistics->getTickerCount(BLOCK_CACHE_BYTES_WRITE);
3930 }
3931
3932 void AssertIndexBlockStat(int64_t expected_index_block_cache_miss,
3933 int64_t expected_index_block_cache_hit) {
3934 ASSERT_EQ(expected_index_block_cache_miss, index_block_cache_miss);
3935 ASSERT_EQ(expected_index_block_cache_hit, index_block_cache_hit);
3936 }
3937
3938 void AssertFilterBlockStat(int64_t expected_filter_block_cache_miss,
3939 int64_t expected_filter_block_cache_hit) {
3940 ASSERT_EQ(expected_filter_block_cache_miss, filter_block_cache_miss);
3941 ASSERT_EQ(expected_filter_block_cache_hit, filter_block_cache_hit);
3942 }
3943
3944 // Check if the fetched props matches the expected ones.
3945 // TODO(kailiu) Use this only when you disabled filter policy!
3946 void AssertEqual(int64_t expected_index_block_cache_miss,
3947 int64_t expected_index_block_cache_hit,
3948 int64_t expected_data_block_cache_miss,
3949 int64_t expected_data_block_cache_hit) const {
3950 ASSERT_EQ(expected_index_block_cache_miss, index_block_cache_miss);
3951 ASSERT_EQ(expected_index_block_cache_hit, index_block_cache_hit);
3952 ASSERT_EQ(expected_data_block_cache_miss, data_block_cache_miss);
3953 ASSERT_EQ(expected_data_block_cache_hit, data_block_cache_hit);
3954 ASSERT_EQ(expected_index_block_cache_miss + expected_data_block_cache_miss,
3955 block_cache_miss);
3956 ASSERT_EQ(expected_index_block_cache_hit + expected_data_block_cache_hit,
3957 block_cache_hit);
3958 }
3959
3960 int64_t GetCacheBytesRead() { return block_cache_bytes_read; }
3961
3962 int64_t GetCacheBytesWrite() { return block_cache_bytes_write; }
3963
3964 private:
3965 int64_t block_cache_miss = 0;
3966 int64_t block_cache_hit = 0;
3967 int64_t index_block_cache_miss = 0;
3968 int64_t index_block_cache_hit = 0;
3969 int64_t data_block_cache_miss = 0;
3970 int64_t data_block_cache_hit = 0;
3971 int64_t filter_block_cache_miss = 0;
3972 int64_t filter_block_cache_hit = 0;
3973 int64_t block_cache_bytes_read = 0;
3974 int64_t block_cache_bytes_write = 0;
3975};
3976
3977// Make sure, by default, index/filter blocks were pre-loaded (meaning we
3978// won't use block cache to store them).
3979TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, BlockCacheDisabledTest) {
3980 Options options;
3981 options.create_if_missing = true;
3982 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
3983 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
3984 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(1024, 4);
3985 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(10));
3986 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
3987 std::vector<std::string> keys;
3988 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
3989
3990 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
3991 c.Add("key", "value");
3992 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
3993 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
3994 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
3995 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
3996
3997 // preloading filter/index blocks is enabled.
3998 auto reader = dynamic_cast<BlockBasedTable*>(c.GetTableReader());
3999 ASSERT_FALSE(reader->TEST_FilterBlockInCache());
4000 ASSERT_FALSE(reader->TEST_IndexBlockInCache());
4001
4002 {
4003 // nothing happens in the beginning
4004 BlockCachePropertiesSnapshot props(options.statistics.get());
4005 props.AssertIndexBlockStat(0, 0);
4006 props.AssertFilterBlockStat(0, 0);
4007 }
4008
4009 {
4010 GetContext get_context(options.comparator, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr,
4011 GetContext::kNotFound, Slice(), nullptr, nullptr,
4012 nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, nullptr);
4013 // a hack that just to trigger BlockBasedTable::GetFilter.
4014 ASSERT_OK(reader->Get(ReadOptions(), "non-exist-key", &get_context,
4015 moptions.prefix_extractor.get()));
4016 BlockCachePropertiesSnapshot props(options.statistics.get());
4017 props.AssertIndexBlockStat(0, 0);
4018 props.AssertFilterBlockStat(0, 0);
4019 }
4020}

4022// Due to the difficulities of the intersaction between statistics, this test
4023// only tests the case when "index block is put to block cache"
4024TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, FilterBlockInBlockCache) {
4025 // -- Table construction
4026 Options options;
4027 options.create_if_missing = true;
4028 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
4029
4030 // Enable the cache for index/filter blocks
4031 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
4032 LRUCacheOptions co;
4033 co.capacity = 2048;
4034 co.num_shard_bits = 2;
4035 co.metadata_charge_policy = kDontChargeCacheMetadata;
4036 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(co);
4037 table_options.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = true;
4038 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
4039 std::vector<std::string> keys;
4040 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
4041
4042 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
4043 c.Add("key", "value");
4044 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
4045 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
4046 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
4047 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
4048 // preloading filter/index blocks is prohibited.
4049 auto* reader = dynamic_cast<BlockBasedTable*>(c.GetTableReader());
4050 ASSERT_FALSE(reader->TEST_FilterBlockInCache());
4051 ASSERT_TRUE(reader->TEST_IndexBlockInCache());
4052
4053 // -- PART 1: Open with regular block cache.
4054 // Since block_cache is disabled, no cache activities will be involved.
4055 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter;
4056
4057 int64_t last_cache_bytes_read = 0;
4058 // At first, no block will be accessed.
4059 {
4060 BlockCachePropertiesSnapshot props(options.statistics.get());
4061 // index will be added to block cache.
4062 props.AssertEqual(1, // index block miss
4063 0, 0, 0);
4064 ASSERT_EQ(props.GetCacheBytesRead(), 0);
4065 ASSERT_EQ(props.GetCacheBytesWrite(),
4066 static_cast<int64_t>(table_options.block_cache->GetUsage()));
4067 last_cache_bytes_read = props.GetCacheBytesRead();
4068 }
4069
4070 // Only index block will be accessed
4071 {
4072 iter.reset(c.NewIterator(moptions.prefix_extractor.get()));
4073 BlockCachePropertiesSnapshot props(options.statistics.get());
4074 // NOTE: to help better highlight the "detla" of each ticker, I use
4075 // <last_value> + <added_value> to indicate the increment of changed
4076 // value; other numbers remain the same.
4077 props.AssertEqual(1, 0 + 1, // index block hit
4078 0, 0);
4079 // Cache hit, bytes read from cache should increase
4080 ASSERT_GT(props.GetCacheBytesRead(), last_cache_bytes_read);
4081 ASSERT_EQ(props.GetCacheBytesWrite(),
4082 static_cast<int64_t>(table_options.block_cache->GetUsage()));
4083 last_cache_bytes_read = props.GetCacheBytesRead();
4084 }
4085
4086 // Only data block will be accessed
4087 {
4088 iter->SeekToFirst();
4089 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
4090 BlockCachePropertiesSnapshot props(options.statistics.get());
4091 props.AssertEqual(1, 1, 0 + 1, // data block miss
4092 0);
4093 // Cache miss, Bytes read from cache should not change
4094 ASSERT_EQ(props.GetCacheBytesRead(), last_cache_bytes_read);
4095 ASSERT_EQ(props.GetCacheBytesWrite(),
4096 static_cast<int64_t>(table_options.block_cache->GetUsage()));
4097 last_cache_bytes_read = props.GetCacheBytesRead();
4098 }
4099
4100 // Data block will be in cache
4101 {
4102 iter.reset(c.NewIterator(moptions.prefix_extractor.get()));
4103 iter->SeekToFirst();
4104 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
4105 BlockCachePropertiesSnapshot props(options.statistics.get());
4106 props.AssertEqual(1, 1 + 1, /* index block hit */
4107 1, 0 + 1 /* data block hit */);
4108 // Cache hit, bytes read from cache should increase
4109 ASSERT_GT(props.GetCacheBytesRead(), last_cache_bytes_read);
4110 ASSERT_EQ(props.GetCacheBytesWrite(),
4111 static_cast<int64_t>(table_options.block_cache->GetUsage()));
4112 }
4113 // release the iterator so that the block cache can reset correctly.
4114 iter.reset();
4115
4116 c.ResetTableReader();
4117
4118 // -- PART 2: Open with very small block cache
4119 // In this test, no block will ever get hit since the block cache is
4120 // too small to fit even one entry.
4121 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(1, 4);
4122 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
4123 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
4124 const ImmutableOptions ioptions2(options);
4125 const MutableCFOptions moptions2(options);
4126 ASSERT_OK(c.Reopen(ioptions2, moptions2));
4127 {
4128 BlockCachePropertiesSnapshot props(options.statistics.get());
4129 props.AssertEqual(1, // index block miss
4130 0, 0, 0);
4131 // Cache miss, Bytes read from cache should not change
4132 ASSERT_EQ(props.GetCacheBytesRead(), 0);
4133 }
4134
4135 {
4136 // Both index and data block get accessed.
4137 // It first cache index block then data block. But since the cache size
4138 // is only 1, index block will be purged after data block is inserted.
4139 iter.reset(c.NewIterator(moptions2.prefix_extractor.get()));
4140 BlockCachePropertiesSnapshot props(options.statistics.get());
4141 props.AssertEqual(1 + 1, // index block miss
4142 0, 0, // data block miss
4143 0);
4144 // Cache hit, bytes read from cache should increase
4145 ASSERT_EQ(props.GetCacheBytesRead(), 0);
4146 }
4147
4148 {
4149 // SeekToFirst() accesses data block. With similar reason, we expect data
4150 // block's cache miss.
4151 iter->SeekToFirst();
4152 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
4153 BlockCachePropertiesSnapshot props(options.statistics.get());
4154 props.AssertEqual(2, 0, 0 + 1, // data block miss
4155 0);
4156 // Cache miss, Bytes read from cache should not change
4157 ASSERT_EQ(props.GetCacheBytesRead(), 0);
4158 }
4159 iter.reset();
4160 c.ResetTableReader();
4161
4162 // -- PART 3: Open table with bloom filter enabled but not in SST file
4163 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(4096, 4);
4164 table_options.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = false;
4165 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
4166
4167 TableConstructor c3(BytewiseComparator());
4168 std::string user_key = "k01";
4169 InternalKey internal_key(user_key, 0, kTypeValue);
4170 c3.Add(internal_key.Encode().ToString(), "hello");
4171 ImmutableOptions ioptions3(options);
4172 MutableCFOptions moptions3(options);
4173 // Generate table without filter policy
4174 c3.Finish(options, ioptions3, moptions3, table_options,
4175 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
4176 c3.ResetTableReader();
4177
4178 // Open table with filter policy
4179 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(1));
4180 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
4181 options.statistics = CreateDBStatistics();
4182 ImmutableOptions ioptions4(options);
4183 MutableCFOptions moptions4(options);
4184 ASSERT_OK(c3.Reopen(ioptions4, moptions4));
4185 reader = dynamic_cast<BlockBasedTable*>(c3.GetTableReader());
4186 ASSERT_FALSE(reader->TEST_FilterBlockInCache());
4187 PinnableSlice value;
4188 GetContext get_context(options.comparator, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr,
4189 GetContext::kNotFound, user_key, &value, nullptr,
4190 nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, nullptr);
4191 ASSERT_OK(reader->Get(ReadOptions(), internal_key.Encode(), &get_context,
4192 moptions4.prefix_extractor.get()));
4193 ASSERT_STREQ(value.data(), "hello");
4194 BlockCachePropertiesSnapshot props(options.statistics.get());
4195 props.AssertFilterBlockStat(0, 0);
4196 c3.ResetTableReader();
4197}

4225 // 0

4227 ValidateBlockSizeDeviation(-1, 0);

4229 ValidateBlockSizeDeviation(1, 1);

4233 ValidateBlockSizeDeviation(1000, 0);

4238 ValidateBlockRestartInterval(0, 1);
4239 ValidateBlockRestartInterval(1, 1);

4244TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, BlockReadCountTest) {
4245 // bloom_filter_type = 1 -- full filter using use_block_based_builder=false
4246 // bloom_filter_type = 2 -- full filter using use_block_based_builder=true
4247 // because of API change to hide block-based filter
4248 for (int bloom_filter_type = 1; bloom_filter_type <= 2; ++bloom_filter_type) {
4249 for (int index_and_filter_in_cache = 0; index_and_filter_in_cache < 2;
4250 ++index_and_filter_in_cache) {
4251 Options options;
4252 options.create_if_missing = true;
4253
4254 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
4255 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(1, 0);
4256 table_options.cache_index_and_filter_blocks = index_and_filter_in_cache;
4257 table_options.filter_policy.reset(
4258 NewBloomFilterPolicy(10, bloom_filter_type == 2));
4259 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
4260 std::vector<std::string> keys;
4261 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
4262
4263 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator());
4264 std::string user_key = "k04";
4265 InternalKey internal_key(user_key, 0, kTypeValue);
4266 std::string encoded_key = internal_key.Encode().ToString();
4267 c.Add(encoded_key, "hello");
4268 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
4269 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
4270 // Generate table with filter policy
4271 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
4272 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
4273 auto reader = c.GetTableReader();
4274 PinnableSlice value;
4275 {
4276 GetContext get_context(options.comparator, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr,
4277 GetContext::kNotFound, user_key, &value, nullptr,
4278 nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, nullptr);
4279 get_perf_context()->Reset();
4280 ASSERT_OK(reader->Get(ReadOptions(), encoded_key, &get_context,
4281 moptions.prefix_extractor.get()));
4282 if (index_and_filter_in_cache) {
4283 // data, index and filter block
4284 ASSERT_EQ(get_perf_context()->block_read_count, 3);
4285 ASSERT_EQ(get_perf_context()->index_block_read_count, 1);
4286 ASSERT_EQ(get_perf_context()->filter_block_read_count, 1);
4287 } else {
4288 // just the data block
4289 ASSERT_EQ(get_perf_context()->block_read_count, 1);
4290 }
4291 ASSERT_EQ(get_context.State(), GetContext::kFound);
4292 ASSERT_STREQ(value.data(), "hello");
4293 }
4294
4295 // Get non-existing key
4296 user_key = "does-not-exist";
4297 internal_key = InternalKey(user_key, 0, kTypeValue);
4298 encoded_key = internal_key.Encode().ToString();
4299
4300 value.Reset();
4301 {
4302 GetContext get_context(options.comparator, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr,
4303 GetContext::kNotFound, user_key, &value, nullptr,
4304 nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, nullptr);
4305 get_perf_context()->Reset();
4306 ASSERT_OK(reader->Get(ReadOptions(), encoded_key, &get_context,
4307 moptions.prefix_extractor.get()));
4308 ASSERT_EQ(get_context.State(), GetContext::kNotFound);
4309 }
4310
4311 if (index_and_filter_in_cache) {
4312 if (bloom_filter_type == 0) {
4313 // with block-based, we read index and then the filter
4314 ASSERT_EQ(get_perf_context()->block_read_count, 2);
4315 ASSERT_EQ(get_perf_context()->index_block_read_count, 1);
4316 ASSERT_EQ(get_perf_context()->filter_block_read_count, 1);
4317 } else {
4318 // with full-filter, we read filter first and then we stop
4319 ASSERT_EQ(get_perf_context()->block_read_count, 1);
4320 ASSERT_EQ(get_perf_context()->filter_block_read_count, 1);
4321 }
4322 } else {
4323 // filter is already in memory and it figures out that the key doesn't
4324 // exist
4325 ASSERT_EQ(get_perf_context()->block_read_count, 0);
4326 }
4327 }
4328 }
4329}

4331TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, BlockCacheLeak) {
4332 // Check that when we reopen a table we don't lose access to blocks already
4333 // in the cache. This test checks whether the Table actually makes use of
4334 // the unique ID from the file.
4335
4336 Options opt;
4337 std::unique_ptr<InternalKeyComparator> ikc;
4338 ikc.reset(new test::PlainInternalKeyComparator(opt.comparator));
4339 opt.compression = kNoCompression;
4340 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
4341 table_options.block_size = 1024;
4342 // big enough so we don't ever lose cached values.
4343 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(16 * 1024 * 1024, 4);
4344 opt.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
4345
4346 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
4347 c.Add("k01", "hello");
4348 c.Add("k02", "hello2");
4349 c.Add("k03", std::string(10000, 'x'));
4350 c.Add("k04", std::string(200000, 'x'));
4351 c.Add("k05", std::string(300000, 'x'));
4352 c.Add("k06", "hello3");
4353 c.Add("k07", std::string(100000, 'x'));
4354 std::vector<std::string> keys;
4355 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
4356 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(opt);
4357 const MutableCFOptions moptions(opt);
4358 c.Finish(opt, ioptions, moptions, table_options, *ikc, &keys, &kvmap);
4359
4360 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter(
4361 c.NewIterator(moptions.prefix_extractor.get()));
4362 iter->SeekToFirst();
4363 while (iter->Valid()) {
4364 iter->key();
4365 iter->value();
4366 iter->Next();
4367 }
4368 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
4369 iter.reset();
4370
4371 const ImmutableOptions ioptions1(opt);
4372 const MutableCFOptions moptions1(opt);
4373 ASSERT_OK(c.Reopen(ioptions1, moptions1));
4374 auto table_reader = dynamic_cast<BlockBasedTable*>(c.GetTableReader());
4375 for (const std::string& key : keys) {
4376 InternalKey ikey(key, kMaxSequenceNumber, kTypeValue);
4377 ASSERT_TRUE(table_reader->TEST_KeyInCache(ReadOptions(), ikey.Encode()));
4378 }
4379 c.ResetTableReader();
4380
4381 // rerun with different block cache
4382 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(16 * 1024 * 1024, 4);
4383 opt.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
4384 const ImmutableOptions ioptions2(opt);
4385 const MutableCFOptions moptions2(opt);
4386 ASSERT_OK(c.Reopen(ioptions2, moptions2));
4387 table_reader = dynamic_cast<BlockBasedTable*>(c.GetTableReader());
4388 for (const std::string& key : keys) {
4389 InternalKey ikey(key, kMaxSequenceNumber, kTypeValue);
4390 ASSERT_TRUE(!table_reader->TEST_KeyInCache(ReadOptions(), ikey.Encode()));
4391 }
4392 c.ResetTableReader();
4393}

4395TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, MemoryAllocator) {
4396 auto default_memory_allocator = std::make_shared<DefaultMemoryAllocator>();
4397 auto custom_memory_allocator =
4398 std::make_shared<CountedMemoryAllocator>(default_memory_allocator);
4399 {
4400 Options opt;
4401 std::unique_ptr<InternalKeyComparator> ikc;
4402 ikc.reset(new test::PlainInternalKeyComparator(opt.comparator));
4403 opt.compression = kNoCompression;
4404 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
4405 table_options.block_size = 1024;
4406 LRUCacheOptions lruOptions;
4407 lruOptions.memory_allocator = custom_memory_allocator;
4408 lruOptions.capacity = 16 * 1024 * 1024;
4409 lruOptions.num_shard_bits = 4;
4410 table_options.block_cache = NewLRUCache(std::move(lruOptions));
4411 opt.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
4412
4413 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(),
4414 true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
4415 c.Add("k01", "hello");
4416 c.Add("k02", "hello2");
4417 c.Add("k03", std::string(10000, 'x'));
4418 c.Add("k04", std::string(200000, 'x'));
4419 c.Add("k05", std::string(300000, 'x'));
4420 c.Add("k06", "hello3");
4421 c.Add("k07", std::string(100000, 'x'));
4422 std::vector<std::string> keys;
4423 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
4424 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(opt);
4425 const MutableCFOptions moptions(opt);
4426 c.Finish(opt, ioptions, moptions, table_options, *ikc, &keys, &kvmap);
4427
4428 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter(
4429 c.NewIterator(moptions.prefix_extractor.get()));
4430 iter->SeekToFirst();
4431 while (iter->Valid()) {
4432 iter->key();
4433 iter->value();
4434 iter->Next();
4435 }
4436 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
4437 }
4438
4439 // out of scope, block cache should have been deleted, all allocations
4440 // deallocated
4441 EXPECT_EQ(custom_memory_allocator->GetNumAllocations(),
4442 custom_memory_allocator->GetNumDeallocations());
4443 // make sure that allocations actually happened through the cache allocator
4444 EXPECT_GT(custom_memory_allocator->GetNumAllocations(), 0);
4445}

4452 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
4453 std::unique_ptr<InternalKeyComparator> comparator(

4478TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, Crc32cFileChecksum) {
4479 FileChecksumGenCrc32cFactory* file_checksum_gen_factory =
4480 new FileChecksumGenCrc32cFactory();
4481 Options options;
4482 options.file_checksum_gen_factory.reset(file_checksum_gen_factory);
4483 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
4484 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
4485 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
4486 std::unique_ptr<InternalKeyComparator> comparator(
4487 new InternalKeyComparator(BytewiseComparator()));
4488 int level = 0;
4489 InternalTblPropCollFactories internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories;
4490 std::string column_family_name;
4491
4492 FileChecksumGenContext gen_context;
4493 gen_context.file_name = "db/tmp";
4494 std::unique_ptr<FileChecksumGenerator> checksum_crc32c_gen1 =
4495 options.file_checksum_gen_factory->CreateFileChecksumGenerator(
4496 gen_context);
4497 FileChecksumTestHelper f(true);
4498 f.CreateWritableFile();
4499 f.SetFileChecksumGenerator(checksum_crc32c_gen1.release());
4500 std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder> builder;
4501 const ReadOptions read_options;
4502 const WriteOptions write_options;
4503 builder.reset(moptions.table_factory->NewTableBuilder(
4504 TableBuilderOptions(ioptions, moptions, read_options, write_options,
4505 *comparator, &internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories,
4506 options.compression, options.compression_opts,
4507 kUnknownColumnFamily, column_family_name, level,
4508 kUnknownNewestKeyTime),
4509 f.GetFileWriter()));
4510 ASSERT_OK(f.ResetTableBuilder(std::move(builder)));
4511 f.AddKVtoKVMap(1000);
4512 ASSERT_OK(f.WriteKVAndFlushTable());
4513 ASSERT_STREQ(f.GetFileChecksumFuncName(), "FileChecksumCrc32c");
4514
4515 std::unique_ptr<FileChecksumGenerator> checksum_crc32c_gen2 =
4516 options.file_checksum_gen_factory->CreateFileChecksumGenerator(
4517 gen_context);
4518 std::string checksum;
4519 ASSERT_OK(f.CalculateFileChecksum(checksum_crc32c_gen2.get(), &checksum));
4520 ASSERT_STREQ(f.GetFileChecksum().c_str(), checksum.c_str());
4521
4522 // Unit test the generator itself for schema stability
4523 std::unique_ptr<FileChecksumGenerator> checksum_crc32c_gen3 =
4524 options.file_checksum_gen_factory->CreateFileChecksumGenerator(
4525 gen_context);
4526 const char data[] = "here is some data";
4527 checksum_crc32c_gen3->Update(data, sizeof(data));
4528 checksum_crc32c_gen3->Finalize();
4529 checksum = checksum_crc32c_gen3->GetChecksum();
4530 ASSERT_STREQ(checksum.c_str(), "\345\245\277\110");
4531}

4533TEST_F(PlainTableTest, BasicPlainTableProperties) {
4534 PlainTableOptions plain_table_options;
4535 plain_table_options.user_key_len = 8;
4536 plain_table_options.bloom_bits_per_key = 8;
4537 plain_table_options.hash_table_ratio = 0;
4538
4539 PlainTableFactory factory(plain_table_options);
4540 std::unique_ptr<FSWritableFile> sink(new test::StringSink());
4541 std::unique_ptr<WritableFileWriter> file_writer(new WritableFileWriter(
4542 std::move(sink), "" /* don't care */, FileOptions()));
4543 Options options;
4544 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
4545 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
4546 InternalKeyComparator ikc(options.comparator);
4547 InternalTblPropCollFactories internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories;
4548 std::string column_family_name;
4549 int unknown_level = -1;
4550 const ReadOptions read_options;
4551 const WriteOptions write_options;
4552 std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder> builder(factory.NewTableBuilder(
4553 TableBuilderOptions(ioptions, moptions, read_options, write_options, ikc,
4554 &internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories, kNoCompression,
4555 CompressionOptions(), kUnknownColumnFamily,
4556 column_family_name, unknown_level,
4557 kUnknownNewestKeyTime),
4558 file_writer.get()));
4559
4560 for (char c = 'a'; c <= 'z'; ++c) {
4561 std::string key(8, c);
4562 key.append("\1 "); // PlainTable expects internal key structure
4563 std::string value(28, c + 42);
4564 builder->Add(key, value);
4565 }
4566 ASSERT_OK(builder->Finish());
4567 ASSERT_OK(file_writer->Flush(IOOptions()));
4568
4569 test::StringSink* ss =
4570 static_cast<test::StringSink*>(file_writer->writable_file());
4571 std::unique_ptr<FSRandomAccessFile> source(
4572 new test::StringSource(ss->contents(), 72242, true));
4573 std::unique_ptr<RandomAccessFileReader> file_reader(
4574 new RandomAccessFileReader(std::move(source), "test"));
4575
4576 std::unique_ptr<TableProperties> props;
4577 auto s = ReadTableProperties(file_reader.get(), ss->contents().size(),
4578 kPlainTableMagicNumber, ioptions, read_options,
4579 &props);
4580 ASSERT_OK(s);
4581
4582 ASSERT_EQ(0ul, props->index_size);
4583 ASSERT_EQ(0ul, props->filter_size);
4584 ASSERT_EQ(16ul * 26, props->raw_key_size);
4585 ASSERT_EQ(28ul * 26, props->raw_value_size);
4586 ASSERT_EQ(26ul, props->num_entries);
4587 ASSERT_EQ(1ul, props->num_data_blocks);
4588}

4622TEST_F(PlainTableTest, Crc32cFileChecksum) {
4623 PlainTableOptions plain_table_options;
4624 plain_table_options.user_key_len = 20;
4625 plain_table_options.bloom_bits_per_key = 8;
4626 plain_table_options.hash_table_ratio = 0;

4628
4629 FileChecksumGenCrc32cFactory* file_checksum_gen_factory =
4630 new FileChecksumGenCrc32cFactory();
4631 Options options;
4632 options.file_checksum_gen_factory.reset(file_checksum_gen_factory);
4633 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
4634 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
4635 InternalKeyComparator ikc(options.comparator);
4636 InternalTblPropCollFactories internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories;
4637 std::string column_family_name;
4638 int unknown_level = -1;
4639
4640 FileChecksumGenContext gen_context;
4641 gen_context.file_name = "db/tmp";
4642 std::unique_ptr<FileChecksumGenerator> checksum_crc32c_gen1 =
4643 options.file_checksum_gen_factory->CreateFileChecksumGenerator(
4644 gen_context);
4645 FileChecksumTestHelper f(true);
4646 f.CreateWritableFile();
4647 f.SetFileChecksumGenerator(checksum_crc32c_gen1.release());
4648 const ReadOptions read_options;
4649 const WriteOptions write_options;
4650 std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder> builder(factory.NewTableBuilder(
4651 TableBuilderOptions(ioptions, moptions, read_options, write_options, ikc,
4652 &internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories, kNoCompression,
4653 CompressionOptions(), kUnknownColumnFamily,
4654 column_family_name, unknown_level,
4655 kUnknownNewestKeyTime),
4656 f.GetFileWriter()));
4657 ASSERT_OK(f.ResetTableBuilder(std::move(builder)));
4658 f.AddKVtoKVMap(1000);
4659 ASSERT_OK(f.WriteKVAndFlushTable());
4660 ASSERT_STREQ(f.GetFileChecksumFuncName(), "FileChecksumCrc32c");
4661
4662 std::unique_ptr<FileChecksumGenerator> checksum_crc32c_gen2 =
4663 options.file_checksum_gen_factory->CreateFileChecksumGenerator(
4664 gen_context);
4665 std::string checksum;
4666 ASSERT_OK(f.CalculateFileChecksum(checksum_crc32c_gen2.get(), &checksum));
4667 EXPECT_STREQ(f.GetFileChecksum().c_str(), checksum.c_str());
4668}
