4670TEST_F(GeneralTableTest, ApproximateOffsetOfPlain) {
4671 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
4672 c.Add("k01", "hello");
4673 c.Add("k02", "hello2");
4674 c.Add("k03", std::string(10000, 'x'));
4675 c.Add("k04", std::string(200000, 'x'));
4676 c.Add("k05", std::string(300000, 'x'));
4677 c.Add("k06", "hello3");
4678 c.Add("k07", std::string(100000, 'x'));
4679 std::vector<std::string> keys;
4680 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
4681 Options options;
4682 options.db_host_id = "";
4683 test::PlainInternalKeyComparator internal_comparator(options.comparator);
4684 options.compression = kNoCompression;
4685 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
4686 table_options.block_size = 1024;
4687 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
4688 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
4689 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options, internal_comparator,
4690 &keys, &kvmap);
4691
4692 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("abc"), 0, 0));
4693 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k01"), 0, 0));
4694 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k01a"), 0, 0));
4695 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k02"), 0, 0));
4696 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k03"), 0, 0));
4697 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k04"), 10000, 11000));
4698 // k04 and k05 will be in two consecutive blocks, the index is
4699 // an arbitrary slice between k04 and k05, either before or after k04a
4700 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k04a"), 10000, 211000));
4701 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k05"), 210000, 211000));
4702 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k06"), 510000, 511000));
4703 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k07"), 510000, 511000));
4704 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("xyz"), 610000, 612000));
4705 c.ResetTableReader();
4706}

4708static void DoCompressionTest(CompressionType comp) {
4709 SCOPED_TRACE("CompressionType = " + CompressionTypeToString(comp));
4710 Random rnd(301);
4711 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
4712 std::string tmp;
4713 c.Add("k01", "hello");
4714 c.Add("k02", test::CompressibleString(&rnd, 0.25, 10000, &tmp));
4715 c.Add("k03", "hello3");
4716 c.Add("k04", test::CompressibleString(&rnd, 0.25, 10000, &tmp));
4717 std::vector<std::string> keys;
4718 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
4719 Options options;
4720 test::PlainInternalKeyComparator ikc(options.comparator);
4721 options.compression = comp;
4722 options.db_host_id = "";
4723 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
4724 table_options.block_size = 1024;
4725 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
4726 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
4727 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
4728 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options, ikc, &keys, &kvmap);
4729
4730 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("abc"), 0, 0));
4731 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k01"), 0, 0));
4732 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k02"), 0, 0));
4733 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k03"), 2000, 3555));
4734 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("k04"), 2000, 3555));
4735 ASSERT_TRUE(Between(c.ApproximateOffsetOf("xyz"), 4000, 7110));
4736 c.ResetTableReader();
4737}

4780TEST_F(GeneralTableTest, ApproximateKeyAnchors) {
4781 Random rnd(301);
4782 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
4783 std::string tmp;
4784 for (int i = 1000; i < 9000; i++) {
4785 c.Add(std::to_string(i), rnd.RandomString(2000));
4786 }
4787 std::vector<std::string> keys;
4788 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
4789 Options options;
4790 InternalKeyComparator ikc(options.comparator);
4791 options.compression = kNoCompression;
4792 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
4793 table_options.block_size = 4096;
4794 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
4795 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
4796 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options, ikc, &keys, &kvmap);
4797
4798 std::vector<TableReader::Anchor> anchors;
4799 ASSERT_OK(c.GetTableReader()->ApproximateKeyAnchors(ReadOptions(), anchors));
4800 // The target is 128 anchors. But in reality it can be slightly more or
4801 // fewer.
4802 ASSERT_GT(anchors.size(), 120);
4803 ASSERT_LT(anchors.size(), 140);
4804
4805 // We have around 8000 keys. With 128 anchors, in average 62.5 keys per
4806 // anchor. Here we take a rough range and estimate the distance between
4807 // anchors is between 50 and 100.
4808 // Total data size is about 18,000,000, so each anchor range is about
4809 // 140,625. We also take a rough range.
4810 int prev_num = 1000;
4811 // Non-last anchor
4812 for (size_t i = 0; i + 1 < anchors.size(); i++) {
4813 auto& anchor = anchors[i];
4814 ASSERT_GT(anchor.range_size, 100000);
4815 ASSERT_LT(anchor.range_size, 200000);
4816
4817 // Key might be shortened, so fill 0 in the end if it is the case.
4818 std::string key_cpy = anchor.user_key;
4819 key_cpy.append(4 - key_cpy.size(), '0');
4820 int num = std::stoi(key_cpy);
4821 ASSERT_GT(num - prev_num, 50);
4822 ASSERT_LT(num - prev_num, 100);
4823 prev_num = num;
4824 }
4825
4826 ASSERT_EQ("8999", anchors.back().user_key);
4827 ASSERT_LT(anchors.back().range_size, 200000);
4828
4829 c.ResetTableReader();
4830}

4893TEST_F(MemTableTest, Simple) {
4894 WriteBatch batch;
4895 WriteBatchInternal::SetSequence(&batch, 100);
4896 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(std::string("k1"), std::string("v1")));
4897 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(std::string("k2"), std::string("v2")));
4898 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(std::string("k3"), std::string("v3")));
4899 ASSERT_OK(batch.Put(std::string("largekey"), std::string("vlarge")));
4900 ASSERT_OK(batch.DeleteRange(std::string("chi"), std::string("xigua")));
4901 ASSERT_OK(batch.DeleteRange(std::string("begin"), std::string("end")));
4902 ColumnFamilyMemTablesDefault cf_mems_default(GetMemTable());
4903 ASSERT_TRUE(
4904 WriteBatchInternal::InsertInto(&batch, &cf_mems_default, nullptr, nullptr)
4905 .ok());
4906
4907 for (int i = 0; i < 2; ++i) {
4908 Arena arena;
4909 ScopedArenaPtr<InternalIterator> arena_iter_guard;
4910 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter_guard;
4911 InternalIterator* iter;
4912 if (i == 0) {
4913 iter = GetMemTable()->NewIterator(ReadOptions(),
4914 /*seqno_to_time_mapping=*/nullptr,
4915 &arena, /*prefix_extractor=*/nullptr,
4916 /*for_flush=*/false);
4917 arena_iter_guard.reset(iter);
4918 } else {
4919 iter = GetMemTable()->NewRangeTombstoneIterator(
4920 ReadOptions(), kMaxSequenceNumber /* read_seq */,
4921 false /* immutable_memtable */);
4922 iter_guard.reset(iter);
4923 }
4924 if (iter == nullptr) {
4925 continue;
4926 }
4927 iter->SeekToFirst();
4928 while (iter->Valid()) {
4929 fprintf(stderr, "key: '%s' -> '%s'\n", iter->key().ToString().c_str(),
4930 iter->value().ToString().c_str());
4931 iter->Next();
4932 }
4933 }
4934}

4963TEST(TableTest, FooterTests) {
4964 Random* r = Random::GetTLSInstance();
4965 uint64_t data_size = (uint64_t{1} << r->Uniform(40)) + r->Uniform(100);
4966 uint64_t index_size = r->Uniform(1000000000);
4967 uint64_t metaindex_size = r->Uniform(1000000);
4968 // 5 == block trailer size
4969 BlockHandle index(data_size + 5, index_size);
4970 BlockHandle meta_index(data_size + index_size + 2 * 5, metaindex_size);
4971 uint64_t footer_offset = data_size + metaindex_size + index_size + 3 * 5;
4972 uint32_t base_context_checksum = 123456789;
4973 {
4974 // legacy block based
4975 FooterBuilder footer;
4976 ASSERT_OK(footer.Build(kBlockBasedTableMagicNumber, /* format_version */ 0,
4977 footer_offset, kCRC32c, meta_index, index));
4978 Footer decoded_footer;
4979 ASSERT_OK(decoded_footer.DecodeFrom(footer.GetSlice(), footer_offset));
4980 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.table_magic_number(), kBlockBasedTableMagicNumber);
4981 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.checksum_type(), kCRC32c);
4982 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.metaindex_handle().offset(), meta_index.offset());
4983 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.metaindex_handle().size(), meta_index.size());
4984 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.index_handle().offset(), index.offset());
4985 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.index_handle().size(), index.size());
4986 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.format_version(), 0U);
4987 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.base_context_checksum(), 0U);
4988 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.GetBlockTrailerSize(), 5U);
4989 // Ensure serialized with legacy magic
4990 ASSERT_EQ(
4991 DecodeFixed64(footer.GetSlice().data() + footer.GetSlice().size() - 8),
4992 kLegacyBlockBasedTableMagicNumber);
4993 }
4994 // block based, various checksums, various versions
4995 for (auto t : GetSupportedChecksums()) {
4996 for (uint32_t fv = 1; IsSupportedFormatVersion(fv); ++fv) {
4997 uint32_t maybe_bcc =
4998 FormatVersionUsesContextChecksum(fv) ? base_context_checksum : 0U;
4999 FooterBuilder footer;
5000 ASSERT_OK(footer.Build(kBlockBasedTableMagicNumber, fv, footer_offset, t,
5001 meta_index, index, maybe_bcc));
5002 Footer decoded_footer;
5003 ASSERT_OK(decoded_footer.DecodeFrom(footer.GetSlice(), footer_offset));
5004 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.table_magic_number(),
5005 kBlockBasedTableMagicNumber);
5006 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.checksum_type(), t);
5007 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.metaindex_handle().offset(),
5008 meta_index.offset());
5009 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.metaindex_handle().size(), meta_index.size());
5010 if (FormatVersionUsesIndexHandleInFooter(fv)) {
5011 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.index_handle().offset(), index.offset());
5012 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.index_handle().size(), index.size());
5013 }
5014 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.format_version(), fv);
5015 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.GetBlockTrailerSize(), 5U);
5016
5017 if (FormatVersionUsesContextChecksum(fv)) {
5018 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.base_context_checksum(),
5019 base_context_checksum);
5020
5021 // Bad offset should fail footer checksum
5022 decoded_footer = Footer();
5023 ASSERT_NOK(
5024 decoded_footer.DecodeFrom(footer.GetSlice(), footer_offset - 1));
5025 } else {
5026 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.base_context_checksum(), 0U);
5027 }
5028
5029 // Too big metaindex size should also fail encoding only in new footer
5030 uint64_t big_metaindex_size = 0x100000007U;
5031 uint64_t big_footer_offset =
5032 data_size + big_metaindex_size + index_size + 3 * 5;
5033 BlockHandle big_metaindex =
5034 BlockHandle(data_size + index_size + 2 * 5, big_metaindex_size);
5035 ASSERT_NE(footer
5036 .Build(kBlockBasedTableMagicNumber, fv, big_footer_offset,
5037 t, big_metaindex, index, maybe_bcc)
5038 .ok(),
5039 FormatVersionUsesContextChecksum(fv));
5040 }
5041 }
5042
5043 {
5044 // legacy plain table
5045 FooterBuilder footer;
5046 ASSERT_OK(footer.Build(kPlainTableMagicNumber, /* format_version */ 0,
5047 footer_offset, kNoChecksum, meta_index));
5048 Footer decoded_footer;
5049 ASSERT_OK(decoded_footer.DecodeFrom(footer.GetSlice(), footer_offset));
5050 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.table_magic_number(), kPlainTableMagicNumber);
5051 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.checksum_type(), kCRC32c);
5052 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.metaindex_handle().offset(), meta_index.offset());
5053 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.metaindex_handle().size(), meta_index.size());
5054 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.index_handle().offset(), 0U);
5055 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.index_handle().size(), 0U);
5056 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.format_version(), 0U);
5057 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.GetBlockTrailerSize(), 0U);
5058 // Ensure serialized with legacy magic
5059 ASSERT_EQ(
5060 DecodeFixed64(footer.GetSlice().data() + footer.GetSlice().size() - 8),
5061 kLegacyPlainTableMagicNumber);
5062 }
5063 {
5064 // xxhash plain table (not currently used)
5065 FooterBuilder footer;
5066 ASSERT_OK(footer.Build(kPlainTableMagicNumber, /* format_version */ 1,
5067 footer_offset, kxxHash, meta_index));
5068 Footer decoded_footer;
5069 ASSERT_OK(decoded_footer.DecodeFrom(footer.GetSlice(), footer_offset));
5070 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.table_magic_number(), kPlainTableMagicNumber);
5071 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.checksum_type(), kxxHash);
5072 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.metaindex_handle().offset(), meta_index.offset());
5073 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.metaindex_handle().size(), meta_index.size());
5074 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.index_handle().offset(), 0U);
5075 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.index_handle().size(), 0U);
5076 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.format_version(), 1U);
5077 ASSERT_EQ(decoded_footer.GetBlockTrailerSize(), 0U);
5078 }
5079}

5081class IndexBlockRestartIntervalTest
5082 : public TableTest,
5083 public ::testing::WithParamInterface<std::pair<int, bool>> {
5084 public:
5085 static std::vector<std::pair<int, bool>> GetRestartValues() {
5086 return {{-1, false}, {0, false}, {1, false}, {8, false},
5087 {16, false}, {32, false}, {-1, true}, {0, true},
5088 {1, true}, {8, true}, {16, true}, {32, true}};
5089 }
5090};
5091
5092INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(
5093 IndexBlockRestartIntervalTest, IndexBlockRestartIntervalTest,
5094 ::testing::ValuesIn(IndexBlockRestartIntervalTest::GetRestartValues()));
5095
5096TEST_P(IndexBlockRestartIntervalTest, IndexBlockRestartInterval) {
5097 const int kKeysInTable = 10000;
5098 const int kKeySize = 100;
5099 const int kValSize = 500;
5100
5101 const int index_block_restart_interval = std::get<0>(GetParam());
5102 const bool value_delta_encoding = std::get<1>(GetParam());
5103
5104 Options options;
5105 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
5106 table_options.block_size = 64; // small block size to get big index block
5107 table_options.index_block_restart_interval = index_block_restart_interval;
5108 if (value_delta_encoding) {
5109 table_options.format_version = 4;
5110 } else {
5111 table_options.format_version = 3;
5112 }
5113 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
5114
5115 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator());
5116 static Random rnd(301);
5117 for (int i = 0; i < kKeysInTable; i++) {
5118 InternalKey k(rnd.RandomString(kKeySize), 0, kTypeValue);
5119 c.Add(k.Encode().ToString(), rnd.RandomString(kValSize));
5120 }
5121
5122 std::vector<std::string> keys;
5123 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
5124 std::unique_ptr<InternalKeyComparator> comparator(
5125 new InternalKeyComparator(BytewiseComparator()));
5126 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
5127 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
5128 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options, *comparator, &keys,
5129 &kvmap);
5130 auto reader = c.GetTableReader();
5131
5132 ReadOptions read_options;
5133 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> db_iter(reader->NewIterator(
5134 read_options, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), /*arena=*/nullptr,
5135 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized));
5136
5137 // Test point lookup
5138 for (auto& kv : kvmap) {
5139 db_iter->Seek(kv.first);
5140
5141 ASSERT_TRUE(db_iter->Valid());
5142 ASSERT_OK(db_iter->status());
5143 ASSERT_EQ(db_iter->key(), kv.first);
5144 ASSERT_EQ(db_iter->value(), kv.second);
5145 }
5146
5147 // Test iterating
5148 auto kv_iter = kvmap.begin();
5149 for (db_iter->SeekToFirst(); db_iter->Valid(); db_iter->Next()) {
5150 ASSERT_EQ(db_iter->key(), kv_iter->first);
5151 ASSERT_EQ(db_iter->value(), kv_iter->second);
5152 kv_iter++;
5153 }
5154 ASSERT_EQ(kv_iter, kvmap.end());
5155 c.ResetTableReader();
5156}

5158class PrefixTest : public testing::Test {

5164namespace {
5165// A simple PrefixExtractor that only works for test PrefixAndWholeKeyTest
5166class TestPrefixExtractor : public ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SliceTransform {
5167 public:
5168 ~TestPrefixExtractor() override = default;
5169 ;
5170 const char* Name() const override { return "TestPrefixExtractor"; }
5171
5172 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::Slice Transform(
5173 const ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::Slice& src) const override {
5174 assert(IsValid(src));
5175 return ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::Slice(src.data(), 3);
5176 }
5177
5178 bool InDomain(const ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::Slice& src) const override {
5179 return IsValid(src);
5180 }
5181
5182 bool InRange(const ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::Slice& /*dst*/) const override {
5183 return true;
5184 }
5185
5186 bool IsValid(const ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::Slice& src) const {
5187 if (src.size() != 4) {
5188 return false;
5189 }
5190 if (src[0] != '[') {
5191 return false;
5192 }
5193 if (src[1] < '0' || src[1] > '9') {
5194 return false;
5195 }
5196 if (src[2] != ']') {
5197 return false;
5198 }
5199 if (src[3] < '0' || src[3] > '9') {
5200 return false;
5201 }
5202 return true;
5203 }
5204};
5205} // namespace

5207TEST_F(PrefixTest, PrefixAndWholeKeyTest) {
5208 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::Options options;
5209 options.compaction_style = ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::kCompactionStyleUniversal;
5210 options.num_levels = 20;
5211 options.create_if_missing = true;
5212 options.optimize_filters_for_hits = false;
5213 options.target_file_size_base = 268435456;
5214 options.prefix_extractor = std::make_shared<TestPrefixExtractor>();
5215 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
5216 bbto.filter_policy.reset(ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::NewBloomFilterPolicy(10));
5217 bbto.block_size = 262144;
5218 bbto.whole_key_filtering = true;
5219
5220 const std::string kDBPath = test::PerThreadDBPath("table_prefix_test");
5221 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
5222 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(kDBPath, options));
5223 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DB* db;
5224 ASSERT_OK(ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DB::Open(options, kDBPath, &db));
5225
5226 // Create a bunch of keys with 10 filters.

5242/*
5243 * Disable TableWithGlobalSeqno since RocksDB does not store global_seqno in
5244 * the SST file any more. Instead, RocksDB deduces global_seqno from the
5245 * MANIFEST while reading from an SST. Therefore, it's not possible to test the
5246 * functionality of global_seqno in a single, isolated unit test without the
5247 * involvement of Version, VersionSet, etc.
5248 */
5249TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, DISABLED_TableWithGlobalSeqno) {
5250 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
5251 test::StringSink* sink = new test::StringSink();
5252 std::unique_ptr<FSWritableFile> holder(sink);
5253 std::unique_ptr<WritableFileWriter> file_writer(new WritableFileWriter(
5254 std::move(holder), "" /* don't care */, FileOptions()));
5255 Options options;
5256 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
5257 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
5258 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
5259 InternalKeyComparator ikc(options.comparator);
5260 InternalTblPropCollFactories internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories;
5261 internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories.emplace_back(
5262 new SstFileWriterPropertiesCollectorFactory(2 /* version */,
5263 0 /* global_seqno*/));
5264 std::string column_family_name;
5265 const ReadOptions read_options;
5266 const WriteOptions write_options;
5267 std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder> builder(options.table_factory->NewTableBuilder(
5268 TableBuilderOptions(ioptions, moptions, read_options, write_options, ikc,
5269 &internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories, kNoCompression,
5270 CompressionOptions(), kUnknownColumnFamily,
5271 column_family_name, -1, kUnknownNewestKeyTime),
5272 file_writer.get()));
5273
5274 for (char c = 'a'; c <= 'z'; ++c) {
5275 std::string key(8, c);
5276 std::string value = key;
5277 InternalKey ik(key, 0, kTypeValue);
5278
5279 builder->Add(ik.Encode(), value);
5280 }
5281 ASSERT_OK(builder->Finish());
5282 ASSERT_OK(file_writer->Flush(IOOptions()));
5283
5284 test::RandomRWStringSink ss_rw(sink);
5285 uint32_t version;
5286 uint64_t global_seqno;
5287 uint64_t global_seqno_offset;
5288
5289 // Helper function to get version, global_seqno, global_seqno_offset
5290 std::function<void()> GetVersionAndGlobalSeqno = [&]() {
5291 std::unique_ptr<FSRandomAccessFile> source(
5292 new test::StringSource(ss_rw.contents(), 73342, true));
5293 std::unique_ptr<RandomAccessFileReader> file_reader(
5294 new RandomAccessFileReader(std::move(source), ""));
5295
5296 std::unique_ptr<TableProperties> props;
5297 ASSERT_OK(ReadTableProperties(file_reader.get(), ss_rw.contents().size(),
5298 kBlockBasedTableMagicNumber, ioptions,
5299 read_options, &props));
5300
5301 UserCollectedProperties user_props = props->user_collected_properties;
5302 version = DecodeFixed32(
5303 user_props[ExternalSstFilePropertyNames::kVersion].c_str());
5304 global_seqno = DecodeFixed64(
5305 user_props[ExternalSstFilePropertyNames::kGlobalSeqno].c_str());
5306 global_seqno_offset = props->external_sst_file_global_seqno_offset;
5307 };
5308
5309 // Helper function to update the value of the global seqno in the file
5310 std::function<void(uint64_t)> SetGlobalSeqno = [&](uint64_t val) {
5311 std::string new_global_seqno;
5312 PutFixed64(&new_global_seqno, val);
5313
5314 ASSERT_OK(ss_rw.Write(global_seqno_offset, new_global_seqno, IOOptions(),
5315 nullptr));
5316 };
5317
5318 // Helper function to get the contents of the table InternalIterator
5319 std::unique_ptr<TableReader> table_reader;
5320 std::function<InternalIterator*()> GetTableInternalIter = [&]() {
5321 std::unique_ptr<FSRandomAccessFile> source(
5322 new test::StringSource(ss_rw.contents(), 73342, true));
5323 std::unique_ptr<RandomAccessFileReader> file_reader(
5324 new RandomAccessFileReader(std::move(source), ""));
5325
5326 options.table_factory->NewTableReader(
5327 TableReaderOptions(ioptions, moptions.prefix_extractor, EnvOptions(),
5328 ikc, 0 /* block_protection_bytes_per_key */),
5329 std::move(file_reader), ss_rw.contents().size(), &table_reader);
5330
5331 return table_reader->NewIterator(
5332 read_options, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), /*arena=*/nullptr,
5333 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized);
5334 };
5335
5336 GetVersionAndGlobalSeqno();
5337 ASSERT_EQ(2u, version);
5338 ASSERT_EQ(0u, global_seqno);
5339
5340 InternalIterator* iter = GetTableInternalIter();
5341 char current_c = 'a';
5342 for (iter->SeekToFirst(); iter->Valid(); iter->Next()) {
5343 ParsedInternalKey pik;
5344 ASSERT_OK(ParseInternalKey(iter->key(), &pik, true /* log_err_key */));
5345
5346 ASSERT_EQ(pik.type, ValueType::kTypeValue);
5347 ASSERT_EQ(pik.sequence, 0);
5348 ASSERT_EQ(pik.user_key, iter->value());
5349 ASSERT_EQ(pik.user_key.ToString(), std::string(8, current_c));
5350 current_c++;
5351 }
5352 ASSERT_EQ(current_c, 'z' + 1);
5353 delete iter;
5354
5355 // Update global sequence number to 10
5356 SetGlobalSeqno(10);
5357 GetVersionAndGlobalSeqno();
5358 ASSERT_EQ(2u, version);
5359 ASSERT_EQ(10u, global_seqno);
5360
5361 iter = GetTableInternalIter();
5362 current_c = 'a';
5363 for (iter->SeekToFirst(); iter->Valid(); iter->Next()) {
5364 ParsedInternalKey pik;
5365 ASSERT_OK(ParseInternalKey(iter->key(), &pik, true /* log_err_key */));
5366
5367 ASSERT_EQ(pik.type, ValueType::kTypeValue);
5368 ASSERT_EQ(pik.sequence, 10);
5369 ASSERT_EQ(pik.user_key, iter->value());
5370 ASSERT_EQ(pik.user_key.ToString(), std::string(8, current_c));
5371 current_c++;
5372 }
5373 ASSERT_EQ(current_c, 'z' + 1);
5374
5375 // Verify Seek
5376 for (char c = 'a'; c <= 'z'; c++) {
5377 std::string k = std::string(8, c);
5378 InternalKey ik(k, 10, kValueTypeForSeek);
5379 iter->Seek(ik.Encode());
5380 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
5381
5382 ParsedInternalKey pik;
5383 ASSERT_OK(ParseInternalKey(iter->key(), &pik, true /* log_err_key */));
5384
5385 ASSERT_EQ(pik.type, ValueType::kTypeValue);
5386 ASSERT_EQ(pik.sequence, 10);
5387 ASSERT_EQ(pik.user_key.ToString(), k);
5388 ASSERT_EQ(iter->value().ToString(), k);
5389 }
5390 delete iter;
5391
5392 // Update global sequence number to 3
5393 SetGlobalSeqno(3);
5394 GetVersionAndGlobalSeqno();
5395 ASSERT_EQ(2u, version);
5396 ASSERT_EQ(3u, global_seqno);
5397
5398 iter = GetTableInternalIter();
5399 current_c = 'a';
5400 for (iter->SeekToFirst(); iter->Valid(); iter->Next()) {
5401 ParsedInternalKey pik;
5402 ASSERT_OK(ParseInternalKey(iter->key(), &pik, true /* log_err_key */));
5403
5404 ASSERT_EQ(pik.type, ValueType::kTypeValue);
5405 ASSERT_EQ(pik.sequence, 3);
5406 ASSERT_EQ(pik.user_key, iter->value());
5407 ASSERT_EQ(pik.user_key.ToString(), std::string(8, current_c));
5408 current_c++;
5409 }
5410 ASSERT_EQ(current_c, 'z' + 1);
5411
5412 // Verify Seek
5413 for (char c = 'a'; c <= 'z'; c++) {
5414 std::string k = std::string(8, c);
5415 // seqno=4 is less than 3 so we still should get our key
5416 InternalKey ik(k, 4, kValueTypeForSeek);
5417 iter->Seek(ik.Encode());
5418 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
5419
5420 ParsedInternalKey pik;
5421 ASSERT_OK(ParseInternalKey(iter->key(), &pik, true /* log_err_key */));
5422
5423 ASSERT_EQ(pik.type, ValueType::kTypeValue);
5424 ASSERT_EQ(pik.sequence, 3);
5425 ASSERT_EQ(pik.user_key.ToString(), k);
5426 ASSERT_EQ(iter->value().ToString(), k);
5427 }
5428
5429 delete iter;
5430}

5432TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, BlockAlignTest) {
5433 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
5434 bbto.block_align = true;
5435 test::StringSink* sink = new test::StringSink();
5436 std::unique_ptr<FSWritableFile> holder(sink);

5438 std::move(holder), "" /* don't care */, FileOptions()));
5439 Options options;
5440 options.compression = kNoCompression;
5441 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
5442 ASSERT_OK(options.table_factory->ValidateOptions(
5443 DBOptions(options), ColumnFamilyOptions(options)));
5444 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
5445 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
5446 InternalKeyComparator ikc(options.comparator);
5447 InternalTblPropCollFactories internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories;
5448 std::string column_family_name;
5449 const ReadOptions read_options;
5450 const WriteOptions write_options;
5451 std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder> builder(options.table_factory->NewTableBuilder(
5452 TableBuilderOptions(ioptions, moptions, read_options, write_options, ikc,
5453 &internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories, kNoCompression,
5454 CompressionOptions(), kUnknownColumnFamily,
5455 column_family_name, -1, kUnknownNewestKeyTime),
5456 file_writer.get()));
5457
5458 for (int i = 1; i <= 10000; ++i) {
5459 std::ostringstream ostr;
5460 ostr << std::setfill('0') << std::setw(5) << i;
5461 std::string key = ostr.str();
5462 std::string value = "val";
5463 InternalKey ik(key, 0, kTypeValue);
5464
5465 builder->Add(ik.Encode(), value);
5466 }
5467 ASSERT_OK(builder->Finish());
5468 ASSERT_OK(file_writer->Flush(IOOptions()));
5469
5470 std::unique_ptr<FSRandomAccessFile> source(
5471 new test::StringSource(sink->contents(), 73342, false));
5472 std::unique_ptr<RandomAccessFileReader> file_reader(
5473 new RandomAccessFileReader(std::move(source), "test"));
5474 // Helper function to get version, global_seqno, global_seqno_offset
5475 std::function<void()> VerifyBlockAlignment = [&]() {
5476 std::unique_ptr<TableProperties> props;
5477 ASSERT_OK(ReadTableProperties(file_reader.get(), sink->contents().size(),
5478 kBlockBasedTableMagicNumber, ioptions,
5479 read_options, &props));
5480
5481 uint64_t data_block_size = props->data_size / props->num_data_blocks;
5482 ASSERT_EQ(data_block_size, 4096);
5483 ASSERT_EQ(props->data_size, data_block_size * props->num_data_blocks);
5484 };
5485
5486 VerifyBlockAlignment();
5487
5488 // The below block of code verifies that we can read back the keys. Set
5489 // block_align to false when creating the reader to ensure we can flip between
5490 // the two modes without any issues
5491 std::unique_ptr<TableReader> table_reader;
5492 bbto.block_align = false;
5493 Options options2;
5494 options2.compression = kNoCompression;
5495 options2.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
5496 ASSERT_OK(options2.table_factory->ValidateOptions(
5497 DBOptions(options2), ColumnFamilyOptions(options2)));
5498 ImmutableOptions ioptions2(options2);
5499 const MutableCFOptions moptions2(options2);
5500
5501 ASSERT_OK(moptions.table_factory->NewTableReader(
5502 TableReaderOptions(ioptions2, moptions2.prefix_extractor, EnvOptions(),
5503 GetPlainInternalComparator(options2.comparator),
5504 0 /* block_protection_bytes_per_key */),
5505 std::move(file_reader), sink->contents().size(), &table_reader));
5506
5507 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> db_iter(table_reader->NewIterator(
5508 read_options, moptions2.prefix_extractor.get(), /*arena=*/nullptr,
5509 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized));
5510
5511 int expected_key = 1;
5512 for (db_iter->SeekToFirst(); db_iter->Valid(); db_iter->Next()) {
5513 std::ostringstream ostr;
5514 ostr << std::setfill('0') << std::setw(5) << expected_key++;
5515 std::string key = ostr.str();
5516 std::string value = "val";
5517
5518 ASSERT_OK(db_iter->status());
5519 ASSERT_EQ(ExtractUserKey(db_iter->key()).ToString(), key);
5520 ASSERT_EQ(db_iter->value().ToString(), value);
5521 }
5522 expected_key--;
5523 ASSERT_EQ(expected_key, 10000);
5524 table_reader.reset();
5525}

5527TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, FixBlockAlignMismatchedFileChecksums) {
5528 Options options;
5529 options.create_if_missing = true;
5530 options.compression = kNoCompression;
5531 options.file_checksum_gen_factory = GetFileChecksumGenCrc32cFactory();
5532 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto;
5533 bbto.block_align = true;
5534 bbto.block_size = 1024;
5535 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));

5537 DBOptions(options), ColumnFamilyOptions(options)));

5539 test::PerThreadDBPath("block_align_padded_bytes_verify_file_checksums");

5541 DB* db;
5542 ASSERT_OK(DB::Open(options, kDBPath, &db));
5543 ASSERT_OK(db->Put(WriteOptions(), "k1", "v1"));
5544 ASSERT_OK(db->Flush(FlushOptions()));
5545 // Before the fix, VerifyFileChecksums() will fail as padded bytes from
5546 // aligning blocks are used to generate the checksum to compare against the
5547 // one not generated by padded bytes
5548 ASSERT_OK(db->VerifyFileChecksums(ReadOptions()));
5549 delete db;

5616TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, PropertiesBlockRestartPointTest) {
5617 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
5618 bbto.block_align = true;
5619 test::StringSink* sink = new test::StringSink();
5620 std::unique_ptr<FSWritableFile> holder(sink);
5621 std::unique_ptr<WritableFileWriter> file_writer(new WritableFileWriter(
5622 std::move(holder), "" /* don't care */, FileOptions()));
5623
5624 Options options;
5625 options.compression = kNoCompression;
5626 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
5627 ASSERT_OK(options.table_factory->ValidateOptions(
5628 DBOptions(options), ColumnFamilyOptions(options)));
5629
5630 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
5631 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
5632 InternalKeyComparator ikc(options.comparator);
5633 InternalTblPropCollFactories internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories;
5634 std::string column_family_name;
5635 const ReadOptions read_options;
5636 const WriteOptions write_options;
5637 std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder> builder(options.table_factory->NewTableBuilder(
5638 TableBuilderOptions(ioptions, moptions, read_options, write_options, ikc,
5639 &internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories, kNoCompression,
5640 CompressionOptions(), kUnknownColumnFamily,
5641 column_family_name, -1, kUnknownNewestKeyTime),
5642 file_writer.get()));
5643
5644 for (int i = 1; i <= 10000; ++i) {
5645 std::ostringstream ostr;
5646 ostr << std::setfill('0') << std::setw(5) << i;
5647 std::string key = ostr.str();
5648 std::string value = "val";
5649 InternalKey ik(key, 0, kTypeValue);
5650
5651 builder->Add(ik.Encode(), value);
5652 }
5653 ASSERT_OK(builder->Finish());
5654 ASSERT_OK(file_writer->Flush(IOOptions()));
5655
5656 std::unique_ptr<FSRandomAccessFile> source(
5657 new test::StringSource(sink->contents(), 73342, true));
5658 std::unique_ptr<RandomAccessFileReader> file_reader(
5659 new RandomAccessFileReader(std::move(source), "test"));
5660
5661 {
5662 RandomAccessFileReader* file = file_reader.get();
5663 uint64_t file_size = sink->contents().size();
5664
5665 Footer footer;
5666 ASSERT_OK(ReadFooterFromFile(IOOptions(), file, *FileSystem::Default(),
5667 nullptr /* prefetch_buffer */, file_size,
5668 &footer, kBlockBasedTableMagicNumber));
5669
5670 auto BlockFetchHelper = [&](const BlockHandle& handle, BlockType block_type,
5671 BlockContents* contents) {
5672 ReadOptions read_options_for_helper;
5673 read_options_for_helper.verify_checksums = false;
5674 PersistentCacheOptions cache_options;
5675
5676 BlockFetcher block_fetcher(
5677 file, nullptr /* prefetch_buffer */, footer, read_options_for_helper,
5678 handle, contents, ioptions, false /* decompress */,
5679 false /*maybe_compressed*/, block_type,
5680 UncompressionDict::GetEmptyDict(), cache_options);
5681
5682 ASSERT_OK(block_fetcher.ReadBlockContents());
5683 };
5684
5685 // -- Read metaindex block
5686 auto metaindex_handle = footer.metaindex_handle();
5687 BlockContents metaindex_contents;
5688
5689 BlockFetchHelper(metaindex_handle, BlockType::kMetaIndex,
5690 &metaindex_contents);
5691 Block metaindex_block(std::move(metaindex_contents));
5692
5693 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> meta_iter(metaindex_block.NewDataIterator(
5694 BytewiseComparator(), kDisableGlobalSequenceNumber));
5695
5696 // -- Read properties block
5697 BlockHandle properties_handle;
5698 ASSERT_OK(FindOptionalMetaBlock(meta_iter.get(), kPropertiesBlockName,
5699 &properties_handle));
5700 ASSERT_FALSE(properties_handle.IsNull());
5701 BlockContents properties_contents;
5702 BlockFetchHelper(properties_handle, BlockType::kProperties,
5703 &properties_contents);
5704 Block properties_block(std::move(properties_contents));
5705
5706 ASSERT_EQ(properties_block.NumRestarts(), 1u);
5707 }
5708}
5709
5710TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, CompressionRatioThreshold) {
5711 for (CompressionType type : GetSupportedCompressions()) {
5712 if (type == kNoCompression) {
5713 continue;
5714 }
5715 if (type == kBZip2Compression) {
5716 // Weird behavior in this test
5717 continue;
5718 }
5719 SCOPED_TRACE("Compression type: " + std::to_string(type));
5720
5721 Options options;
5722 options.compression = type;
5723
5724 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
5725 int len = 10000;
5726 Random rnd(301);
5727 std::vector<std::string> keys;
5728 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
5729
5730 // Test the max_compressed_bytes_per_kb option
5731 for (int threshold : {0, 1, 100, 400, 600, 900, 1024}) {
5732 SCOPED_TRACE("threshold=" + std::to_string(threshold));
5733 options.compression_opts.max_compressed_bytes_per_kb = threshold;
5734 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
5735 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
5736
5737 for (double compressible_to : {0.25, 0.75}) {
5738 SCOPED_TRACE("compressible_to=" + std::to_string(compressible_to));
5739 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(),
5740 true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
5741 std::string buf;
5742 c.Add("x", test::CompressibleString(&rnd, compressible_to, len, &buf));
5743
5744 // write an SST file
5745 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
5746 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
5747
5748 size_t table_file_size = c.TEST_GetSink()->contents().size();
5749 size_t approx_sst_overhead = 1000;
5750 if (compressible_to < threshold / 1024.0) {
5751 // Should be compressed (substantial variance depending on algorithm)
5752 EXPECT_NEAR2(len * compressible_to + approx_sst_overhead,
5753 table_file_size, len / 8);
5754 } else {
5755 // Should not be compressed
5756 EXPECT_NEAR2(len + approx_sst_overhead, table_file_size, len / 10);
5757 }
5758 }
5759 }
5760 }
5761}
5762
5763TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, PropertiesMetaBlockLast) {
5764 // The properties meta-block should come at the end since we always need to
5765 // read it when opening a file, unlike index/filter/other meta-blocks, which
5766 // are sometimes read depending on the user's configuration. This ordering
5767 // allows us to do a small readahead on the end of the file to read properties
5768 // and meta-index blocks with one I/O.
5769 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
5770 c.Add("a1", "val1");
5771 c.Add("b2", "val2");
5772 c.Add("c3", "val3");
5773 c.Add("d4", "val4");
5774 c.Add("e5", "val5");
5775 c.Add("f6", "val6");
5776 c.Add("g7", "val7");
5777 c.Add("h8", "val8");
5778 c.Add("j9", "val9");
5779
5780 // write an SST file
5781 Options options;
5782 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
5783 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(
5784 8 /* bits_per_key */, false /* use_block_based_filter */));
5785 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
5786 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
5787 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
5788 std::vector<std::string> keys;
5789 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
5790 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
5791 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
5792
5793 // get file reader
5794 test::StringSink* table_sink = c.TEST_GetSink();
5795 std::unique_ptr<FSRandomAccessFile> source(new test::StringSource(
5796 table_sink->contents(), 0 /* unique_id */, false /* allow_mmap_reads */));
5797
5798 std::unique_ptr<RandomAccessFileReader> table_reader(
5799 new RandomAccessFileReader(std::move(source), "test"));
5800 size_t table_size = table_sink->contents().size();
5801
5802 // read footer
5803 Footer footer;
5804 IOOptions opts;
5805 ASSERT_OK(ReadFooterFromFile(opts, table_reader.get(), *FileSystem::Default(),
5806 nullptr /* prefetch_buffer */, table_size,
5807 &footer, kBlockBasedTableMagicNumber));
5808
5809 // read metaindex
5810 auto metaindex_handle = footer.metaindex_handle();
5811 BlockContents metaindex_contents;
5812 PersistentCacheOptions pcache_opts;
5813 BlockFetcher block_fetcher(
5814 table_reader.get(), nullptr /* prefetch_buffer */, footer, ReadOptions(),
5815 metaindex_handle, &metaindex_contents, ioptions, false /* decompress */,
5816 false /*maybe_compressed*/, BlockType::kMetaIndex,
5817 UncompressionDict::GetEmptyDict(), pcache_opts,
5818 nullptr /*memory_allocator*/);
5819 ASSERT_OK(block_fetcher.ReadBlockContents());
5820 Block metaindex_block(std::move(metaindex_contents));
5821
5822 // verify properties block comes last
5823 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> metaindex_iter{
5824 metaindex_block.NewMetaIterator()};
5825 uint64_t max_offset = 0;
5826 std::string key_at_max_offset;
5827 for (metaindex_iter->SeekToFirst(); metaindex_iter->Valid();
5828 metaindex_iter->Next()) {
5829 BlockHandle handle;
5830 Slice value = metaindex_iter->value();
5831 ASSERT_OK(handle.DecodeFrom(&value));
5832 if (handle.offset() > max_offset) {
5833 max_offset = handle.offset();
5834 key_at_max_offset = metaindex_iter->key().ToString();
5835 }
5836 }
5837 ASSERT_EQ(kPropertiesBlockName, key_at_max_offset);
5838 if (FormatVersionUsesIndexHandleInFooter(footer.format_version())) {
5839 // If index handle is stored in footer rather than metaindex block,
5840 // need separate logic to verify it comes before properties block.
5841 ASSERT_GT(max_offset, footer.index_handle().offset());
5842 } else {
5843 ASSERT_TRUE(footer.index_handle().IsNull());
5844 }
5845 c.ResetTableReader();
5846}

5848TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, SeekMetaBlocks) {
5849 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /* convert_to_internal_key_ */);
5850 c.Add("foo_a1", "val1");
5851 c.Add("foo_b2", "val2");
5852 c.Add("foo_c3", "val3");
5853 c.Add("foo_d4", "val4");
5854 c.Add("foo_e5", "val5");
5855 c.Add("foo_f6", "val6");
5856 c.Add("foo_g7", "val7");
5857 c.Add("foo_h8", "val8");
5858 c.Add("foo_j9", "val9");
5859
5860 // write an SST file
5861 Options options;
5862 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
5863 table_options.index_type = BlockBasedTableOptions::kHashSearch;
5864 table_options.filter_policy.reset(NewBloomFilterPolicy(
5865 8 /* bits_per_key */, false /* use_block_based_filter */));
5866 options.prefix_extractor.reset(NewFixedPrefixTransform(4));
5867 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
5868 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
5869 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
5870 std::vector<std::string> keys;
5871 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
5872 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options,
5873 GetPlainInternalComparator(options.comparator), &keys, &kvmap);
5874
5875 // get file reader
5876 test::StringSink* table_sink = c.TEST_GetSink();
5877 std::unique_ptr<FSRandomAccessFile> source(new test::StringSource(
5878 table_sink->contents(), 0 /* unique_id */, false /* allow_mmap_reads */));
5879
5880 std::unique_ptr<RandomAccessFileReader> table_reader(
5881 new RandomAccessFileReader(std::move(source), "test"));
5882 size_t table_size = table_sink->contents().size();
5883
5884 // read footer
5885 Footer footer;
5886 IOOptions opts;
5887 ASSERT_OK(ReadFooterFromFile(opts, table_reader.get(), *FileSystem::Default(),
5888 nullptr /* prefetch_buffer */, table_size,
5889 &footer, kBlockBasedTableMagicNumber));
5890
5891 // read metaindex
5892 auto metaindex_handle = footer.metaindex_handle();
5893 BlockContents metaindex_contents;
5894 PersistentCacheOptions pcache_opts;
5895 BlockFetcher block_fetcher(
5896 table_reader.get(), nullptr /* prefetch_buffer */, footer, ReadOptions(),
5897 metaindex_handle, &metaindex_contents, ioptions, false /* decompress */,
5898 false /*maybe_compressed*/, BlockType::kMetaIndex,
5899 UncompressionDict::GetEmptyDict(), pcache_opts,
5900 nullptr /*memory_allocator*/);
5901 ASSERT_OK(block_fetcher.ReadBlockContents());
5902 Block metaindex_block(std::move(metaindex_contents));
5903
5904 // verify properties block comes last
5905 std::unique_ptr<MetaBlockIter> metaindex_iter(
5906 metaindex_block.NewMetaIterator());
5907 bool has_hash_prefixes = false;
5908 bool has_hash_metadata = false;
5909 for (metaindex_iter->SeekToFirst(); metaindex_iter->Valid();
5910 metaindex_iter->Next()) {
5911 if (metaindex_iter->key().ToString() == kHashIndexPrefixesBlock) {
5912 has_hash_prefixes = true;
5913 } else if (metaindex_iter->key().ToString() ==
5914 kHashIndexPrefixesMetadataBlock) {
5915 has_hash_metadata = true;
5916 }
5917 }
5918 if (has_hash_metadata) {
5919 metaindex_iter->Seek(kHashIndexPrefixesMetadataBlock);
5920 ASSERT_TRUE(metaindex_iter->Valid());
5921 ASSERT_EQ(kHashIndexPrefixesMetadataBlock,
5922 metaindex_iter->key().ToString());
5923 }
5924 if (has_hash_prefixes) {
5925 metaindex_iter->Seek(kHashIndexPrefixesBlock);
5926 ASSERT_TRUE(metaindex_iter->Valid());
5927 ASSERT_EQ(kHashIndexPrefixesBlock, metaindex_iter->key().ToString());
5928 }
5929 c.ResetTableReader();
5930}

5932TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, BadOptions) {
5933 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::Options options;
5934 options.compression = kNoCompression;
5935 options.create_if_missing = true;
5936 BlockBasedTableOptions bbto = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
5937 bbto.block_size = 4000;
5938 bbto.block_align = true;

5941 test::PerThreadDBPath("block_based_table_bad_options_test");

5943 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(kDBPath, options));
5944
5945 std::unique_ptr<DB> db;
5946 {
5947 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DB* _db;
5948 ASSERT_NOK(ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DB::Open(options, kDBPath, &_db));
5949
5950 bbto.block_size = 4096;
5951 options.compression = kSnappyCompression;
5952 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(bbto));
5953 ASSERT_NOK(ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DB::Open(options, kDBPath, &_db));
5954

5958

5961 ASSERT_NOK(ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DB::Open(options, kDBPath, &_db));
5962

5965 db.reset(_db);
5966 }

5969TEST_F(BBTTailPrefetchTest, TestTailPrefetchStats) {
5970 TailPrefetchStats tpstats;
5971 ASSERT_EQ(0, tpstats.GetSuggestedPrefetchSize());
5972 tpstats.RecordEffectiveSize(size_t{1000});
5973 tpstats.RecordEffectiveSize(size_t{1005});
5974 tpstats.RecordEffectiveSize(size_t{1002});
5975 ASSERT_EQ(1005, tpstats.GetSuggestedPrefetchSize());
5976
5977 // One single super large value shouldn't influence much
5978 tpstats.RecordEffectiveSize(size_t{1002000});
5979 tpstats.RecordEffectiveSize(size_t{999});
5980 ASSERT_LE(1005, tpstats.GetSuggestedPrefetchSize());
5981 ASSERT_GT(1200, tpstats.GetSuggestedPrefetchSize());
5982
5983 // Only history of 32 is kept
5984 for (int i = 0; i < 32; i++) {
5985 tpstats.RecordEffectiveSize(size_t{100});
5986 }
5987 ASSERT_EQ(100, tpstats.GetSuggestedPrefetchSize());
5988
5989 // 16 large values and 16 small values. The result should be closer
5990 // to the small value as the algorithm.
5991 for (int i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
5992 tpstats.RecordEffectiveSize(size_t{1000});
5993 }
5994 tpstats.RecordEffectiveSize(size_t{10});
5995 tpstats.RecordEffectiveSize(size_t{20});
5996 for (int i = 0; i < 6; i++) {
5997 tpstats.RecordEffectiveSize(size_t{100});
5998 }
5999 ASSERT_LE(80, tpstats.GetSuggestedPrefetchSize());
6000 ASSERT_GT(200, tpstats.GetSuggestedPrefetchSize());
6001}

6020TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, DataBlockHashIndex) {
6021 const int kNumKeys = 500;
6022 const int kKeySize = 8;
6023 const int kValSize = 40;
6024
6025 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = GetBlockBasedTableOptions();
6026 table_options.data_block_index_type =
6027 BlockBasedTableOptions::kDataBlockBinaryAndHash;
6028
6029 Options options;
6030 options.comparator = BytewiseComparator();
6031
6032 options.table_factory.reset(new BlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
6033
6034 TableConstructor c(options.comparator);
6035
6036 static Random rnd(1048);
6037 for (int i = 0; i < kNumKeys; i++) {
6038 // padding one "0" to mark existent keys.
6039 std::string random_key(rnd.RandomString(kKeySize - 1) + "1");
6040 InternalKey k(random_key, 0, kTypeValue);
6041 c.Add(k.Encode().ToString(), rnd.RandomString(kValSize));
6042 }
6043
6044 std::vector<std::string> keys;
6045 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
6046 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
6047 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
6048 const InternalKeyComparator internal_comparator(options.comparator);
6049 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_options, internal_comparator,
6050 &keys, &kvmap);
6051
6052 auto reader = c.GetTableReader();
6053
6054 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> seek_iter;
6055 ReadOptions read_options;
6056 seek_iter.reset(reader->NewIterator(
6057 read_options, moptions.prefix_extractor.get(), /*arena=*/nullptr,
6058 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized));
6059 for (int i = 0; i < 2; ++i) {
6060 ReadOptions ro;
6061 // for every kv, we seek using two method: Get() and Seek()
6062 // Get() will use the SuffixIndexHash in Block. For non-existent key it
6063 // will invalidate the iterator
6064 // Seek() will use the default BinarySeek() in Block. So for non-existent
6065 // key it will land at the closest key that is large than target.
6066
6067 // Search for existent keys
6068 for (auto& kv : kvmap) {
6069 if (i == 0) {
6070 // Search using Seek()
6071 seek_iter->Seek(kv.first);
6072 ASSERT_OK(seek_iter->status());
6073 ASSERT_TRUE(seek_iter->Valid());
6074 ASSERT_EQ(seek_iter->key(), kv.first);
6075 ASSERT_EQ(seek_iter->value(), kv.second);
6076 } else {
6077 // Search using Get()
6078 PinnableSlice value;
6079 std::string user_key = ExtractUserKey(kv.first).ToString();
6080 GetContext get_context(options.comparator, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr,
6081 GetContext::kNotFound, user_key, &value, nullptr,
6082 nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, nullptr);
6083 ASSERT_OK(reader->Get(ro, kv.first, &get_context,
6084 moptions.prefix_extractor.get()));
6085 ASSERT_EQ(get_context.State(), GetContext::kFound);
6086 ASSERT_EQ(value, Slice(kv.second));
6087 value.Reset();
6088 }
6089 }
6090
6091 // Search for non-existent keys
6092 for (auto& kv : kvmap) {
6093 std::string user_key = ExtractUserKey(kv.first).ToString();
6094 user_key.back() = '0'; // make it non-existent key
6095 InternalKey internal_key(user_key, 0, kTypeValue);
6096 std::string encoded_key = internal_key.Encode().ToString();
6097 if (i == 0) { // Search using Seek()
6098 seek_iter->Seek(encoded_key);
6099 ASSERT_OK(seek_iter->status());
6100 if (seek_iter->Valid()) {
6101 ASSERT_TRUE(BytewiseComparator()->Compare(
6102 user_key, ExtractUserKey(seek_iter->key())) < 0);
6103 }
6104 } else { // Search using Get()
6105 PinnableSlice value;
6106 GetContext get_context(options.comparator, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr,
6107 GetContext::kNotFound, user_key, &value, nullptr,
6108 nullptr, nullptr, true, nullptr, nullptr);
6109 ASSERT_OK(reader->Get(ro, encoded_key, &get_context,
6110 moptions.prefix_extractor.get()));
6111 ASSERT_EQ(get_context.State(), GetContext::kNotFound);
6112 value.Reset();
6113 }
6114 }
6115 }
6116}
6117
6118// BlockBasedTableIterator should invalidate itself and return
6119// OutOfBound()=true immediately after Seek(), to allow LevelIterator
6120// filter out corresponding level.
6121TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, OutOfBoundOnSeek) {
6122 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /*convert_to_internal_key*/);
6123 c.Add("foo", "v1");
6124 std::vector<std::string> keys;
6125 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
6126 Options options;
6127 BlockBasedTableOptions table_opt(GetBlockBasedTableOptions());
6128 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_opt));
6129 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
6130 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
6131 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_opt,
6132 GetPlainInternalComparator(BytewiseComparator()), &keys, &kvmap);
6133 auto* reader = c.GetTableReader();
6134 ReadOptions read_opt;
6135 std::string upper_bound = "bar";
6136 Slice upper_bound_slice(upper_bound);
6137 read_opt.iterate_upper_bound = &upper_bound_slice;
6138 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter;
6139 iter.reset(new KeyConvertingIterator(reader->NewIterator(
6140 read_opt, /*prefix_extractor=*/nullptr, /*arena=*/nullptr,
6141 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized)));
6142 iter->SeekToFirst();
6143 ASSERT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
6144 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
6145 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->UpperBoundCheckResult() == IterBoundCheck::kOutOfBound);
6146 iter.reset(new KeyConvertingIterator(reader->NewIterator(
6147 read_opt, /*prefix_extractor=*/nullptr, /*arena=*/nullptr,
6148 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized)));
6149 iter->Seek("foo");
6150 ASSERT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
6151 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
6152 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->UpperBoundCheckResult() == IterBoundCheck::kOutOfBound);
6153}
6154
6155// BlockBasedTableIterator should invalidate itself and return
6156// OutOfBound()=true after Next(), if it finds current index key is no smaller
6157// than upper bound, unless it is pointing to the last data block.
6158TEST_P(BlockBasedTableTest, OutOfBoundOnNext) {
6159 TableConstructor c(BytewiseComparator(), true /*convert_to_internal_key*/);
6160 c.Add("bar", "v");
6161 c.Add("foo", "v");
6162 std::vector<std::string> keys;
6163 stl_wrappers::KVMap kvmap;
6164 Options options;
6165 BlockBasedTableOptions table_opt(GetBlockBasedTableOptions());
6166 table_opt.flush_block_policy_factory =
6167 std::make_shared<FlushBlockEveryKeyPolicyFactory>();
6168 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_opt));
6169 const ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
6170 const MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
6171 c.Finish(options, ioptions, moptions, table_opt,
6172 GetPlainInternalComparator(BytewiseComparator()), &keys, &kvmap);
6173 auto* reader = c.GetTableReader();
6174 ReadOptions read_opt;
6175 std::string ub1 = "bar_after";
6176 Slice ub_slice1(ub1);
6177 read_opt.iterate_upper_bound = &ub_slice1;
6178 std::unique_ptr<InternalIterator> iter;
6179 iter.reset(new KeyConvertingIterator(reader->NewIterator(
6180 read_opt, /*prefix_extractor=*/nullptr, /*arena=*/nullptr,
6181 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized)));
6182 iter->Seek("bar");
6183 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
6184 ASSERT_EQ("bar", iter->key());
6185 iter->Next();
6186 ASSERT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
6187 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->UpperBoundCheckResult() == IterBoundCheck::kOutOfBound);
6188 std::string ub2 = "foo_after";
6189 Slice ub_slice2(ub2);
6190 read_opt.iterate_upper_bound = &ub_slice2;
6191 iter.reset(new KeyConvertingIterator(reader->NewIterator(
6192 read_opt, /*prefix_extractor=*/nullptr, /*arena=*/nullptr,
6193 /*skip_filters=*/false, TableReaderCaller::kUncategorized)));
6194 iter->Seek("foo");
6195 ASSERT_TRUE(iter->Valid());
6196 ASSERT_EQ("foo", iter->key());
6197 iter->Next();
6198 ASSERT_FALSE(iter->Valid());
6199 ASSERT_FALSE(iter->UpperBoundCheckResult() == IterBoundCheck::kOutOfBound);
6200}
6201
6202class ChargeCompressionDictionaryBuildingBufferTest
6203 : public BlockBasedTableTestBase {};
6204TEST_F(ChargeCompressionDictionaryBuildingBufferTest, Basic) {
6205 constexpr std::size_t kSizeDummyEntry = 256 * 1024;
6206 constexpr std::size_t kMetaDataChargeOverhead = 10000;
6207 constexpr std::size_t kCacheCapacity = 8 * 1024 * 1024;
6208 constexpr std::size_t kMaxDictBytes = 1024;
6209 constexpr std::size_t kMaxDictBufferBytes = 1024;
6210
6211 for (CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision
6212 charge_compression_dictionary_building_buffer :
6213 {CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision::kEnabled,
6214 CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision::kDisabled}) {
6215 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
6216 LRUCacheOptions lo;
6217 lo.capacity = kCacheCapacity;
6218 lo.num_shard_bits = 0; // 2^0 shard
6219 lo.strict_capacity_limit = true;
6220 std::shared_ptr<Cache> cache(NewLRUCache(lo));
6221 table_options.block_cache = cache;
6222 table_options.flush_block_policy_factory =
6223 std::make_shared<FlushBlockEveryKeyPolicyFactory>();
6224 table_options.cache_usage_options.options_overrides.insert(
6225 {CacheEntryRole::kCompressionDictionaryBuildingBuffer,
6226 {/*.charged = */ charge_compression_dictionary_building_buffer}});
6227 Options options;
6228 options.compression = kSnappyCompression;
6229 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = kMaxDictBytes;
6230 options.compression_opts.max_dict_buffer_bytes = kMaxDictBufferBytes;
6231 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
6232
6233 test::StringSink* sink = new test::StringSink();
6234 std::unique_ptr<FSWritableFile> holder(sink);
6235 std::unique_ptr<WritableFileWriter> file_writer(new WritableFileWriter(
6236 std::move(holder), "test_file_name", FileOptions()));
6237
6238 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
6239 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
6240 InternalKeyComparator ikc(options.comparator);
6241 InternalTblPropCollFactories internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories;
6242
6243 const ReadOptions read_options;
6244 const WriteOptions write_options;
6245 std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder> builder(
6246 options.table_factory->NewTableBuilder(
6247 TableBuilderOptions(ioptions, moptions, read_options, write_options,
6248 ikc, &internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories,
6249 kSnappyCompression, options.compression_opts,
6250 kUnknownColumnFamily, "test_cf", -1 /* level */,
6251 kUnknownNewestKeyTime),
6252 file_writer.get()));
6253
6254 std::string key1 = "key1";
6255 std::string value1 = "val1";
6256 InternalKey ik1(key1, 0 /* sequnce number */, kTypeValue);
6257 // Adding the first key won't trigger a flush by FlushBlockEveryKeyPolicy
6258 // therefore won't trigger any data block's buffering
6259 builder->Add(ik1.Encode(), value1);
6260 ASSERT_EQ(cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 0 * kSizeDummyEntry);
6261
6262 std::string key2 = "key2";
6263 std::string value2 = "val2";
6264 InternalKey ik2(key2, 1 /* sequnce number */, kTypeValue);
6265 // Adding the second key will trigger a flush of the last data block (the
6266 // one containing key1 and value1) by FlushBlockEveryKeyPolicy and hence
6267 // trigger buffering of that data block.
6268 builder->Add(ik2.Encode(), value2);
6269 // Cache charging will increase for last buffered data block (the one
6270 // containing key1 and value1) since the buffer limit is not exceeded after
6271 // that buffering and the cache will not be full after this reservation
6272 if (charge_compression_dictionary_building_buffer ==
6273 CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision::kEnabled) {
6274 EXPECT_GE(cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 1 * kSizeDummyEntry);
6275 EXPECT_LT(cache->GetPinnedUsage(),
6276 1 * kSizeDummyEntry + kMetaDataChargeOverhead);
6277 } else {
6278 EXPECT_EQ(cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 0 * kSizeDummyEntry);
6279 }
6280
6281 ASSERT_OK(builder->Finish());
6282 EXPECT_EQ(cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 0 * kSizeDummyEntry);
6283 }
6284}
6285
6286TEST_F(ChargeCompressionDictionaryBuildingBufferTest,
6287 BasicWithBufferLimitExceed) {
6288 constexpr std::size_t kSizeDummyEntry = 256 * 1024;
6289 constexpr std::size_t kMetaDataChargeOverhead = 10000;
6290 constexpr std::size_t kCacheCapacity = 8 * 1024 * 1024;
6291 constexpr std::size_t kMaxDictBytes = 1024;
6292 constexpr std::size_t kMaxDictBufferBytes = 2 * kSizeDummyEntry;
6293
6294 // `CacheEntryRoleOptions::charged` is enabled by default for
6295 // CacheEntryRole::kCompressionDictionaryBuildingBuffer
6296 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
6297 LRUCacheOptions lo;
6298 lo.capacity = kCacheCapacity;
6299 lo.num_shard_bits = 0; // 2^0 shard
6300 lo.strict_capacity_limit = true;
6301 std::shared_ptr<Cache> cache(NewLRUCache(lo));
6302 table_options.block_cache = cache;
6303 table_options.flush_block_policy_factory =
6304 std::make_shared<FlushBlockEveryKeyPolicyFactory>();
6305
6306 Options options;
6307 options.compression = kSnappyCompression;
6308 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = kMaxDictBytes;
6309 options.compression_opts.max_dict_buffer_bytes = kMaxDictBufferBytes;
6310 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
6311
6312 test::StringSink* sink = new test::StringSink();
6313 std::unique_ptr<FSWritableFile> holder(sink);
6314 std::unique_ptr<WritableFileWriter> file_writer(new WritableFileWriter(
6315 std::move(holder), "test_file_name", FileOptions()));
6316
6317 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
6318 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
6319 InternalKeyComparator ikc(options.comparator);
6320 InternalTblPropCollFactories internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories;
6321
6322 const ReadOptions read_options;
6323 const WriteOptions write_options;
6324 std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder> builder(options.table_factory->NewTableBuilder(
6325 TableBuilderOptions(ioptions, moptions, read_options, write_options, ikc,
6326 &internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories, kSnappyCompression,
6327 options.compression_opts, kUnknownColumnFamily,
6328 "test_cf", -1 /* level */, kUnknownNewestKeyTime),
6329 file_writer.get()));
6330
6331 std::string key1 = "key1";
6332 std::string value1(kSizeDummyEntry, '0');
6333 InternalKey ik1(key1, 0 /* sequnce number */, kTypeValue);
6334 // Adding the first key won't trigger a flush by FlushBlockEveryKeyPolicy
6335 // therefore won't trigger any data block's buffering
6336 builder->Add(ik1.Encode(), value1);
6337 ASSERT_EQ(cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 0 * kSizeDummyEntry);
6338
6339 std::string key2 = "key2";
6340 std::string value2(kSizeDummyEntry, '0');
6341 InternalKey ik2(key2, 1 /* sequnce number */, kTypeValue);
6342 // Adding the second key will trigger a flush of the last data block (the one
6343 // containing key1 and value1) by FlushBlockEveryKeyPolicy and hence trigger
6344 // buffering of the last data block.
6345 builder->Add(ik2.Encode(), value2);
6346 // Cache charging will increase for last buffered data block (the one
6347 // containing key1 and value1) since the buffer limit is not exceeded after
6348 // the buffering and the cache will not be full after this reservation
6349 EXPECT_GE(cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 2 * kSizeDummyEntry);
6350 EXPECT_LT(cache->GetPinnedUsage(),
6351 2 * kSizeDummyEntry + kMetaDataChargeOverhead);
6352
6353 std::string key3 = "key3";
6354 std::string value3 = "val3";
6355 InternalKey ik3(key3, 2 /* sequnce number */, kTypeValue);
6356 // Adding the third key will trigger a flush of the last data block (the one
6357 // containing key2 and value2) by FlushBlockEveryKeyPolicy and hence trigger
6358 // buffering of the last data block.
6359 builder->Add(ik3.Encode(), value3);
6360 // Cache charging will decrease since the buffer limit is now exceeded
6361 // after the last buffering and EnterUnbuffered() is triggered
6362 EXPECT_EQ(cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 0 * kSizeDummyEntry);
6363
6364 ASSERT_OK(builder->Finish());
6365 EXPECT_EQ(cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 0 * kSizeDummyEntry);
6366}
6367
6368TEST_F(ChargeCompressionDictionaryBuildingBufferTest, BasicWithCacheFull) {
6369 constexpr std::size_t kSizeDummyEntry = 256 * 1024;
6370 constexpr std::size_t kMetaDataChargeOverhead = 10000;
6371 // A small kCacheCapacity is chosen so that increase cache charging for
6372 // buffering two data blocks, each containing key1/value1, key2/a big
6373 // value2, will cause cache full
6374 constexpr std::size_t kCacheCapacity =
6375 1 * kSizeDummyEntry + kSizeDummyEntry / 2;
6376 constexpr std::size_t kMaxDictBytes = 1024;
6377 // A big kMaxDictBufferBytes is chosen so that adding a big key value pair
6378 // (key2, value2) won't exceed the buffer limit
6379 constexpr std::size_t kMaxDictBufferBytes = 1024 * 1024 * 1024;
6380
6381 // `CacheEntryRoleOptions::charged` is enabled by default for
6382 // CacheEntryRole::kCompressionDictionaryBuildingBuffer
6383 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
6384 LRUCacheOptions lo;
6385 lo.capacity = kCacheCapacity;
6386 lo.num_shard_bits = 0; // 2^0 shard
6387 lo.strict_capacity_limit = true;
6388 std::shared_ptr<Cache> cache(NewLRUCache(lo));
6389 table_options.block_cache = cache;
6390 table_options.flush_block_policy_factory =
6391 std::make_shared<FlushBlockEveryKeyPolicyFactory>();
6392
6393 Options options;
6394 options.compression = kSnappyCompression;
6395 options.compression_opts.max_dict_bytes = kMaxDictBytes;
6396 options.compression_opts.max_dict_buffer_bytes = kMaxDictBufferBytes;
6397 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
6398
6399 test::StringSink* sink = new test::StringSink();
6400 std::unique_ptr<FSWritableFile> holder(sink);
6401 std::unique_ptr<WritableFileWriter> file_writer(new WritableFileWriter(
6402 std::move(holder), "test_file_name", FileOptions()));
6403
6404 ImmutableOptions ioptions(options);
6405 MutableCFOptions moptions(options);
6406 InternalKeyComparator ikc(options.comparator);
6407 InternalTblPropCollFactories internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories;
6408
6409 const ReadOptions read_options;
6410 const WriteOptions write_options;
6411 std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder> builder(options.table_factory->NewTableBuilder(
6412 TableBuilderOptions(ioptions, moptions, read_options, write_options, ikc,
6413 &internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories, kSnappyCompression,
6414 options.compression_opts, kUnknownColumnFamily,
6415 "test_cf", -1 /* level */, kUnknownNewestKeyTime),
6416 file_writer.get()));
6417
6418 std::string key1 = "key1";
6419 std::string value1 = "val1";
6420 InternalKey ik1(key1, 0 /* sequnce number */, kTypeValue);
6421 // Adding the first key won't trigger a flush by FlushBlockEveryKeyPolicy
6422 // therefore won't trigger any data block's buffering
6423 builder->Add(ik1.Encode(), value1);
6424 ASSERT_EQ(cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 0 * kSizeDummyEntry);
6425
6426 std::string key2 = "key2";
6427 std::string value2(kSizeDummyEntry, '0');
6428 InternalKey ik2(key2, 1 /* sequnce number */, kTypeValue);
6429 // Adding the second key will trigger a flush of the last data block (the one
6430 // containing key1 and value1) by FlushBlockEveryKeyPolicy and hence trigger
6431 // buffering of the last data block.
6432 builder->Add(ik2.Encode(), value2);
6433 // Cache charging will increase for the last buffered data block (the one
6434 // containing key1 and value1) since the buffer limit is not exceeded after
6435 // the buffering and the cache will not be full after this reservation
6436 EXPECT_GE(cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 1 * kSizeDummyEntry);
6437 EXPECT_LT(cache->GetPinnedUsage(),
6438 1 * kSizeDummyEntry + kMetaDataChargeOverhead);
6439
6440 std::string key3 = "key3";
6441 std::string value3 = "value3";
6442 InternalKey ik3(key3, 2 /* sequnce number */, kTypeValue);
6443 // Adding the third key will trigger a flush of the last data block (the one
6444 // containing key2 and value2) by FlushBlockEveryKeyPolicy and hence trigger
6445 // buffering of the last data block.
6446 builder->Add(ik3.Encode(), value3);
6447 // Cache charging will decrease since the cache is now full after
6448 // increasing reservation for the last buffered block and EnterUnbuffered() is
6449 // triggered
6450 EXPECT_EQ(cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 0 * kSizeDummyEntry);
6451
6452 ASSERT_OK(builder->Finish());
6453 EXPECT_EQ(cache->GetPinnedUsage(), 0 * kSizeDummyEntry);
6454}

6456class CacheUsageOptionsOverridesTest : public DBTestBase {
6457 public:
6458 CacheUsageOptionsOverridesTest()
6459 : DBTestBase("cache_usage_options_overrides_test",
6460 /*env_do_fsync=*/false) {}
6461};
6462
6463TEST_F(CacheUsageOptionsOverridesTest, SanitizeAndValidateOptions) {
6464 // To test `cache_usage_options.options_overrides` is sanitized
6465 // where `cache_usage_options.options` is used when there is no entry in
6466 // `cache_usage_options.options_overrides`
6467 Options options;
6468 options.create_if_missing = true;
6469 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options = BlockBasedTableOptions();
6470 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
6471 Destroy(options);
6472 Status s = TryReopen(options);
6473 EXPECT_TRUE(s.ok());
6474 const auto* sanitized_table_options =
6475 options.table_factory->GetOptions<BlockBasedTableOptions>();
6476 const auto sanitized_options_overrides =
6477 sanitized_table_options->cache_usage_options.options_overrides;
6478 EXPECT_EQ(sanitized_options_overrides.size(), kNumCacheEntryRoles);
6479 for (auto options_overrides_iter = sanitized_options_overrides.cbegin();
6480 options_overrides_iter != sanitized_options_overrides.cend();
6481 ++options_overrides_iter) {
6482 CacheEntryRoleOptions role_options = options_overrides_iter->second;
6483 CacheEntryRoleOptions default_options =
6484 sanitized_table_options->cache_usage_options.options;
6485 EXPECT_TRUE(role_options == default_options);
6486 }
6487 Destroy(options);
6488
6489 // To test option validation on unsupported CacheEntryRole
6490 table_options = BlockBasedTableOptions();
6491 table_options.cache_usage_options.options_overrides.insert(
6492 {CacheEntryRole::kDataBlock,
6493 {/*.charged = */ CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision::kDisabled}});
6494 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
6495 Destroy(options);
6496 s = TryReopen(options);
6497 EXPECT_TRUE(s.IsNotSupported());
6498 EXPECT_TRUE(
6499 s.ToString().find("Enable/Disable CacheEntryRoleOptions::charged") !=
6500 std::string::npos);
6501 EXPECT_TRUE(
6502 s.ToString().find(kCacheEntryRoleToCamelString[static_cast<uint32_t>(
6503 CacheEntryRole::kDataBlock)]) != std::string::npos);
6504 Destroy(options);
6505
6506 // To test option validation on existence of block cache
6507 table_options = BlockBasedTableOptions();
6508 table_options.no_block_cache = true;
6509 table_options.cache_usage_options.options_overrides.insert(
6510 {CacheEntryRole::kFilterConstruction,
6511 {/*.charged = */ CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision::kEnabled}});
6512 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
6513 Destroy(options);
6514 s = TryReopen(options);
6515 EXPECT_TRUE(s.IsInvalidArgument());
6516 EXPECT_TRUE(s.ToString().find("Enable CacheEntryRoleOptions::charged") !=
6517 std::string::npos);
6518 EXPECT_TRUE(
6519 s.ToString().find(kCacheEntryRoleToCamelString[static_cast<std::size_t>(
6520 CacheEntryRole::kFilterConstruction)]) != std::string::npos);
6521 EXPECT_TRUE(s.ToString().find("block cache is disabled") !=
6522 std::string::npos);
6523 Destroy(options);
6524}
6525} // namespace ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE

6529 ::testing::InitGoogleTest(&argc, argv);
6530 return RUN_ALL_TESTS();
6531}
